101 void TextGeneratorOLImpl::writeString(const char *s,bool keepSpaces) const
102 {
103  if (s==0) return;
104  //printf("TextGeneratorOlImpl::writeString('%s',%d)\n",s,keepSpaces);
105  if (keepSpaces)
106  {
107  const char *p=s;
108  if (p)
109  {
110  char cs[2];
111  char c;
112  cs[1]='\0';
113  while ((c=*p++))
114  {
115  if (c==' ') m_od.writeNonBreakableSpace(1);
116  else cs[0]=c,m_od.docify(cs);
117  }
118  }
119  }
120  else
121  {
122  m_od.docify(s);
123  }
124 }
125 
126 void TextGeneratorOLImpl::writeBreak(int indent) const
127 {
128  m_od.lineBreak("typebreak");
129  int i;
130  for (i=0;i<indent;i++)
131  {
132  m_od.writeNonBreakableSpace(3);
133  }
134 }

138  ) const
139 {
140  //printf("TextGeneratorOlImpl::writeLink('%s')\n",text);
141  m_od.writeObjectLink(extRef,file,anchor,text);
142 }

164 QCString removeAnonymousScopes(const QCString &s)
165 {
166  QCString result;
167  if (s.isEmpty()) return result;
168  static QRegExp re("[ :]*@[0-9]+[: ]*");
169  int i,l,sl=s.length();
170  int p=0;
171  while ((i=re.match(s,p,&l))!=-1)
172  {
173  result+=s.mid(p,i-p);
174  int c=i;
175  bool b1=FALSE,b2=FALSE;
176  while (c<i+l && s.at(c)!='@') if (s.at(c++)==':') b1=TRUE;
177  c=i+l-1;
178  while (c>=i && s.at(c)!='@') if (s.at(c--)==':') b2=TRUE;
179  if (b1 && b2)
180  {
181  result+="::";
182  }
183  p=i+l;
184  }
185  result+=s.right(sl-p);
186  //printf("removeAnonymousScopes(`%s')=`%s'\n",s.data(),result.data());
187  return result;
188 }
189 
190 // replace anonymous scopes with __anonymous__ or replacement if provided
191 QCString replaceAnonymousScopes(const QCString &s,const char *replacement)
192 {
193  QCString result;
194  if (s.isEmpty()) return result;
195  static QRegExp re("@[0-9]+");
196  int i,l,sl=s.length();
197  int p=0;
198  while ((i=re.match(s,p,&l))!=-1)
199  {
200  result+=s.mid(p,i-p);
201  if (replacement)
202  {
203  result+=replacement;
204  }
205  else
206  {
207  result+="__anonymous__";
208  }
209  p=i+l;
210  }
211  result+=s.right(sl-p);
212  //printf("replaceAnonymousScopes(`%s')=`%s'\n",s.data(),result.data());
213  return result;
214 }
215 
216 
217 // strip anonymous left hand side part of the scope
218 QCString stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(const QCString &s)
219 {
220  int i,p=0,l;
221  QCString newScope;
222  int sl = s.length();
223  while ((i=getScopeFragment(s,p,&l))!=-1)
224  {
225  //printf("Scope fragment %s\n",s.mid(i,l).data());
226  if (Doxygen::namespaceSDict->find(s.left(i+l))!=0)
227  {
228  if (s.at(i)!='@')
229  {
230  if (!newScope.isEmpty()) newScope+="::";
231  newScope+=s.mid(i,l);
232  }
233  }
234  else if (i<sl)
235  {
236  if (!newScope.isEmpty()) newScope+="::";
237  newScope+=s.right(sl-i);
238  goto done;
239  }
240  p=i+l;
241  }
242 done:
243  //printf("stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(`%s')=`%s'\n",s.data(),newScope.data());
244  return newScope;
245 }

247 void writePageRef(OutputDocInterface &od,const char *cn,const char *mn)
248 {
249  od.pushGeneratorState();
250 
251  od.disable(OutputGenerator::Html);
252  od.disable(OutputGenerator::Man);
253  if (Config_getBool(PDF_HYPERLINKS)) od.disable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
254  if (Config_getBool(RTF_HYPERLINKS)) od.disable(OutputGenerator::RTF);
255  od.startPageRef();
256  od.docify(theTranslator->trPageAbbreviation());
257  od.endPageRef(cn,mn);
258 
259  od.popGeneratorState();
260 }

266 QCString generateMarker(int id)
267 {
268  const int maxMarkerStrLen = 20;
269  char result[maxMarkerStrLen];
270  qsnprintf(result,maxMarkerStrLen,"@%d",id);
271  return result;

274 static QCString stripFromPath(const QCString &path,QStrList &l)
275 {
276  // look at all the strings in the list and strip the longest match
277  const char *s=l.first();
278  QCString potential;
279  unsigned int length = 0;
280  while (s)
281  {
282  QCString prefix = s;
283  if (prefix.length() > length &&
284  qstricmp(path.left(prefix.length()),prefix)==0) // case insensitive compare
285  {
286  length = prefix.length();
287  potential = path.right(path.length()-prefix.length());
288  }
289  s = l.next();
290  }
291  if (length) return potential;
292  return path;
293 }
294 
298 QCString stripFromPath(const QCString &path)

300  return stripFromPath(path,Config_getList(STRIP_FROM_PATH));

315 int guessSection(const char *name)
316 {
317  QCString n=((QCString)name).lower();
318  if (n.right(2)==".c" || // source
319  n.right(3)==".cc" ||
320  n.right(4)==".cxx" ||
321  n.right(4)==".cpp" ||
322  n.right(4)==".c++" ||
323  n.right(5)==".java" ||
324  n.right(2)==".m" ||
325  n.right(2)==".M" ||
326  n.right(3)==".mm" ||
327  n.right(3)==".ii" || // inline
328  n.right(4)==".ixx" ||
329  n.right(4)==".ipp" ||
330  n.right(4)==".i++" ||
331  n.right(4)==".inl" ||
332  n.right(4)==".xml" ||
333  n.right(4)==".sql"
334  ) return Entry::SOURCE_SEC;
335  if (n.right(2)==".h" || // header
336  n.right(3)==".hh" ||
337  n.right(4)==".hxx" ||
338  n.right(4)==".hpp" ||
339  n.right(4)==".h++" ||
340  n.right(4)==".idl" ||
341  n.right(4)==".ddl" ||
342  n.right(5)==".pidl"
343  ) return Entry::HEADER_SEC;
344  return 0;
345 }
346 
347 QCString resolveTypeDef(Definition *context,const QCString &qualifiedName,
348  Definition **typedefContext)
349 {
350  //printf("<<resolveTypeDef(%s,%s)\n",
351  // context ? context->name().data() : "<none>",qualifiedName.data());
352  QCString result;
353  if (qualifiedName.isEmpty())
354  {
355  //printf(" qualified name empty!\n");
356  return result;
357  }
358 
359  Definition *mContext=context;
360  if (typedefContext) *typedefContext=context;
361 
362  // see if the qualified name has a scope part
363  int scopeIndex = qualifiedName.findRev("::");
364  QCString resName=qualifiedName;
365  if (scopeIndex!=-1) // strip scope part for the name
366  {
367  resName=qualifiedName.right(qualifiedName.length()-scopeIndex-2);
368  if (resName.isEmpty())
369  {
370  // qualifiedName was of form A:: !
371  //printf(" qualified name of form A::!\n");
372  return result;
373  }
374  }
375  MemberDef *md=0;
376  while (mContext && md==0)
377  {
378  // step 1: get the right scope
379  Definition *resScope=mContext;
380  if (scopeIndex!=-1)
381  {
382  // split-off scope part
383  QCString resScopeName = qualifiedName.left(scopeIndex);
384  //printf("resScopeName=`%s'\n",resScopeName.data());
385 
386  // look-up scope in context
387  int is,ps=0;
388  int l;
389  while ((is=getScopeFragment(resScopeName,ps,&l))!=-1)
390  {
391  QCString qualScopePart = resScopeName.mid(is,l);
392  QCString tmp = resolveTypeDef(mContext,qualScopePart);
393  if (!tmp.isEmpty()) qualScopePart=tmp;
394  resScope = resScope->findInnerCompound(qualScopePart);
395  //printf("qualScopePart=`%s' resScope=%p\n",qualScopePart.data(),resScope);
396  if (resScope==0) break;
397  ps=is+l;
398  }
399  }
400  //printf("resScope=%s\n",resScope?resScope->name().data():"<none>");
401 
402  // step 2: get the member
403  if (resScope) // no scope or scope found in the current context
404  {
405  //printf("scope found: %s, look for typedef %s\n",
406  // resScope->qualifiedName().data(),resName.data());
407  MemberNameSDict *mnd=0;
408  if (resScope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass)
409  {
410  mnd=Doxygen::memberNameSDict;
411  }
412  else
413  {
414  mnd=Doxygen::functionNameSDict;
415  }
416  MemberName *mn=mnd->find(resName);
417  if (mn)
418  {
419  MemberNameIterator mni(*mn);
420  MemberDef *tmd=0;
421  int minDist=-1;
422  for (;(tmd=mni.current());++mni)
423  {
424  //printf("Found member %s resScope=%s outerScope=%s mContext=%p\n",
425  // tmd->name().data(), resScope->name().data(),
426  // tmd->getOuterScope()->name().data(), mContext);
427  if (tmd->isTypedef() /*&& tmd->getOuterScope()==resScope*/)
428  {
429  int dist=isAccessibleFrom(resScope,0,tmd);
430  if (dist!=-1 && (md==0 || dist<minDist))
431  {
432  md = tmd;
433  minDist = dist;
434  }
435  }
436  }
437  }
438  }
439  mContext=mContext->getOuterScope();
440  }
441 
442  // step 3: get the member's type
443  if (md)
444  {
445  //printf(">>resolveTypeDef: Found typedef name `%s' in scope `%s' value=`%s' args='%s'\n",
446  // qualifiedName.data(),context->name().data(),md->typeString(),md->argsString()
447  // );
448  result=md->typeString();
449  QCString args = md->argsString();
450  if (args.find(")(")!=-1) // typedef of a function/member pointer
451  {
452  result+=args;
453  }
454  else if (args.find('[')!=-1) // typedef of an array
455  {
456  result+=args;
457  }
458  if (typedefContext) *typedefContext=md->getOuterScope();
459  }
460  else
461  {
462  //printf(">>resolveTypeDef: Typedef `%s' not found in scope `%s'!\n",
463  // qualifiedName.data(),context ? context->name().data() : "<global>");
464  }
465  return result;
466 
467 }

473 ClassDef *getClass(const char *n)
474 {
475  if (n==0 || n[0]=='\0') return 0;
476  QCString name=n;
477  ClassDef *result = Doxygen::classSDict->find(name);
478  //if (result==0 && !exact) // also try generic and protocol versions
479  //{
480  // result = Doxygen::classSDict->find(name+"-g");
481  // if (result==0)
482  // {
483  // result = Doxygen::classSDict->find(name+"-p");
484  // }
485  //}
486  //printf("getClass(%s)=%s\n",n,result?result->name().data():"<none>");
487  return result;
488 }
489 
490 NamespaceDef *getResolvedNamespace(const char *name)
491 {
492  if (name==0 || name[0]=='\0') return 0;
493  QCString *subst = Doxygen::namespaceAliasDict[name];
494  if (subst)
495  {
496  int count=0; // recursion detection guard
497  QCString *newSubst;
498  while ((newSubst=Doxygen::namespaceAliasDict[*subst]) && count<10)
499  {
500  subst=newSubst;
501  count++;
502  }
503  if (count==10)
504  {
505  warn_uncond("possible recursive namespace alias detected for %s!\n",name);
506  }
507  return Doxygen::namespaceSDict->find(subst->data());
508  }
509  else
510  {
511  return Doxygen::namespaceSDict->find(name);
512  }
513 }

515 static QDict<MemberDef> g_resolvedTypedefs;
516 static QDict<Definition> g_visitedNamespaces;
517 
518 // forward declaration
519 static ClassDef *getResolvedClassRec(Definition *scope,
520  FileDef *fileScope,
521  const char *n,
522  MemberDef **pTypeDef,
523  QCString *pTemplSpec,
524  QCString *pResolvedType
525  );
526 int isAccessibleFromWithExpScope(Definition *scope,FileDef *fileScope,Definition *item,
527  const QCString &explicitScopePart);
528 
536 ClassDef *newResolveTypedef(FileDef *fileScope,MemberDef *md,
537  MemberDef **pMemType,QCString *pTemplSpec,
538  QCString *pResolvedType,
539  ArgumentList *actTemplParams)
540 {
541  //printf("newResolveTypedef(md=%p,cachedVal=%p)\n",md,md->getCachedTypedefVal());
542  bool isCached = md->isTypedefValCached(); // value already cached
543  if (isCached)
544  {
545  //printf("Already cached %s->%s [%s]\n",
546  // md->name().data(),
547  // md->getCachedTypedefVal()?md->getCachedTypedefVal()->name().data():"<none>",
548  // md->getCachedResolvedTypedef()?md->getCachedResolvedTypedef().data():"<none>");
549 
550  if (pTemplSpec) *pTemplSpec = md->getCachedTypedefTemplSpec();
551  if (pResolvedType) *pResolvedType = md->getCachedResolvedTypedef();
552  return md->getCachedTypedefVal();
553  }
554  //printf("new typedef\n");
555  QCString qname = md->qualifiedName();
556  if (g_resolvedTypedefs.find(qname)) return 0; // typedef already done
557 
558  g_resolvedTypedefs.insert(qname,md); // put on the trace list
559 
560  ClassDef *typeClass = md->getClassDef();
561  QCString type = md->typeString(); // get the "value" of the typedef
562  if (typeClass && typeClass->isTemplate() &&
563  actTemplParams && actTemplParams->count()>0)
564  {
565  type = substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(type,
566  typeClass->templateArguments(),actTemplParams);
567  }
568  QCString typedefValue = type;
569  int tl=type.length();
570  int ip=tl-1; // remove * and & at the end
571  while (ip>=0 && (type.at(ip)=='*' || type.at(ip)=='&' || type.at(ip)==' '))
572  {
573  ip--;
574  }
575  type=type.left(ip+1);
576  type.stripPrefix("const "); // strip leading "const"
577  type.stripPrefix("struct "); // strip leading "struct"
578  type.stripPrefix("union "); // strip leading "union"
579  int sp=0;
580  tl=type.length(); // length may have been changed
581  while (sp<tl && type.at(sp)==' ') sp++;
582  MemberDef *memTypeDef = 0;
583  ClassDef *result = getResolvedClassRec(md->getOuterScope(),
584  fileScope,type,&memTypeDef,0,pResolvedType);
585  // if type is a typedef then return what it resolves to.
586  if (memTypeDef && memTypeDef->isTypedef())
587  {
588  result=newResolveTypedef(fileScope,memTypeDef,pMemType,pTemplSpec);
589  goto done;
590  }
591  else if (memTypeDef && memTypeDef->isEnumerate() && pMemType)
592  {
593  *pMemType = memTypeDef;
594  }
595 
596  //printf("type=%s result=%p\n",type.data(),result);
597  if (result==0)
598  {
599  // try unspecialized version if type is template
600  int si=type.findRev("::");
601  int i=type.find('<');
602  if (si==-1 && i!=-1) // typedef of a template => try the unspecialized version
603  {
604  if (pTemplSpec) *pTemplSpec = type.mid(i);
605  result = getResolvedClassRec(md->getOuterScope(),fileScope,
606  type.left(i),0,0,pResolvedType);
607  //printf("result=%p pRresolvedType=%s sp=%d ip=%d tl=%d\n",
608  // result,pResolvedType?pResolvedType->data():"<none>",sp,ip,tl);
609  }
610  else if (si!=-1) // A::B
611  {
612  i=type.find('<',si);
613  if (i==-1) // Something like A<T>::B => lookup A::B
614  {
615  i=type.length();
616  }
617  else // Something like A<T>::B<S> => lookup A::B, spec=<S>
618  {
619  if (pTemplSpec) *pTemplSpec = type.mid(i);
620  }
621  result = getResolvedClassRec(md->getOuterScope(),fileScope,
622  stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(type.left(i),FALSE),0,0,
623  pResolvedType);
624  }
625 
626  //if (result) ip=si+sp+1;
627  }
628 
629 done:
630  if (pResolvedType)
631  {
632  if (result)
633  {
634  *pResolvedType=result->qualifiedName();
635  //printf("*pResolvedType=%s\n",pResolvedType->data());
636  if (sp>0) pResolvedType->prepend(typedefValue.left(sp));
637  if (ip<tl-1) pResolvedType->append(typedefValue.right(tl-ip-1));
638  }
639  else
640  {
641  *pResolvedType=typedefValue;
642  }
643  }
644 
645  // remember computed value for next time
646  if (result && result->getDefFileName()!="<code>")
647  // this check is needed to prevent that temporary classes that are
648  // introduced while parsing code fragments are being cached here.
649  {
650  //printf("setting cached typedef %p in result %p\n",md,result);
651  //printf("==> %s (%s,%d)\n",result->name().data(),result->getDefFileName().data(),result->getDefLine());
652  //printf("*pResolvedType=%s\n",pResolvedType?pResolvedType->data():"<none>");
653  md->cacheTypedefVal(result,
654  pTemplSpec ? *pTemplSpec : QCString(),
655  pResolvedType ? *pResolvedType : QCString()
656  );
657  }
658 
659  g_resolvedTypedefs.remove(qname); // remove from the trace list
660 
661  return result;
662 }
663 
667 static QCString substTypedef(Definition *scope,FileDef *fileScope,const QCString &name,
668  MemberDef **pTypeDef=0)
669 {
670  QCString result=name;
671  if (name.isEmpty()) return result;
672 
673  // lookup scope fragment in the symbol map
674  DefinitionIntf *di = Doxygen::symbolMap->find(name);
675  if (di==0) return result; // no matches
676 
677  MemberDef *bestMatch=0;
678  if (di->definitionType()==DefinitionIntf::TypeSymbolList) // multi symbols
679  {
680  // search for the best match
681  DefinitionListIterator dli(*(DefinitionList*)di);
682  Definition *d;
683  int minDistance=10000; // init at "infinite"
684  for (dli.toFirst();(d=dli.current());++dli) // foreach definition
685  {
686  // only look at members
687  if (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeMember)
688  {
689  // that are also typedefs
690  MemberDef *md = (MemberDef *)d;
691  if (md->isTypedef()) // d is a typedef
692  {
693  // test accessibility of typedef within scope.
694  int distance = isAccessibleFromWithExpScope(scope,fileScope,d,"");
695  if (distance!=-1 && distance<minDistance)
696  // definition is accessible and a better match
697  {
698  minDistance=distance;
699  bestMatch = md;
700  }
701  }
702  }
703  }
704  }
705  else if (di->definitionType()==DefinitionIntf::TypeMember) // single symbol
706  {
707  Definition *d = (Definition*)di;
708  // that are also typedefs
709  MemberDef *md = (MemberDef *)di;
710  if (md->isTypedef()) // d is a typedef
711  {
712  // test accessibility of typedef within scope.
713  int distance = isAccessibleFromWithExpScope(scope,fileScope,d,"");
714  if (distance!=-1) // definition is accessible
715  {
716  bestMatch = md;
717  }
718  }
719  }
720  if (bestMatch)
721  {
722  result = bestMatch->typeString();
723  if (pTypeDef) *pTypeDef=bestMatch;
724  }
725 
726  //printf("substTypedef(%s,%s)=%s\n",scope?scope->name().data():"<global>",
727  // name.data(),result.data());
728  return result;
729 }
730 
731 static Definition *endOfPathIsUsedClass(SDict<Definition> *cl,const QCString &localName)
732 {
733  if (cl)
734  {
735  SDict<Definition>::Iterator cli(*cl);
736  Definition *cd;
737  for (cli.toFirst();(cd=cli.current());++cli)
738  {
739  if (cd->localName()==localName)
740  {
741  return cd;
742  }
743  }
744  }
745  return 0;
746 }
747 
753 static Definition *followPath(Definition *start,FileDef *fileScope,const QCString &path)
754 {
755  int is,ps;
756  int l;
757  Definition *current=start;
758  ps=0;
759  //printf("followPath: start='%s' path='%s'\n",start?start->name().data():"<none>",path.data());
760  // for each part of the explicit scope
761  while ((is=getScopeFragment(path,ps,&l))!=-1)
762  {
763  // try to resolve the part if it is a typedef
764  MemberDef *typeDef=0;
765  QCString qualScopePart = substTypedef(current,fileScope,path.mid(is,l),&typeDef);
766  //printf(" qualScopePart=%s\n",qualScopePart.data());
767  if (typeDef)
768  {
769  ClassDef *type = newResolveTypedef(fileScope,typeDef);
770  if (type)
771  {
772  //printf("Found type %s\n",type->name().data());
773  return type;
774  }
775  }
776  Definition *next = current->findInnerCompound(qualScopePart);
777  //printf("++ Looking for %s inside %s result %s\n",
778  // qualScopePart.data(),
779  // current->name().data(),
780  // next?next->name().data():"<null>");
781  if (next==0) // failed to follow the path
782  {
783  //printf("==> next==0!\n");
784  if (current->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace)
785  {
786  next = endOfPathIsUsedClass(
787  ((NamespaceDef *)current)->getUsedClasses(),qualScopePart);
788  }
789  else if (current->definitionType()==Definition::TypeFile)
790  {
791  next = endOfPathIsUsedClass(
792  ((FileDef *)current)->getUsedClasses(),qualScopePart);
793  }
794  current = next;
795  if (current==0) break;
796  }
797  else // continue to follow scope
798  {
799  current = next;
800  //printf("==> current = %p\n",current);
801  }
802  ps=is+l;
803  }
804  //printf("followPath(start=%s,path=%s) result=%s\n",
805  // start->name().data(),path.data(),current?current->name().data():"<null>");
806  return current; // path could be followed
807 }
808 
809 bool accessibleViaUsingClass(const SDict<Definition> *cl,
810  FileDef *fileScope,
811  Definition *item,
812  const QCString &explicitScopePart=""
813  )
814 {
815  //printf("accessibleViaUsingClass(%p)\n",cl);
816  if (cl) // see if the class was imported via a using statement
817  {
818  SDict<Definition>::Iterator cli(*cl);
819  Definition *ucd;
820  bool explicitScopePartEmpty = explicitScopePart.isEmpty();
821  for (cli.toFirst();(ucd=cli.current());++cli)
822  {
823  //printf("Trying via used class %s\n",ucd->name().data());
824  Definition *sc = explicitScopePartEmpty ? ucd : followPath(ucd,fileScope,explicitScopePart);
825  if (sc && sc==item) return TRUE;
826  //printf("Try via used class done\n");
827  }
828  }
829  return FALSE;
830 }
831 
832 bool accessibleViaUsingNamespace(const NamespaceSDict *nl,
833  FileDef *fileScope,
834  Definition *item,
835  const QCString &explicitScopePart="")
836 {
837  static QDict<void> visitedDict;
838  if (nl) // check used namespaces for the class
839  {
840  NamespaceSDict::Iterator nli(*nl);
841  NamespaceDef *und;
842  int count=0;
843  for (nli.toFirst();(und=nli.current());++nli,count++)
844  {
845  //printf("[Trying via used namespace %s: count=%d/%d\n",und->name().data(),
846  // count,nl->count());
847  Definition *sc = explicitScopePart.isEmpty() ? und : followPath(und,fileScope,explicitScopePart);
848  if (sc && item->getOuterScope()==sc)
849  {
850  //printf("] found it\n");
851  return TRUE;
852  }
853  QCString key=und->name();
854  if (und->getUsedNamespaces() && visitedDict.find(key)==0)
855  {
856  visitedDict.insert(key,(void *)0x08);
857 
858  if (accessibleViaUsingNamespace(und->getUsedNamespaces(),fileScope,item,explicitScopePart))
859  {
860  //printf("] found it via recursion\n");
861  return TRUE;
862  }
863 
864  visitedDict.remove(key);
865  }
866  //printf("] Try via used namespace done\n");
867  }
868  }
869  return FALSE;
870 }
871 
872 const int MAX_STACK_SIZE = 1000;
873 
877 class AccessStack
878 {
879  public:
880  AccessStack() : m_index(0) {}
881  void push(Definition *scope,FileDef *fileScope,Definition *item)
882  {
883  if (m_index<MAX_STACK_SIZE)
884  {
885  m_elements[m_index].scope = scope;
886  m_elements[m_index].fileScope = fileScope;
887  m_elements[m_index].item = item;
888  m_index++;
889  }
890  }
891  void push(Definition *scope,FileDef *fileScope,Definition *item,const QCString &expScope)
892  {
893  if (m_index<MAX_STACK_SIZE)
894  {
895  m_elements[m_index].scope = scope;
896  m_elements[m_index].fileScope = fileScope;
897  m_elements[m_index].item = item;
898  m_elements[m_index].expScope = expScope;
899  m_index++;
900  }
901  }
902  void pop()
903  {
904  if (m_index>0) m_index--;
905  }
906  bool find(Definition *scope,FileDef *fileScope, Definition *item)
907  {
908  int i=0;
909  for (i=0;i<m_index;i++)
910  {
911  AccessElem *e = &m_elements[i];
912  if (e->scope==scope && e->fileScope==fileScope && e->item==item)
913  {
914  return TRUE;
915  }
916  }
917  return FALSE;
918  }
919  bool find(Definition *scope,FileDef *fileScope, Definition *item,const QCString &expScope)
920  {
921  int i=0;
922  for (i=0;i<m_index;i++)
923  {
924  AccessElem *e = &m_elements[i];
925  if (e->scope==scope && e->fileScope==fileScope && e->item==item && e->expScope==expScope)
926  {
927  return TRUE;
928  }
929  }
930  return FALSE;
931  }
932 
933  private:
935  struct AccessElem
936  {
937  Definition *scope;
938  FileDef *fileScope;
939  Definition *item;
940  QCString expScope;
941  };
942  int m_index;
943  AccessElem m_elements[MAX_STACK_SIZE];
944 };
945 
946 /* Returns the "distance" (=number of levels up) from item to scope, or -1
947  * if item in not inside scope.
948  */
949 int isAccessibleFrom(Definition *scope,FileDef *fileScope,Definition *item)
950 {
951  //printf("<isAccesibleFrom(scope=%s,item=%s itemScope=%s)\n",
952  // scope->name().data(),item->name().data(),item->getOuterScope()->name().data());
953 
954  static AccessStack accessStack;
955  if (accessStack.find(scope,fileScope,item))
956  {
957  return -1;
958  }
959  accessStack.push(scope,fileScope,item);
960 
961  int result=0; // assume we found it
962  int i;
963 
964  Definition *itemScope=item->getOuterScope();
965  bool memberAccessibleFromScope =
966  (item->definitionType()==Definition::TypeMember && // a member
967  itemScope && itemScope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass && // of a class
968  scope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass && // accessible
969  ((ClassDef*)scope)->isAccessibleMember((MemberDef *)item) // from scope
970  );
971  bool nestedClassInsideBaseClass =
972  (item->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass && // a nested class
973  itemScope && itemScope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass && // inside a base
974  scope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass && // class of scope
975  ((ClassDef*)scope)->isBaseClass((ClassDef*)itemScope,TRUE)
976  );
977 
978  if (itemScope==scope || memberAccessibleFromScope || nestedClassInsideBaseClass)
979  {
980  //printf("> found it\n");
981  if (nestedClassInsideBaseClass) result++; // penalty for base class to prevent
982  // this is preferred over nested class in this class
983  // see bug 686956
984  }
985  else if (scope==Doxygen::globalScope)
986  {
987  if (fileScope)
988  {
989  SDict<Definition> *cl = fileScope->getUsedClasses();
990  if (accessibleViaUsingClass(cl,fileScope,item))
991  {
992  //printf("> found via used class\n");
993  goto done;
994  }
995  NamespaceSDict *nl = fileScope->getUsedNamespaces();
996  if (accessibleViaUsingNamespace(nl,fileScope,item))
997  {
998  //printf("> found via used namespace\n");
999  goto done;
1000  }
1001  }
1002  //printf("> reached global scope\n");
1003  result=-1; // not found in path to globalScope
1004  }
1005  else // keep searching
1006  {
1007  // check if scope is a namespace, which is using other classes and namespaces
1008  if (scope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace)
1009  {
1010  NamespaceDef *nscope = (NamespaceDef*)scope;
1011  //printf(" %s is namespace with %d used classes\n",nscope->name().data(),nscope->getUsedClasses());
1012  SDict<Definition> *cl = nscope->getUsedClasses();
1013  if (accessibleViaUsingClass(cl,fileScope,item))
1014  {
1015  //printf("> found via used class\n");
1016  goto done;
1017  }
1018  NamespaceSDict *nl = nscope->getUsedNamespaces();
1019  if (accessibleViaUsingNamespace(nl,fileScope,item))
1020  {
1021  //printf("> found via used namespace\n");
1022  goto done;
1023  }
1024  }
1025  // repeat for the parent scope
1026  i=isAccessibleFrom(scope->getOuterScope(),fileScope,item);
1027  //printf("> result=%d\n",i);
1028  result= (i==-1) ? -1 : i+2;
1029  }
1030 done:
1031  accessStack.pop();
1032  //Doxygen::lookupCache.insert(key,new int(result));
1033  return result;
1034 }
1035 
1036 
1037 /* Returns the "distance" (=number of levels up) from item to scope, or -1
1038  * if item in not in this scope. The explicitScopePart limits the search
1039  * to scopes that match \a scope (or its parent scope(s)) plus the explicit part.
1040  * Example:
1041  *
1042  * class A { public: class I {}; };
1043  * class B { public: class J {}; };
1044  *
1045  * - Looking for item=='J' inside scope=='B' will return 0.
1046  * - Looking for item=='I' inside scope=='B' will return -1
1047  * (as it is not found in B nor in the global scope).
1048  * - Looking for item=='A::I' inside scope=='B', first the match B::A::I is tried but
1049  * not found and then A::I is searched in the global scope, which matches and
1050  * thus the result is 1.
1051  */
1052 int isAccessibleFromWithExpScope(Definition *scope,FileDef *fileScope,
1053  Definition *item,const QCString &explicitScopePart)
1054 {
1055  if (explicitScopePart.isEmpty())
1056  {
1057  // handle degenerate case where there is no explicit scope.
1058  return isAccessibleFrom(scope,fileScope,item);
1059  }
1060 
1061  static AccessStack accessStack;
1062  if (accessStack.find(scope,fileScope,item,explicitScopePart))
1063  {
1064  return -1;
1065  }
1066  accessStack.push(scope,fileScope,item,explicitScopePart);
1067 
1068 
1069  //printf(" <isAccessibleFromWithExpScope(%s,%s,%s)\n",scope?scope->name().data():"<global>",
1070  // item?item->name().data():"<none>",
1071  // explicitScopePart.data());
1072  int result=0; // assume we found it
1073  Definition *newScope = followPath(scope,fileScope,explicitScopePart);
1074  if (newScope) // explicitScope is inside scope => newScope is the result
1075  {
1076  Definition *itemScope = item->getOuterScope();
1077  //printf(" scope traversal successful %s<->%s!\n",itemScope->name().data(),newScope->name().data());
1078  //if (newScope && newScope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass)
1079  //{
1080  // ClassDef *cd = (ClassDef *)newScope;
1081  // printf("---> Class %s: bases=%p\n",cd->name().data(),cd->baseClasses());
1082  //}
1083  if (itemScope==newScope) // exact match of scopes => distance==0
1084  {
1085  //printf("> found it\n");
1086  }
1087  else if (itemScope && newScope &&
1088  itemScope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass &&
1089  newScope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass &&
1090  ((ClassDef*)newScope)->isBaseClass((ClassDef*)itemScope,TRUE,0)
1091  )
1092  {
1093  // inheritance is also ok. Example: looking for B::I, where
1094  // class A { public: class I {} };
1095  // class B : public A {}
1096  // but looking for B::I, where
1097  // class A { public: class I {} };
1098  // class B { public: class I {} };
1099  // will find A::I, so we still prefer a direct match and give this one a distance of 1
1100  result=1;
1101 
1102  //printf("scope(%s) is base class of newScope(%s)\n",
1103  // scope->name().data(),newScope->name().data());
1104  }
1105  else
1106  {
1107  int i=-1;
1108  if (newScope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace)
1109  {
1110  g_visitedNamespaces.insert(newScope->name(),newScope);
1111  // this part deals with the case where item is a class
1112  // A::B::C but is explicit referenced as A::C, where B is imported
1113  // in A via a using directive.
1114  //printf("newScope is a namespace: %s!\n",newScope->name().data());
1115  NamespaceDef *nscope = (NamespaceDef*)newScope;
1116  SDict<Definition> *cl = nscope->getUsedClasses();
1117  if (cl)
1118  {
1119  SDict<Definition>::Iterator cli(*cl);
1120  Definition *cd;
1121  for (cli.toFirst();(cd=cli.current());++cli)
1122  {
1123  //printf("Trying for class %s\n",cd->name().data());
1124  if (cd==item)
1125  {
1126  //printf("> class is used in this scope\n");
1127  goto done;
1128  }
1129  }
1130  }
1131  NamespaceSDict *nl = nscope->getUsedNamespaces();
1132  if (nl)
1133  {
1134  NamespaceSDict::Iterator nli(*nl);
1135  NamespaceDef *nd;
1136  for (nli.toFirst();(nd=nli.current());++nli)
1137  {
1138  if (g_visitedNamespaces.find(nd->name())==0)
1139  {
1140  //printf("Trying for namespace %s\n",nd->name().data());
1141  i = isAccessibleFromWithExpScope(scope,fileScope,item,nd->name());
1142  if (i!=-1)
1143  {
1144  //printf("> found via explicit scope of used namespace\n");
1145  goto done;
1146  }
1147  }
1148  }
1149  }
1150  }
1151  // repeat for the parent scope
1152  if (scope!=Doxygen::globalScope)
1153  {
1154  i = isAccessibleFromWithExpScope(scope->getOuterScope(),fileScope,
1155  item,explicitScopePart);
1156  }
1157  //printf(" | result=%d\n",i);
1158  result = (i==-1) ? -1 : i+2;
1159  }
1160  }
1161  else // failed to resolve explicitScope
1162  {
1163  //printf(" failed to resolve: scope=%s\n",scope->name().data());
1164  if (scope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace)
1165  {
1166  NamespaceDef *nscope = (NamespaceDef*)scope;
1167  NamespaceSDict *nl = nscope->getUsedNamespaces();
1168  if (accessibleViaUsingNamespace(nl,fileScope,item,explicitScopePart))
1169  {
1170  //printf("> found in used namespace\n");
1171  goto done;
1172  }
1173  }
1174  if (scope==Doxygen::globalScope)
1175  {
1176  if (fileScope)
1177  {
1178  NamespaceSDict *nl = fileScope->getUsedNamespaces();
1179  if (accessibleViaUsingNamespace(nl,fileScope,item,explicitScopePart))
1180  {
1181  //printf("> found in used namespace\n");
1182  goto done;
1183  }
1184  }
1185  //printf("> not found\n");
1186  result=-1;
1187  }
1188  else // continue by looking into the parent scope
1189  {
1190  int i=isAccessibleFromWithExpScope(scope->getOuterScope(),fileScope,
1191  item,explicitScopePart);
1192  //printf("> result=%d\n",i);
1193  result= (i==-1) ? -1 : i+2;
1194  }
1195  }
1196 
1197 done:
1198  //printf(" > result=%d\n",result);
1199  accessStack.pop();
1200  //Doxygen::lookupCache.insert(key,new int(result));
1201  return result;
1202 }
1203 
1204 int computeQualifiedIndex(const QCString &name)
1205 {
1206  int i = name.find('<');
1207  return name.findRev("::",i==-1 ? name.length() : i);
1208 }
1209 
1210 static void getResolvedSymbol(Definition *scope,
1211  FileDef *fileScope,
1212  Definition *d,
1213  const QCString &explicitScopePart,
1214  ArgumentList *actTemplParams,
1215  int &minDistance,
1216  ClassDef *&bestMatch,
1217  MemberDef *&bestTypedef,
1218  QCString &bestTemplSpec,
1219  QCString &bestResolvedType
1220  )
1221 {
1222  //printf(" => found type %x name=%s d=%p\n",
1223  // d->definitionType(),d->name().data(),d);
1224 
1225  // only look at classes and members that are enums or typedefs
1226  if (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass ||
1227  (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeMember &&
1228  (((MemberDef*)d)->isTypedef() || ((MemberDef*)d)->isEnumerate())
1229  )
1230  )
1231  {
1232  g_visitedNamespaces.clear();
1233  // test accessibility of definition within scope.
1234  int distance = isAccessibleFromWithExpScope(scope,fileScope,d,explicitScopePart);
1235  //printf(" %s; distance %s (%p) is %d\n",scope->name().data(),d->name().data(),d,distance);
1236  if (distance!=-1) // definition is accessible
1237  {
1238  // see if we are dealing with a class or a typedef
1239  if (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass) // d is a class
1240  {
1241  ClassDef *cd = (ClassDef *)d;
1242  //printf("cd=%s\n",cd->name().data());
1243  if (!cd->isTemplateArgument()) // skip classes that
1244  // are only there to
1245  // represent a template
1246  // argument
1247  {
1248  //printf("is not a templ arg\n");
1249  if (distance<minDistance) // found a definition that is "closer"
1250  {
1251  minDistance=distance;
1252  bestMatch = cd;
1253  bestTypedef = 0;
1254  bestTemplSpec.resize(0);
1255  bestResolvedType = cd->qualifiedName();
1256  }
1257  else if (distance==minDistance &&
1258  fileScope && bestMatch &&
1259  fileScope->getUsedNamespaces() &&
1260  d->getOuterScope()->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace &&
1261  bestMatch->getOuterScope()==Doxygen::globalScope
1262  )
1263  {
1264  // in case the distance is equal it could be that a class X
1265  // is defined in a namespace and in the global scope. When searched
1266  // in the global scope the distance is 0 in both cases. We have
1267  // to choose one of the definitions: we choose the one in the
1268  // namespace if the fileScope imports namespaces and the definition
1269  // found was in a namespace while the best match so far isn't.
1270  // Just a non-perfect heuristic but it could help in some situations
1271  // (kdecore code is an example).
1272  minDistance=distance;
1273  bestMatch = cd;
1274  bestTypedef = 0;
1275  bestTemplSpec.resize(0);
1276  bestResolvedType = cd->qualifiedName();
1277  }
1278  }
1279  else
1280  {
1281  //printf(" is a template argument!\n");
1282  }
1283  }
1284  else if (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeMember)
1285  {
1286  MemberDef *md = (MemberDef *)d;
1287  //printf(" member isTypedef()=%d\n",md->isTypedef());
1288  if (md->isTypedef()) // d is a typedef
1289  {
1290  QCString args=md->argsString();
1291  if (args.isEmpty()) // do not expand "typedef t a[4];"
1292  {
1293  //printf(" found typedef!\n");
1294 
1295  // we found a symbol at this distance, but if it didn't
1296  // resolve to a class, we still have to make sure that
1297  // something at a greater distance does not match, since
1298  // that symbol is hidden by this one.
1299  if (distance<minDistance)
1300  {
1301  QCString spec;
1302  QCString type;
1303  minDistance=distance;
1304  MemberDef *enumType = 0;
1305  ClassDef *cd = newResolveTypedef(fileScope,md,&enumType,&spec,&type,actTemplParams);
1306  if (cd) // type resolves to a class
1307  {
1308  //printf(" bestTypeDef=%p spec=%s type=%s\n",md,spec.data(),type.data());
1309  bestMatch = cd;
1310  bestTypedef = md;
1311  bestTemplSpec = spec;
1312  bestResolvedType = type;
1313  }
1314  else if (enumType) // type resolves to a enum
1315  {
1316  //printf(" is enum\n");
1317  bestMatch = 0;
1318  bestTypedef = enumType;
1319  bestTemplSpec = "";
1320  bestResolvedType = enumType->qualifiedName();
1321  }
1322  else if (md->isReference()) // external reference
1323  {
1324  bestMatch = 0;
1325  bestTypedef = md;
1326  bestTemplSpec = spec;
1327  bestResolvedType = type;
1328  }
1329  else
1330  {
1331  bestMatch = 0;
1332  bestTypedef = md;
1333  bestTemplSpec.resize(0);
1334  bestResolvedType.resize(0);
1335  //printf(" no match\n");
1336  }
1337  }
1338  else
1339  {
1340  //printf(" not the best match %d min=%d\n",distance,minDistance);
1341  }
1342  }
1343  else
1344  {
1345  //printf(" not a simple typedef\n")
1346  }
1347  }
1348  else if (md->isEnumerate())
1349  {
1350  if (distance<minDistance)
1351  {
1352  minDistance=distance;
1353  bestMatch = 0;
1354  bestTypedef = md;
1355  bestTemplSpec = "";
1356  bestResolvedType = md->qualifiedName();
1357  }
1358  }
1359  }
1360  } // if definition accessible
1361  else
1362  {
1363  //printf(" Not accessible!\n");
1364  }
1365  } // if definition is a class or member
1366  //printf(" bestMatch=%p bestResolvedType=%s\n",bestMatch,bestResolvedType.data());
1367 }
1368 
1369 /* Find the fully qualified class name referred to by the input class
1370  * or typedef name against the input scope.
1371  * Loops through scope and each of its parent scopes looking for a
1372  * match against the input name. Can recursively call itself when
1373  * resolving typedefs.
1374  */
1375 static ClassDef *getResolvedClassRec(Definition *scope,
1376  FileDef *fileScope,
1377  const char *n,
1378  MemberDef **pTypeDef,
1379  QCString *pTemplSpec,
1380  QCString *pResolvedType
1381  )
1382 {
1383  //printf("[getResolvedClassRec(%s,%s)\n",scope?scope->name().data():"<global>",n);
1384  QCString name;
1385  QCString explicitScopePart;
1386  QCString strippedTemplateParams;
1387  name=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope
1388  (removeRedundantWhiteSpace(n),TRUE,
1389  &strippedTemplateParams);
1390  ArgumentList actTemplParams;
1391  if (!strippedTemplateParams.isEmpty()) // template part that was stripped
1392  {
1393  stringToArgumentList(strippedTemplateParams,&actTemplParams);
1394  }
1395 
1396  int qualifierIndex = computeQualifiedIndex(name);
1397  //printf("name=%s qualifierIndex=%d\n",name.data(),qualifierIndex);
1398  if (qualifierIndex!=-1) // qualified name
1399  {
1400  // split off the explicit scope part
1401  explicitScopePart=name.left(qualifierIndex);
1402  // todo: improve namespace alias substitution
1403  replaceNamespaceAliases(explicitScopePart,explicitScopePart.length());
1404  name=name.mid(qualifierIndex+2);
1405  }
1406 
1407  if (name.isEmpty())
1408  {
1409  //printf("] empty name\n");
1410  return 0; // empty name
1411  }
1412 
1413  //printf("Looking for symbol %s\n",name.data());
1414  DefinitionIntf *di = Doxygen::symbolMap->find(name);
1415  // the -g (for C# generics) and -p (for ObjC protocols) are now already
1416  // stripped from the key used in the symbolMap, so that is not needed here.
1417  if (di==0)
1418  {
1419  //di = Doxygen::symbolMap->find(name+"-g");
1420  //if (di==0)
1421  //{
1422  di = Doxygen::symbolMap->find(name+"-p");
1423  if (di==0)
1424  {
1425  //printf("no such symbol!\n");
1426  return 0;
1427  }
1428  //}
1429  }
1430  //printf("found symbol!\n");
1431 
1432  bool hasUsingStatements =
1433  (fileScope && ((fileScope->getUsedNamespaces() &&
1434  fileScope->getUsedNamespaces()->count()>0) ||
1435  (fileScope->getUsedClasses() &&
1436  fileScope->getUsedClasses()->count()>0))
1437  );
1438  //printf("hasUsingStatements=%d\n",hasUsingStatements);
1439  // Since it is often the case that the same name is searched in the same
1440  // scope over an over again (especially for the linked source code generation)
1441  // we use a cache to collect previous results. This is possible since the
1442  // result of a lookup is deterministic. As the key we use the concatenated
1443  // scope, the name to search for and the explicit scope prefix. The speedup
1444  // achieved by this simple cache can be enormous.
1445  int scopeNameLen = scope->name().length()+1;
1446  int nameLen = name.length()+1;
1447  int explicitPartLen = explicitScopePart.length();
1448  int fileScopeLen = hasUsingStatements ? 1+fileScope->absFilePath().length() : 0;
1449 
1450  // below is a more efficient coding of
1451  // QCString key=scope->name()+"+"+name+"+"+explicitScopePart;
1452  QCString key(scopeNameLen+nameLen+explicitPartLen+fileScopeLen+1);
1453  char *p=key.rawData();
1454  qstrcpy(p,scope->name()); *(p+scopeNameLen-1)='+';
1455  p+=scopeNameLen;
1456  qstrcpy(p,name); *(p+nameLen-1)='+';
1457  p+=nameLen;
1458  qstrcpy(p,explicitScopePart);
1459  p+=explicitPartLen;
1460 
1461  // if a file scope is given and it contains using statements we should
1462  // also use the file part in the key (as a class name can be in
1463  // two different namespaces and a using statement in a file can select
1464  // one of them).
1465  if (hasUsingStatements)
1466  {
1467  // below is a more efficient coding of
1468  // key+="+"+fileScope->name();
1469  *p++='+';
1470  qstrcpy(p,fileScope->absFilePath());
1471  p+=fileScopeLen-1;
1472  }
1473  *p='\0';
1474 
1475  LookupInfo *pval=Doxygen::lookupCache->find(key);
1476  //printf("Searching for %s result=%p\n",key.data(),pval);
1477  if (pval)
1478  {
1479  //printf("LookupInfo %p %p '%s' %p\n",
1480  // pval->classDef, pval->typeDef, pval->templSpec.data(),
1481  // pval->resolvedType.data());
1482  if (pTemplSpec) *pTemplSpec=pval->templSpec;
1483  if (pTypeDef) *pTypeDef=pval->typeDef;
1484  if (pResolvedType) *pResolvedType=pval->resolvedType;
1485  //printf("] cachedMatch=%s\n",
1486  // pval->classDef?pval->classDef->name().data():"<none>");
1487  //if (pTemplSpec)
1488  // printf("templSpec=%s\n",pTemplSpec->data());
1489  return pval->classDef;
1490  }
1491  else // not found yet; we already add a 0 to avoid the possibility of
1492  // endless recursion.
1493  {
1494  Doxygen::lookupCache->insert(key,new LookupInfo);
1495  }
1496 
1497  ClassDef *bestMatch=0;
1498  MemberDef *bestTypedef=0;
1499  QCString bestTemplSpec;
1500  QCString bestResolvedType;
1501  int minDistance=10000; // init at "infinite"
1502 
1503  if (di->definitionType()==DefinitionIntf::TypeSymbolList) // not a unique name
1504  {
1505  //printf(" name is not unique\n");
1506  DefinitionListIterator dli(*(DefinitionList*)di);
1507  Definition *d;
1508  int count=0;
1509  for (dli.toFirst();(d=dli.current());++dli,++count) // foreach definition
1510  {
1511  getResolvedSymbol(scope,fileScope,d,explicitScopePart,&actTemplParams,
1512  minDistance,bestMatch,bestTypedef,bestTemplSpec,
1513  bestResolvedType);
1514  }
1515  }
1516  else // unique name
1517  {
1518  //printf(" name is unique\n");
1519  Definition *d = (Definition *)di;
1520  getResolvedSymbol(scope,fileScope,d,explicitScopePart,&actTemplParams,
1521  minDistance,bestMatch,bestTypedef,bestTemplSpec,
1522  bestResolvedType);
1523  }
1524 
1525  if (pTypeDef)
1526  {
1527  *pTypeDef = bestTypedef;
1528  }
1529  if (pTemplSpec)
1530  {
1531  *pTemplSpec = bestTemplSpec;
1532  }
1533  if (pResolvedType)
1534  {
1535  *pResolvedType = bestResolvedType;
1536  }
1537  //printf("getResolvedClassRec: bestMatch=%p pval->resolvedType=%s\n",
1538  // bestMatch,bestResolvedType.data());
1539 
1540  pval=Doxygen::lookupCache->find(key);
1541  if (pval)
1542  {
1543  pval->classDef = bestMatch;
1544  pval->typeDef = bestTypedef;
1545  pval->templSpec = bestTemplSpec;
1546  pval->resolvedType = bestResolvedType;
1547  }
1548  else
1549  {
1550  Doxygen::lookupCache->insert(key,new LookupInfo(bestMatch,bestTypedef,bestTemplSpec,bestResolvedType));
1551  }
1552  //printf("] bestMatch=%s distance=%d\n",
1553  // bestMatch?bestMatch->name().data():"<none>",minDistance);
1554  //if (pTemplSpec)
1555  // printf("templSpec=%s\n",pTemplSpec->data());
1556  return bestMatch;
1557 }
1558 
1559 /* Find the fully qualified class name referred to by the input class
1560  * or typedef name against the input scope.
1561  * Loops through scope and each of its parent scopes looking for a
1562  * match against the input name.
1563  */
1564 ClassDef *getResolvedClass(Definition *scope,
1565  FileDef *fileScope,
1566  const char *n,
1567  MemberDef **pTypeDef,
1568  QCString *pTemplSpec,
1569  bool mayBeUnlinkable,
1570  bool mayBeHidden,
1571  QCString *pResolvedType
1572  )
1573 {
1574  static bool optimizeOutputVhdl = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_VHDL);
1575  g_resolvedTypedefs.clear();
1576  if (scope==0 ||
1577  (scope->definitionType()!=Definition::TypeClass &&
1578  scope->definitionType()!=Definition::TypeNamespace
1579  ) ||
1580  (scope->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Java && QCString(n).find("::")!=-1)
1581  )
1582  {
1583  scope=Doxygen::globalScope;
1584  }
1585  //printf("------------ getResolvedClass(scope=%s,file=%s,name=%s,mayUnlinkable=%d)\n",
1586  // scope?scope->name().data():"<global>",
1587  // fileScope?fileScope->name().data():"<none>",
1588  // n,
1589  // mayBeUnlinkable
1590  // );
1591  ClassDef *result;
1592  if (optimizeOutputVhdl)
1593  {
1594  result = getClass(n);
1595  }
1596  else
1597  {
1598  result = getResolvedClassRec(scope,fileScope,n,pTypeDef,pTemplSpec,pResolvedType);
1599  }
1600  if (result==0) // for nested classes imported via tag files, the scope may not
1601  // present, so we check the class name directly as well.
1602  // See also bug701314
1603  {
1604  result = getClass(n);
1605  }
1606  if (!mayBeUnlinkable && result && !result->isLinkable())
1607  {
1608  if (!mayBeHidden || !result->isHidden())
1609  {
1610  //printf("result was %s\n",result?result->name().data():"<none>");
1611  result=0; // don't link to artificial/hidden classes unless explicitly allowed
1612  }
1613  }
1614  //printf("getResolvedClass(%s,%s)=%s\n",scope?scope->name().data():"<global>",
1615  // n,result?result->name().data():"<none>");
1616  return result;
1617 }

1620 //-------------------------------------------------------------------------
1621 //-------------------------------------------------------------------------

1624 static bool findOperator(const QCString &s,int i)
1625 {
1626  int b = s.findRev("operator",i);
1627  if (b==-1) return FALSE; // not found
1628  b+=8;
1629  while (b<i) // check if there are only spaces in between
1630  // the operator and the >
1631  {
1632  if (!isspace((uchar)s.at(b))) return FALSE;
1633  b++;
1634  }
1635  return TRUE;
1636 }
1637 
1638 static bool findOperator2(const QCString &s,int i)
1639 {
1640  int b = s.findRev("operator",i);
1641  if (b==-1) return FALSE; // not found
1642  b+=8;
1643  while (b<i) // check if there are only non-ascii
1644  // characters in front of the operator
1645  {
1646  if (isId((uchar)s.at(b))) return FALSE;
1647  b++;
1648  }
1649  return TRUE;
1650 }
1651 
1652 static const char constScope[] = { 'c', 'o', 'n', 's', 't', ':' };
1653 static const char virtualScope[] = { 'v', 'i', 'r', 't', 'u', 'a', 'l', ':' };
1654 static const char operatorScope[] = { 'o', 'p', 'e', 'r', 'a', 't', 'o', 'r', '?', '?', '?' };
1655 
1656 struct CharAroundSpace
1657 {
1658  CharAroundSpace()
1659  {
1660  charMap['('].before=FALSE;
1661  charMap['='].before=FALSE;
1662  charMap['&'].before=FALSE;
1663  charMap['*'].before=FALSE;
1664  charMap['['].before=FALSE;
1665  charMap['|'].before=FALSE;
1666  charMap['+'].before=FALSE;
1667  charMap[';'].before=FALSE;
1668  charMap[':'].before=FALSE;
1669  charMap['/'].before=FALSE;
1670 
1671  charMap['='].after=FALSE;
1672  charMap[' '].after=FALSE;
1673  charMap[']'].after=FALSE;
1674  charMap['\t'].after=FALSE;
1675  charMap['\n'].after=FALSE;
1676  charMap[')'].after=FALSE;
1677  charMap[','].after=FALSE;
1678  charMap['<'].after=FALSE;
1679  charMap['|'].after=FALSE;
1680  charMap['+'].after=FALSE;
1681  charMap['('].after=FALSE;
1682  charMap['/'].after=FALSE;
1683  }
1684  struct CharElem
1685  {
1686  CharElem() : before(TRUE), after(TRUE) {}
1687  bool before;
1688  bool after;
1689  };
1690 
1691  CharElem charMap[256];
1692 };
1693 
1694 static CharAroundSpace g_charAroundSpace;
1695 
1696 // Note: this function is not reentrant due to the use of static buffer!
1697 QCString removeRedundantWhiteSpace(const QCString &s)
1698 {
1699  static bool cliSupport = Config_getBool(CPP_CLI_SUPPORT);
1700  static bool vhdl = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_VHDL);
1701 
1702  if (s.isEmpty() || vhdl) return s;
1703 
1704  // We use a static character array to
1705  // improve the performance of this function
1706  static char *growBuf = 0;
1707  static int growBufLen = 0;
1708  if (s.length()*3>growBufLen) // For input character we produce at most 3 output characters,
1709  {
1710  growBufLen = s.length()*3;
1711  growBuf = (char *)realloc(growBuf,growBufLen+1); // add 1 for 0-terminator
1712  }
1713  if (growBuf==0) return s; // should not happen, only we run out of memory
1714 
1715  char *src=s.rawData();
1716  char *dst=growBuf;
1717 
1718  uint i=0;
1719  uint l=s.length();
1720  uint csp=0;
1721  uint vsp=0;
1722  uint osp=0;
1723  char c;
1724  char pc=0;
1725  // skip leading whitespace
1726  while (i<l && isspace((uchar)src[i]))
1727  {
1728  i++;
1729  }
1730  for (;i<l;i++)
1731  {
1732  c=src[i];
1733  char nc=i<l-1 ? src[i+1] : ' ';
1734 
1735  // search for "const"
1736  if (csp<6 && c==constScope[csp] && // character matches substring "const"
1737  (csp>0 || // inside search string
1738  i==0 || // if it is the first character
1739  !isId(pc) // the previous may not be a digit
1740  )
1741  )
1742  csp++;
1743  else // reset counter
1744  csp=0;
1745 
1746  // search for "virtual"
1747  if (vsp<8 && c==virtualScope[vsp] && // character matches substring "virtual"
1748  (vsp>0 || // inside search string
1749  i==0 || // if it is the first character
1750  !isId(pc) // the previous may not be a digit
1751  )
1752  )
1753  vsp++;
1754  else // reset counter
1755  vsp=0;
1756 
1757  // search for "operator"
1758  if (osp<11 && (osp>=8 || c==operatorScope[osp]) && // character matches substring "operator" followed by 3 arbitrary characters
1759  (osp>0 || // inside search string
1760  i==0 || // if it is the first character
1761  !isId(pc) // the previous may not be a digit
1762  )
1763  )
1764  osp++;
1765  else // reset counter
1766  osp=0;
1767 
1768  switch(c)
1769  {
1770  case '"': // quoted string
1771  {
1772  *dst++=c;
1773  pc = c;
1774  i++;
1775  for (;i<l;i++) // find end of string
1776  {
1777  c = src[i];
1778  *dst++=c;
1779  if (c=='\\' && i+1<l)
1780  {
1781  pc = c;
1782  i++;
1783  c = src[i];
1784  *dst+=c;
1785  }
1786  else if (c=='"')
1787  {
1788  break;
1789  }
1790  pc = c;
1791  }
1792  }
1793  break;
1794  case '<': // current char is a <
1795  *dst++=c;
1796  if (i<l-1 &&
1797  (isId(nc)) && // next char is an id char
1798  (osp<8) // string in front is not "operator"
1799  )
1800  {
1801  *dst++=' '; // add extra space
1802  }
1803  break;
1804  case '>': // current char is a >
1805  if (i>0 && !isspace((uchar)pc) &&
1806  (isId(pc) || pc=='*' || pc=='&' || pc=='.') && // prev char is an id char or space or *&.
1807  (osp<8 || (osp==8 && pc!='-')) // string in front is not "operator>" or "operator->"
1808  )
1809  {
1810  *dst++=' '; // add extra space in front
1811  }
1812  *dst++=c;
1813  if (i<l-1 && (nc=='-' || nc=='&')) // '>-' -> '> -'
1814  {
1815  *dst++=' '; // add extra space after
1816  }
1817  break;
1818  case ',': // current char is a ,
1819  *dst++=c;
1820  if (i>0 && !isspace((uchar)pc) &&
1821  ((i<l-1 && (isId(nc) || nc=='[')) || // the [ is for attributes (see bug702170)
1822  (i<l-2 && nc=='$' && isId(src[i+2])) || // for PHP: ',$name' -> ', $name'
1823  (i<l-3 && nc=='&' && src[i+2]=='$' && isId(src[i+3])) // for PHP: ',&$name' -> ', &$name'
1824  )
1825  )
1826  {
1827  *dst++=' '; // add extra space after
1828  }
1829  break;
1830  case '^': // CLI 'Type^name' -> 'Type^ name'
1831  case '%': // CLI 'Type%name' -> 'Type% name'
1832  *dst++=c;
1833  if (cliSupport && i<l-1 && (isId(nc) || nc=='-'))
1834  {
1835  *dst++=' '; // add extra space after
1836  }
1837  break;
1838  case ')': // current char is a ) -> ')name' -> ') name'
1839  *dst++=c;
1840  if (i<l-1 && (isId(nc) || nc=='-'))
1841  {
1842  *dst++=' '; // add extra space after
1843  }
1844  break;
1845  case '*':
1846  if (i>0 && pc!=' ' && pc!='\t' && pc!=':' &&
1847  pc!='*' && pc!='&' && pc!='(' && pc!='/' &&
1848  pc!='.' && (osp<9 || (pc=='>' && osp==11)))
1849  // avoid splitting &&, **, .*, operator*, operator->*
1850  {
1851  *dst++=' ';
1852  }
1853  *dst++=c;
1854  break;
1855  case '&':
1856  if (i>0 && isId(pc))
1857  {
1858  *dst++=' ';
1859  }
1860  *dst++=c;
1861  break;
1862  case '@': // '@name' -> ' @name'
1863  case '$': // '$name' -> ' $name'
1864  case '\'': // ''name' -> '' name'
1865  if (i>0 && i<l-1 && pc!='=' && pc!=':' && !isspace(pc) &&
1866  isId(nc) && osp<8) // ")id" -> ") id"
1867  {
1868  *dst++=' ';
1869  }
1870  *dst++=c;
1871  break;
1872  case ':': // current char is a :
1873  if (csp==6) // replace const::A by const ::A
1874  {
1875  *dst++=' ';
1876  csp=0;
1877  }
1878  else if (vsp==8) // replace virtual::A by virtual ::A
1879  {
1880  *dst++=' ';
1881  vsp=0;
1882  }
1883  *dst++=c;
1884  break;
1885  case ' ': // fallthrough
1886  case '\n': // fallthrough
1887  case '\t':
1888  {
1889  if (g_charAroundSpace.charMap[(uchar)pc].before &&
1890  g_charAroundSpace.charMap[(uchar)nc].after &&
1891  !(pc==',' && nc=='.') &&
1892  (osp<8 || (osp>=8 && isId(nc))) // e.g. "operator >>" -> "operator>>", but not "operator int" -> operatorint"
1893  )
1894  { // keep space
1895  *dst++=' ';
1896  }
1897  }
1898  break;
1899  default:
1900  *dst++=c;
1901  if (c=='t' && csp==5 && i<l-1 && // found 't' in 'const'
1902  !(isId(nc) || nc==')' || nc==',' || isspace(nc))
1903  ) // prevent const ::A from being converted to const::A
1904  {
1905  *dst++=' ';
1906  csp=0;
1907  }
1908  else if (c=='l' && vsp==7 && i<l-1 && // found 'l' in 'virtual'
1909  !(isId(nc) || nc==')' || nc==',' || isspace(nc))
1910  ) // prevent virtual ::A from being converted to virtual::A
1911  {
1912  *dst++=' ';
1913  vsp=0;
1914  }
1915  break;
1916  }
1917  pc=c;
1918  }
1919  *dst++='\0';
1920  //printf("removeRedundantWhitespace(%s)->%s\n",s.data(),growBuf);
1921  return growBuf;
1922 }
1923 
1928 int findParameterList(const QCString &name)
1929 {
1930  int pos=-1;
1931  int templateDepth=0;
1932  do
1933  {
1934  if (templateDepth > 0)
1935  {
1936  int nextOpenPos=name.findRev('>', pos);
1937  int nextClosePos=name.findRev('<', pos);
1938  if (nextOpenPos!=-1 && nextOpenPos>nextClosePos)
1939  {
1940  ++templateDepth;
1941  pos=nextOpenPos-1;
1942  }
1943  else if (nextClosePos!=-1)
1944  {
1945  --templateDepth;
1946  pos=nextClosePos-1;
1947  }
1948  else // more >'s than <'s, see bug701295
1949  {
1950  return -1;
1951  }
1952  }
1953  else
1954  {
1955  int lastAnglePos=name.findRev('>', pos);
1956  int bracePos=name.findRev('(', pos);
1957  if (lastAnglePos!=-1 && lastAnglePos>bracePos)
1958  {
1959  ++templateDepth;
1960  pos=lastAnglePos-1;
1961  }
1962  else
1963  {
1964  int bp = bracePos>0 ? name.findRev('(',bracePos-1) : -1;
1965  // bp test is to allow foo(int(&)[10]), but we need to make an exception for operator()
1966  return bp==-1 || (bp>=8 && name.mid(bp-8,10)=="operator()") ? bracePos : bp;
1967  }
1968  }
1969  } while (pos!=-1);
1970  return -1;
1971 }
1972 
1973 bool rightScopeMatch(const QCString &scope, const QCString &name)
1974 {
1975  int sl=scope.length();
1976  int nl=name.length();
1977  return (name==scope || // equal
1978  (scope.right(nl)==name && // substring
1979  sl-nl>1 && scope.at(sl-nl-1)==':' && scope.at(sl-nl-2)==':' // scope
1980  )
1981  );
1982 }
1983 
1984 bool leftScopeMatch(const QCString &scope, const QCString &name)
1985 {
1986  int sl=scope.length();
1987  int nl=name.length();
1988  return (name==scope || // equal
1989  (scope.left(nl)==name && // substring
1990  sl>nl+1 && scope.at(nl)==':' && scope.at(nl+1)==':' // scope
1991  )
1992  );
1993 }

1995 
1996 void linkifyText(const TextGeneratorIntf &out,Definition *scope,
1997  FileDef *fileScope,Definition *self,
1998  const char *text, bool autoBreak,bool external,
1999  bool keepSpaces,int indentLevel)
2000 {
2001  //printf("linkify=`%s'\n",text);
2002  static QRegExp regExp("[a-z_A-Z\\x80-\\xFF][~!a-z_A-Z0-9$\\\\.:\\x80-\\xFF]*");
2003  static QRegExp regExpSplit("(?!:),");
2004  QCString txtStr=text;
2005  int strLen = txtStr.length();
2006  //printf("linkifyText scope=%s fileScope=%s strtxt=%s strlen=%d external=%d\n",
2007  // scope?scope->name().data():"<none>",
2008  // fileScope?fileScope->name().data():"<none>",
2009  // txtStr.data(),strLen,external);
2010  int matchLen;
2011  int index=0;
2012  int newIndex;
2013  int skipIndex=0;
2014  int floatingIndex=0;
2015  if (strLen==0) return;
2016  // read a word from the text string
2017  while ((newIndex=regExp.match(txtStr,index,&matchLen))!=-1 &&
2018  (newIndex==0 || !(txtStr.at(newIndex-1)>='0' && txtStr.at(newIndex-1)<='9')) // avoid matching part of hex numbers
2019  )
2020  {
2021  // add non-word part to the result
2022  floatingIndex+=newIndex-skipIndex+matchLen;
2023  bool insideString=FALSE;
2024  int i;
2025  for (i=index;i<newIndex;i++)
2026  {
2027  if (txtStr.at(i)=='"') insideString=!insideString;
2028  }
2029 
2030  //printf("floatingIndex=%d strlen=%d autoBreak=%d\n",floatingIndex,strLen,autoBreak);
2031  if (strLen>35 && floatingIndex>30 && autoBreak) // try to insert a split point
2032  {
2033  QCString splitText = txtStr.mid(skipIndex,newIndex-skipIndex);
2034  int splitLength = splitText.length();
2035  int offset=1;
2036  i=splitText.find(regExpSplit,0);
2037  if (i==-1) { i=splitText.find('<'); if (i!=-1) offset=0; }
2038  if (i==-1) i=splitText.find('>');
2039  if (i==-1) i=splitText.find(' ');
2040  //printf("splitText=[%s] len=%d i=%d offset=%d\n",splitText.data(),splitLength,i,offset);
2041  if (i!=-1) // add a link-break at i in case of Html output
2042  {
2043  out.writeString(splitText.left(i+offset),keepSpaces);
2044  out.writeBreak(indentLevel==0 ? 0 : indentLevel+1);
2045  out.writeString(splitText.right(splitLength-i-offset),keepSpaces);
2046  floatingIndex=splitLength-i-offset+matchLen;
2047  }
2048  else
2049  {
2050  out.writeString(splitText,keepSpaces);
2051  }
2052  }
2053  else
2054  {
2055  //ol.docify(txtStr.mid(skipIndex,newIndex-skipIndex));
2056  out.writeString(txtStr.mid(skipIndex,newIndex-skipIndex),keepSpaces);
2057  }
2058  // get word from string
2059  QCString word=txtStr.mid(newIndex,matchLen);
2060  QCString matchWord = substitute(substitute(word,"\\","::"),".","::");
2061  //printf("linkifyText word=%s matchWord=%s scope=%s\n",
2062  // word.data(),matchWord.data(),scope?scope->name().data():"<none>");
2063  bool found=FALSE;
2064  if (!insideString)
2065  {
2066  ClassDef *cd=0;
2067  FileDef *fd=0;
2068  MemberDef *md=0;
2069  NamespaceDef *nd=0;
2070  GroupDef *gd=0;
2071  //printf("** Match word '%s'\n",matchWord.data());
2072 
2073  MemberDef *typeDef=0;
2074  cd=getResolvedClass(scope,fileScope,matchWord,&typeDef);
2075  if (typeDef) // First look at typedef then class, see bug 584184.
2076  {
2077  //printf("Found typedef %s\n",typeDef->name().data());
2078  if (external ? typeDef->isLinkable() : typeDef->isLinkableInProject())
2079  {
2080  if (typeDef->getOuterScope()!=self)
2081  {
2082  out.writeLink(typeDef->getReference(),
2083  typeDef->getOutputFileBase(),
2084  typeDef->anchor(),
2085  word);
2086  found=TRUE;
2087  }
2088  }
2089  }
2090  if (!found && (cd || (cd=getClass(matchWord))))
2091  {
2092  //printf("Found class %s\n",cd->name().data());
2093  // add link to the result
2094  if (external ? cd->isLinkable() : cd->isLinkableInProject())
2095  {
2096  if (cd!=self)
2097  {
2098  out.writeLink(cd->getReference(),cd->getOutputFileBase(),cd->anchor(),word);
2099  found=TRUE;
2100  }
2101  }
2102  }
2103  else if ((cd=getClass(matchWord+"-p"))) // search for Obj-C protocols as well
2104  {
2105  // add link to the result
2106  if (external ? cd->isLinkable() : cd->isLinkableInProject())
2107  {
2108  if (cd!=self)
2109  {
2110  out.writeLink(cd->getReference(),cd->getOutputFileBase(),cd->anchor(),word);
2111  found=TRUE;
2112  }
2113  }
2114  }
2115 // else if ((cd=getClass(matchWord+"-g"))) // C# generic as well
2116 // {
2117 // // add link to the result
2118 // if (external ? cd->isLinkable() : cd->isLinkableInProject())
2119 // {
2120 // if (cd!=self)
2121 // {
2122 // out.writeLink(cd->getReference(),cd->getOutputFileBase(),cd->anchor(),word);
2123 // found=TRUE;
2124 // }
2125 // }
2126 // }
2127  else
2128  {
2129  //printf(" -> nothing\n");
2130  }
2131 
2132  int m = matchWord.findRev("::");
2133  QCString scopeName;
2134  if (scope &&
2135  (scope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeClass ||
2136  scope->definitionType()==Definition::TypeNamespace
2137  )
2138  )
2139  {
2140  scopeName=scope->name();
2141  }
2142  else if (m!=-1)
2143  {
2144  scopeName = matchWord.left(m);
2145  matchWord = matchWord.mid(m+2);
2146  }
2147 
2148  //printf("ScopeName=%s\n",scopeName.data());
2149  //if (!found) printf("Trying to link %s in %s\n",word.data(),scopeName.data());
2150  if (!found &&
2151  getDefs(scopeName,matchWord,0,md,cd,fd,nd,gd) &&
2152  //(md->isTypedef() || md->isEnumerate() ||
2153  // md->isReference() || md->isVariable()
2154  //) &&
2155  (external ? md->isLinkable() : md->isLinkableInProject())
2156  )
2157  {
2158  //printf("Found ref scope=%s\n",d?d->name().data():"<global>");
2159  //ol.writeObjectLink(d->getReference(),d->getOutputFileBase(),
2160  // md->anchor(),word);
2161  if (md!=self && (self==0 || md->name()!=self->name()))
2162  // name check is needed for overloaded members, where getDefs just returns one
2163  {
2164  out.writeLink(md->getReference(),md->getOutputFileBase(),
2165  md->anchor(),word);
2166  //printf("found symbol %s\n",matchWord.data());
2167  found=TRUE;
2168  }
2169  }
2170  }
2171 
2172  if (!found) // add word to the result
2173  {
2174  out.writeString(word,keepSpaces);
2175  }
2176  // set next start point in the string
2177  //printf("index=%d/%d\n",index,txtStr.length());
2178  skipIndex=index=newIndex+matchLen;
2179  }
2180  // add last part of the string to the result.
2181  //ol.docify(txtStr.right(txtStr.length()-skipIndex));
2182  out.writeString(txtStr.right(txtStr.length()-skipIndex),keepSpaces);
2183 }

2186 void writeExample(OutputList &ol,ExampleSDict *ed)
2187 {
2188  QCString exampleLine=theTranslator->trWriteList(ed->count());
2189 
2190  //bool latexEnabled = ol.isEnabled(OutputGenerator::Latex);
2191  //bool manEnabled = ol.isEnabled(OutputGenerator::Man);
2192  //bool htmlEnabled = ol.isEnabled(OutputGenerator::Html);
2193  QRegExp marker("@[0-9]+");
2194  int index=0,newIndex,matchLen;
2195  // now replace all markers in inheritLine with links to the classes
2196  while ((newIndex=marker.match(exampleLine,index,&matchLen))!=-1)
2197  {
2198  bool ok;
2199  ol.parseText(exampleLine.mid(index,newIndex-index));
2200  uint entryIndex = exampleLine.mid(newIndex+1,matchLen-1).toUInt(&ok);
2201  Example *e=ed->at(entryIndex);
2202  if (ok && e)
2203  {
2204  ol.pushGeneratorState();
2205  //if (latexEnabled) ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
2206  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
2207  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::RTF);
2208  // link for Html / man
2209  //printf("writeObjectLink(file=%s)\n",e->file.data());
2210  ol.writeObjectLink(0,e->file,e->anchor,e->name);
2211  ol.popGeneratorState();
2212 
2213  ol.pushGeneratorState();
2214  //if (latexEnabled) ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Latex);
2215  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Man);
2216  ol.disable(OutputGenerator::Html);
2217  // link for Latex / pdf with anchor because the sources
2218  // are not hyperlinked (not possible with a verbatim environment).
2219  ol.writeObjectLink(0,e->file,0,e->name);
2220  //if (manEnabled) ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Man);
2221  //if (htmlEnabled) ol.enable(OutputGenerator::Html);
2222  ol.popGeneratorState();
2223  }
2224  index=newIndex+matchLen;
2225  }
2226  ol.parseText(exampleLine.right(exampleLine.length()-index));
2227  ol.writeString(".");
2228 }

2231 QCString argListToString(ArgumentList *al,bool useCanonicalType,bool showDefVals)
2232 {
2233  QCString result;
2234  if (al==0) return result;
2235  ArgumentListIterator ali(*al);
2236  Argument *a=ali.current();
2237  result+="(";
2238  while (a)
2239  {
2240  QCString type1 = useCanonicalType && !a->canType.isEmpty() ?
2241  a->canType : a->type;
2242  QCString type2;
2243  int i=type1.find(")("); // hack to deal with function pointers
2244  if (i!=-1)
2245  {
2246  type2=type1.mid(i);
2247  type1=type1.left(i);
2248  }
2249  if (!a->attrib.isEmpty())
2250  {
2251  result+=a->attrib+" ";
2252  }
2253  if (!a->name.isEmpty() || !a->array.isEmpty())
2254  {
2255  result+= type1+" "+a->name+type2+a->array;
2256  }
2257  else
2258  {
2259  result+= type1+type2;
2260  }
2261  if (!a->defval.isEmpty() && showDefVals)
2262  {
2263  result+="="+a->defval;
2264  }
2265  ++ali;
2266  a = ali.current();
2267  if (a) result+=", ";
2268  }
2269  result+=")";
2270  if (al->constSpecifier) result+=" const";
2271  if (al->volatileSpecifier) result+=" volatile";
2272  if (al->refQualifier==RefQualifierLValue) result+=" &";
2273  else if (al->refQualifier==RefQualifierRValue) result+=" &&";
2274  if (!al->trailingReturnType.isEmpty()) result+=" -> "+al->trailingReturnType;
2275  if (al->pureSpecifier) result+=" =0";
2276  return removeRedundantWhiteSpace(result);
2277 }
2278 
2279 QCString tempArgListToString(ArgumentList *al,SrcLangExt lang)
2280 {
2281  QCString result;
2282  if (al==0) return result;
2283  result="<";
2284  ArgumentListIterator ali(*al);
2285  Argument *a=ali.current();
2286  while (a)
2287  {
2288  if (!a->name.isEmpty()) // add template argument name
2289  {
2290  if (a->type.left(4)=="out") // C# covariance
2291  {
2292  result+="out ";
2293  }
2294  else if (a->type.left(3)=="in") // C# contravariance
2295  {
2296  result+="in ";
2297  }
2298  if (lang==SrcLangExt_Java || lang==SrcLangExt_CSharp)
2299  {
2300  result+=a->type+" ";
2301  }
2302  result+=a->name;
2303  }
2304  else // extract name from type
2305  {
2306  int i=a->type.length()-1;
2307  while (i>=0 && isId(a->type.at(i))) i--;
2308  if (i>0)
2309  {
2310  result+=a->type.right(a->type.length()-i-1);
2311  if (a->type.find("...")!=-1)
2312  {
2313  result+="...";
2314  }
2315  }
2316  else // nothing found -> take whole name
2317  {
2318  result+=a->type;
2319  }
2320  }
2321  if (!a->typeConstraint.isEmpty() && lang==SrcLangExt_Java)
2322  {
2323  result+=" extends "; // TODO: now Java specific, C# has where...
2324  result+=a->typeConstraint;
2325  }
2326  ++ali;
2327  a=ali.current();
2328  if (a) result+=", ";
2329  }
2330  result+=">";
2331  return removeRedundantWhiteSpace(result);
2332 }

2359 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2360 
2366 int filterCRLF(char *buf,int len)
2367 {
2368  int src = 0; // source index
2369  int dest = 0; // destination index
2370  char c; // current character
2371 
2372  while (src<len)
2373  {
2374  c = buf[src++]; // Remember the processed character.
2375  if (c == '\r') // CR to be solved (MAC, DOS)
2376  {
2377  c = '\n'; // each CR to LF
2378  if (src<len && buf[src] == '\n')
2379  ++src; // skip LF just after CR (DOS)
2380  }
2381  else if ( c == '\0' && src<len-1) // filter out internal \0 characters, as it will confuse the parser
2382  {
2383  c = ' '; // turn into a space
2384  }
2385  buf[dest++] = c; // copy the (modified) character to dest
2386  }
2387  return dest; // length of the valid part of the buf
2388 }
2389 
2390 static QCString getFilterFromList(const char *name,const QStrList &filterList,bool &found)
2391 {
2392  found=FALSE;
2393  // compare the file name to the filter pattern list
2394  QStrListIterator sli(filterList);
2395  char* filterStr;
2396  for (sli.toFirst(); (filterStr = sli.current()); ++sli)
2397  {
2398  QCString fs = filterStr;
2399  int i_equals=fs.find('=');
2400  if (i_equals!=-1)
2401  {
2402  QCString filterPattern = fs.left(i_equals);
2403  QRegExp fpat(filterPattern,portable_fileSystemIsCaseSensitive(),TRUE);
2404  if (fpat.match(name)!=-1)
2405  {
2406  // found a match!
2407  QCString filterName = fs.mid(i_equals+1);
2408  if (filterName.find(' ')!=-1)
2409  { // add quotes if the name has spaces
2410  filterName="\""+filterName+"\"";
2411  }
2412  found=TRUE;
2413  return filterName;
2414  }
2415  }
2416  }
2417 
2418  // no match
2419  return "";
2420 }
2421 
2427 QCString getFileFilter(const char* name,bool isSourceCode)
2428 {
2429  // sanity check
2430  if (name==0) return "";
2431 
2432  QStrList& filterSrcList = Config_getList(FILTER_SOURCE_PATTERNS);
2433  QStrList& filterList = Config_getList(FILTER_PATTERNS);
2434 
2435  QCString filterName;
2436  bool found=FALSE;
2437  if (isSourceCode && !filterSrcList.isEmpty())
2438  { // first look for source filter pattern list
2439  filterName = getFilterFromList(name,filterSrcList,found);
2440  }
2441  if (!found && filterName.isEmpty())
2442  { // then look for filter pattern list
2443  filterName = getFilterFromList(name,filterList,found);
2444  }
2445  if (!found)
2446  { // then use the generic input filter
2447  return Config_getString(INPUT_FILTER);
2448  }
2449  else
2450  {
2451  /* remove surrounding double quotes */
2452  if ((filterName.right(1) == "\"") && (filterName.left(1) == "\""))
2453  {
2454  filterName.remove(filterName.length() - 1, 1);
2455  filterName.remove(0, 1);
2456  }
2457  return filterName;
2458  }
2459 }

2462 QCString transcodeCharacterStringToUTF8(const QCString &input)
2463 {
2464  bool error=FALSE;
2465  static QCString inputEncoding = Config_getString(INPUT_ENCODING);
2466  const char *outputEncoding = "UTF-8";
2467  if (inputEncoding.isEmpty() || qstricmp(inputEncoding,outputEncoding)==0) return input;
2468  int inputSize=input.length();
2469  int outputSize=inputSize*4+1;
2470  QCString output(outputSize);
2471  void *cd = portable_iconv_open(outputEncoding,inputEncoding);
2472  if (cd==(void *)(-1))
2473  {
2474  err("unsupported character conversion: '%s'->'%s'\n",
2475  inputEncoding.data(),outputEncoding);
2476  error=TRUE;
2477  }
2478  if (!error)
2479  {
2480  size_t iLeft=inputSize;
2481  size_t oLeft=outputSize;
2482  char *inputPtr = input.rawData();
2483  char *outputPtr = output.rawData();
2484  if (!portable_iconv(cd, &inputPtr, &iLeft, &outputPtr, &oLeft))
2485  {
2486  outputSize-=(int)oLeft;
2487  output.resize(outputSize+1);
2488  output.at(outputSize)='\0';
2489  //printf("iconv: input size=%d output size=%d\n[%s]\n",size,newSize,srcBuf.data());
2490  }
2491  else
2492  {
2493  err("failed to translate characters from %s to %s: check INPUT_ENCODING\ninput=[%s]\n",
2494  inputEncoding.data(),outputEncoding,input.data());
2495  error=TRUE;
2496  }
2497  }
2498  portable_iconv_close(cd);
2499  return error ? input : output;
2500 }
2501 
2506 QCString fileToString(const char *name,bool filter,bool isSourceCode)
2507 {
2508  if (name==0 || name[0]==0) return 0;
2509  QFile f;
2510 
2511  bool fileOpened=FALSE;
2512  if (name[0]=='-' && name[1]==0) // read from stdin
2513  {
2514  fileOpened=f.open(IO_ReadOnly,stdin);
2515  if (fileOpened)
2516  {
2517  const int bSize=4096;
2518  QCString contents(bSize);
2519  int totalSize=0;
2520  int size;
2521  while ((size=f.readBlock(contents.rawData()+totalSize,bSize))==bSize)
2522  {
2523  totalSize+=bSize;
2524  contents.resize(totalSize+bSize);
2525  }
2526  totalSize = filterCRLF(contents.rawData(),totalSize+size)+2;
2527  contents.resize(totalSize);
2528  contents.at(totalSize-2)='\n'; // to help the scanner
2529  contents.at(totalSize-1)='\0';
2530  return contents;
2531  }
2532  }
2533  else // read from file
2534  {
2535  QFileInfo fi(name);
2536  if (!fi.exists() || !fi.isFile())
2537  {
2538  err("file `%s' not found\n",name);
2539  return "";
2540  }
2541  BufStr buf(fi.size());
2542  fileOpened=readInputFile(name,buf,filter,isSourceCode);
2543  if (fileOpened)
2544  {
2545  int s = buf.size();
2546  if (s>1 && buf.at(s-2)!='\n')
2547  {
2548  buf.at(s-1)='\n';
2549  buf.addChar(0);
2550  }
2551  return buf.data();
2552  }
2553  }
2554  if (!fileOpened)
2555  {
2556  err("cannot open file `%s' for reading\n",name);
2557  }
2558  return "";
2559 }

2561 QCString dateToString(bool includeTime)
2562 {
2563  QDateTime current = QDateTime::currentDateTime();
2564  QCString sourceDateEpoch = portable_getenv("SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH");
2565  if (!sourceDateEpoch.isEmpty())
2566  {
2567  bool ok;
2568  uint64 epoch = sourceDateEpoch.toUInt64(&ok);
2569  if (!ok)
2570  {
2571  static bool warnedOnce=FALSE;
2572  if (!warnedOnce)
2573  {
2574  warn_uncond("Environment variable SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH does not contain a valid number; value is '%s'\n",
2575  sourceDateEpoch.data());
2576  warnedOnce=TRUE;
2577  }
2578  }
2579  else if (epoch>UINT_MAX)
2580  {
2581  static bool warnedOnce=FALSE;
2582  if (!warnedOnce)
2583  {
2584  warn_uncond("Environment variable SOURCE_DATA_EPOCH must have a value smaller than or equal to %llu; actual value %llu\n",UINT_MAX,epoch);
2585  warnedOnce=TRUE;
2586  }
2587  }
2588  else // all ok, replace current time with epoch value
2589  {
2590  current.setTimeUtc_t((ulong)epoch); // TODO: add support for 64bit epoch value
2591  }
2592  }
2593  return theTranslator->trDateTime(current.date().year(),
2594  current.date().month(),
2595  current.date().day(),
2596  current.date().dayOfWeek(),
2597  current.time().hour(),
2598  current.time().minute(),
2599  current.time().second(),
2600  includeTime);
2601 }

2610 
2611 //----------------------------------------------------------------------
2612 // recursive function that returns the number of branches in the
2613 // inheritance tree that the base class `bcd' is below the class `cd'
2614 
2615 int minClassDistance(const ClassDef *cd,const ClassDef *bcd,int level)
2616 {
2617  if (bcd->categoryOf()) // use class that is being extended in case of
2618  // an Objective-C category
2619  {
2620  bcd=bcd->categoryOf();
2621  }
2622  if (cd==bcd) return level;
2623  if (level==256)
2624  {
2625  warn_uncond("class %s seem to have a recursive "
2626  "inheritance relation!\n",cd->name().data());
2627  return -1;
2628  }
2629  int m=maxInheritanceDepth;
2630  if (cd->baseClasses())
2631  {
2632  BaseClassListIterator bcli(*cd->baseClasses());
2633  BaseClassDef *bcdi;
2634  for (;(bcdi=bcli.current());++bcli)
2635  {
2636  int mc=minClassDistance(bcdi->classDef,bcd,level+1);
2637  if (mc<m) m=mc;
2638  if (m<0) break;
2639  }
2640  }
2641  return m;
2642 }
2643 
2644 Protection classInheritedProtectionLevel(ClassDef *cd,ClassDef *bcd,Protection prot,int level)
2645 {
2646  if (bcd->categoryOf()) // use class that is being extended in case of
2647  // an Objective-C category
2648  {
2649  bcd=bcd->categoryOf();
2650  }
2651  if (cd==bcd)
2652  {
2653  goto exit;
2654  }
2655  if (level==256)
2656  {
2657  err("Internal inconsistency: found class %s seem to have a recursive "
2658  "inheritance relation! Please send a bug report to dimitri@stack.nl\n",cd->name().data());
2659  }
2660  else if (cd->baseClasses())
2661  {
2662  BaseClassListIterator bcli(*cd->baseClasses());
2663  BaseClassDef *bcdi;
2664  for (;(bcdi=bcli.current()) && prot!=Private;++bcli)
2665  {
2666  Protection baseProt = classInheritedProtectionLevel(bcdi->classDef,bcd,bcdi->prot,level+1);
2667  if (baseProt==Private) prot=Private;
2668  else if (baseProt==Protected) prot=Protected;
2669  }
2670  }
2671 exit:
2672  //printf("classInheritedProtectionLevel(%s,%s)=%d\n",cd->name().data(),bcd->name().data(),prot);
2673  return prot;
2674 }

2681 // printf("(");

2685 // }
