2689 #ifndef NEWMATCH
2690 // strip any template specifiers that follow className in string s
2691 static QCString trimTemplateSpecifiers(
2692  const QCString &namespaceName,
2693  const QCString &className,
2694  const QCString &s
2695  )
2696 {
2697  //printf("trimTemplateSpecifiers(%s,%s,%s)\n",namespaceName.data(),className.data(),s.data());
2698  QCString scopeName=mergeScopes(namespaceName,className);
2699  ClassDef *cd=getClass(scopeName);
2700  if (cd==0) return s; // should not happen, but guard anyway.
2701 
2702  QCString result=s;
2703 
2704  int i=className.length()-1;
2705  if (i>=0 && className.at(i)=='>') // template specialization
2706  {
2707  // replace unspecialized occurrences in s, with their specialized versions.
2708  int count=1;
2709  int cl=i+1;
2710  while (i>=0)
2711  {
2712  char c=className.at(i);
2713  if (c=='>') count++,i--;
2714  else if (c=='<') { count--; if (count==0) break; }
2715  else i--;
2716  }
2717  QCString unspecClassName=className.left(i);
2718  int l=i;
2719  int p=0;
2720  while ((i=result.find(unspecClassName,p))!=-1)
2721  {
2722  if (result.at(i+l)!='<') // unspecialized version
2723  {
2724  result=result.left(i)+className+result.right(result.length()-i-l);
2725  l=cl;
2726  }
2727  p=i+l;
2728  }
2729  }
2730 
2731  //printf("result after specialization: %s\n",result.data());
2732 
2733  QCString qualName=cd->qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters();
2734  //printf("QualifiedName = %s\n",qualName.data());
2735  // We strip the template arguments following className (if any)
2736  if (!qualName.isEmpty()) // there is a class name
2737  {
2738  int is,ps=0;
2739  int p=0,l,i;
2740 
2741  while ((is=getScopeFragment(qualName,ps,&l))!=-1)
2742  {
2743  QCString qualNamePart = qualName.right(qualName.length()-is);
2744  //printf("qualNamePart=%s\n",qualNamePart.data());
2745  while ((i=result.find(qualNamePart,p))!=-1)
2746  {
2747  int ql=qualNamePart.length();
2748  result=result.left(i)+cd->name()+result.right(result.length()-i-ql);
2749  p=i+cd->name().length();
2750  }
2751  ps=is+l;
2752  }
2753  }
2754  //printf("result=%s\n",result.data());
2755 
2756  return result.stripWhiteSpace();
2757 }
2758 
2766 static int findScopePattern(const QCString &pattern,const QCString &s,
2767  int p,int *len)
2768 {
2769  int sl=s.length();
2770  int pl=pattern.length();
2771  int sp=0;
2772  *len=0;
2773  while (p<sl)
2774  {
2775  sp=p; // start of match
2776  int pp=0; // pattern position
2777  while (p<sl && pp<pl)
2778  {
2779  if (s.at(p)=='<') // skip template arguments while matching
2780  {
2781  int bc=1;
2782  //printf("skipping pos=%d c=%c\n",p,s.at(p));
2783  p++;
2784  while (p<sl)
2785  {
2786  if (s.at(p)=='<') bc++;
2787  else if (s.at(p)=='>')
2788  {
2789  bc--;
2790  if (bc==0)
2791  {
2792  p++;
2793  break;
2794  }
2795  }
2796  //printf("skipping pos=%d c=%c\n",p,s.at(p));
2797  p++;
2798  }
2799  }
2800  else if (s.at(p)==pattern.at(pp))
2801  {
2802  //printf("match at position p=%d pp=%d c=%c\n",p,pp,s.at(p));
2803  p++;
2804  pp++;
2805  }
2806  else // no match
2807  {
2808  //printf("restarting at %d c=%c pat=%s\n",p,s.at(p),pattern.data());
2809  p=sp+1;
2810  break;
2811  }
2812  }
2813  if (pp==pl) // whole pattern matches
2814  {
2815  *len=p-sp;
2816  return sp;
2817  }
2818  }
2819  return -1;
2820 }
2821 
2822 static QCString trimScope(const QCString &name,const QCString &s)
2823 {
2824  int scopeOffset=name.length();
2825  QCString result=s;
2826  do // for each scope
2827  {
2828  QCString tmp;
2829  QCString scope=name.left(scopeOffset)+"::";
2830  //printf("Trying with scope=`%s'\n",scope.data());
2831 
2832  int i,p=0,l;
2833  while ((i=findScopePattern(scope,result,p,&l))!=-1) // for each occurrence
2834  {
2835  tmp+=result.mid(p,i-p); // add part before pattern
2836  p=i+l;
2837  }
2838  tmp+=result.right(result.length()-p); // add trailing part
2839 
2840  scopeOffset=name.findRev("::",scopeOffset-1);
2841  result = tmp;
2842  } while (scopeOffset>0);
2843  //printf("trimScope(name=%s,scope=%s)=%s\n",name.data(),s.data(),result.data());
2844  return result;
2845 }
2846 #endif

2859  {

2861  s.length()-spos-cd->name().length()-2
2862  );

2864  //printf("base class `%s'\n",cd->name().data());
2865  if (cd->baseClasses())
2866  trimBaseClassScope(cd->baseClasses(),s,level+1);
2867  }

2947 static void stripIrrelevantString(QCString &target,const QCString &str)
2948 {
2949  if (target==str) { target.resize(0); return; }
2950  int i,p=0;
2951  int l=str.length();
2952  bool changed=FALSE;
2953  while ((i=target.find(str,p))!=-1)
2954  {
2955  bool isMatch = (i==0 || !isId(target.at(i-1))) && // not a character before str
2956  (i+l==(int)target.length() || !isId(target.at(i+l))); // not a character after str
2957  if (isMatch)
2958  {
2959  int i1=target.find('*',i+l);
2960  int i2=target.find('&',i+l);
2961  if (i1==-1 && i2==-1)
2962  {
2963  // strip str from target at index i
2964  target=target.left(i)+target.right(target.length()-i-l);
2965  changed=TRUE;
2966  i-=l;
2967  }
2968  else if ((i1!=-1 && i<i1) || (i2!=-1 && i<i2)) // str before * or &
2969  {
2970  // move str to front
2971  target=str+" "+target.left(i)+target.right(target.length()-i-l);
2972  changed=TRUE;
2973  i++;
2974  }
2975  }
2976  p = i+l;
2977  }
2978  if (changed) target=target.stripWhiteSpace();
2979 }

3003  stripIrrelevantString(s,"final");
3004  //printf("%s\n",s.data());
3005 }

3015 static bool matchArgument(const Argument *srcA,const Argument *dstA,
3016  const QCString &className,
3017  const QCString &namespaceName,
3018  NamespaceSDict *usingNamespaces,
3019  SDict<Definition> *usingClasses)
3020 {

3023  // dstA->type.data(),dstA->name.data(),

3035  QCString dstAName=dstA->name.stripWhiteSpace();

3037  dstAType.stripPrefix("class ");
3038

3040  // from a syntactic point of view they would be two names of the same
3041  // type "const". This is not fool prove of course, but should at least
3042  // catch the most common cases.
3043  if ((srcAType=="const" || srcAType=="volatile") && !srcAName.isEmpty())
3044  {
3045  srcAType+=" ";
3046  srcAType+=srcAName;
3047  }
3048  if ((dstAType=="const" || dstAType=="volatile") && !dstAName.isEmpty())
3049  {
3050  dstAType+=" ";
3051  dstAType+=dstAName;
3052  }
3053  if (srcAName=="const" || srcAName=="volatile")
3054  {
3055  srcAType+=srcAName;
3056  srcAName.resize(0);
3057  }
3058  else if (dstA->name=="const" || dstA->name=="volatile")
3059  {
3060  dstAType+=dstA->name;
3061  dstAName.resize(0);
3062  }

3071  }

3073  {
3074  dstAType = dstAType.right(dstAType.length()-9);
3075  }

3078  dstAType = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(dstAType);
3079 
3080  //srcAType=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(srcAType,FALSE);
3081  //dstAType=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(dstAType,FALSE);
3082 
3083  //printf("srcA=`%s|%s' dstA=`%s|%s'\n",srcAType.data(),srcAName.data(),
3084  // dstAType.data(),dstAName.data());
3085 
3086  if (srcA->array!=dstA->array) // nomatch for char[] against char
3087  {
3088  NOMATCH
3089  return FALSE;
3090  }
3091  if (srcAType!=dstAType) // check if the argument only differs on name
3092  {
3093 
3094  // remove a namespace scope that is only in one type
3095  // (assuming a using statement was used)
3096  //printf("Trimming %s<->%s: %s\n",srcAType.data(),dstAType.data(),namespaceName.data());
3097  //trimNamespaceScope(srcAType,dstAType,namespaceName);

3099 
3100  //QCString srcScope;
3101  //QCString dstScope;

3104  if (!className.isEmpty())
3105  {
3106  srcAType=trimScope(className,srcAType);
3107  dstAType=trimScope(className,dstAType);
3108  //printf("trimScope: `%s' <=> `%s'\n",srcAType.data(),dstAType.data());
3109  ClassDef *cd;
3110  if (!namespaceName.isEmpty())
3111  cd=getClass(namespaceName+"::"+className);
3112  else
3113  cd=getClass(className);
3114  if (cd && cd->baseClasses())
3115  {
3116  trimBaseClassScope(cd->baseClasses(),srcAType);
3117  trimBaseClassScope(cd->baseClasses(),dstAType);
3118  }
3119  //printf("trimBaseClassScope: `%s' <=> `%s'\n",srcAType.data(),dstAType.data());
3120  }
3121  if (!namespaceName.isEmpty())
3122  {
3123  srcAType=trimScope(namespaceName,srcAType);
3124  dstAType=trimScope(namespaceName,dstAType);
3125  }
3126  //printf("#usingNamespace=%d\n",usingNamespaces->count());
3127  if (usingNamespaces && usingNamespaces->count()>0)
3128  {
3129  NamespaceSDict::Iterator nli(*usingNamespaces);
3130  NamespaceDef *nd;
3131  for (;(nd=nli.current());++nli)
3132  {
3133  srcAType=trimScope(nd->name(),srcAType);
3134  dstAType=trimScope(nd->name(),dstAType);
3135  }
3136  }
3137  //printf("#usingClasses=%d\n",usingClasses->count());
3138  if (usingClasses && usingClasses->count()>0)
3139  {
3140  SDict<Definition>::Iterator cli(*usingClasses);
3141  Definition *cd;
3142  for (;(cd=cli.current());++cli)
3143  {
3144  srcAType=trimScope(cd->name(),srcAType);
3145  dstAType=trimScope(cd->name(),dstAType);
3146  }
3147  }
3148 
3149  //printf("2. srcA=%s|%s dstA=%s|%s\n",srcAType.data(),srcAName.data(),
3150  // dstAType.data(),dstAName.data());
3151 
3152  if (!srcAName.isEmpty() && !dstA->type.isEmpty() &&
3153  (srcAType+" "+srcAName)==dstAType)
3154  {
3155  MATCH
3156  return TRUE;
3157  }
3158  else if (!dstAName.isEmpty() && !srcA->type.isEmpty() &&
3159  (dstAType+" "+dstAName)==srcAType)
3160  {
3161  MATCH
3162  return TRUE;
3163  }
3164 
3165 
3166  uint srcPos=0,dstPos=0;
3167  bool equal=TRUE;
3168  while (srcPos<srcAType.length() && dstPos<dstAType.length() && equal)
3169  {
3170  equal=srcAType.at(srcPos)==dstAType.at(dstPos);
3171  if (equal) srcPos++,dstPos++;
3172  }
3173  uint srcATypeLen=srcAType.length();
3174  uint dstATypeLen=dstAType.length();
3175  if (srcPos<srcATypeLen && dstPos<dstATypeLen)
3176  {
3177  // if nothing matches or the match ends in the middle or at the
3178  // end of a string then there is no match
3179  if (srcPos==0 || dstPos==0)
3180  {
3181  NOMATCH
3182  return FALSE;
3183  }
3184  if (isId(srcAType.at(srcPos)) && isId(dstAType.at(dstPos)))
3185  {
3186  //printf("partial match srcPos=%d dstPos=%d!\n",srcPos,dstPos);
3187  // check if a name if already found -> if no then there is no match
3188  if (!srcAName.isEmpty() || !dstAName.isEmpty())
3189  {
3190  NOMATCH
3191  return FALSE;
3192  }
3193  // types only
3194  while (srcPos<srcATypeLen && isId(srcAType.at(srcPos))) srcPos++;
3195  while (dstPos<dstATypeLen && isId(dstAType.at(dstPos))) dstPos++;
3196  if (srcPos<srcATypeLen ||
3197  dstPos<dstATypeLen ||
3198  (srcPos==srcATypeLen && dstPos==dstATypeLen)
3199  )
3200  {
3201  NOMATCH
3202  return FALSE;
3203  }
3204  }
3205  else
3206  {
3207  // otherwise we assume that a name starts at the current position.
3208  while (srcPos<srcATypeLen && isId(srcAType.at(srcPos))) srcPos++;
3209  while (dstPos<dstATypeLen && isId(dstAType.at(dstPos))) dstPos++;
3210 
3211  // if nothing more follows for both types then we assume we have
3212  // found a match. Note that now `signed int' and `signed' match, but
3213  // seeing that int is not a name can only be done by looking at the
3214  // semantics.
3215 
3216  if (srcPos!=srcATypeLen || dstPos!=dstATypeLen)
3217  {
3218  NOMATCH
3219  return FALSE;
3220  }
3221  }
3222  }
3223  else if (dstPos<dstAType.length())
3224  {
3225  if (!isspace((uchar)dstAType.at(dstPos))) // maybe the names differ
3226  {
3227  if (!dstAName.isEmpty()) // dst has its name separated from its type
3228  {
3229  NOMATCH
3230  return FALSE;
3231  }
3232  while (dstPos<dstAType.length() && isId(dstAType.at(dstPos))) dstPos++;
3233  if (dstPos!=dstAType.length())
3234  {
3235  NOMATCH
3236  return FALSE; // more than a difference in name -> no match
3237  }
3238  }
3239  else // maybe dst has a name while src has not
3240  {
3241  dstPos++;
3242  while (dstPos<dstAType.length() && isId(dstAType.at(dstPos))) dstPos++;
3243  if (dstPos!=dstAType.length() || !srcAName.isEmpty())
3244  {
3245  NOMATCH
3246  return FALSE; // nope not a name -> no match
3247  }
3248  }
3249  }
3250  else if (srcPos<srcAType.length())
3251  {
3252  if (!isspace((uchar)srcAType.at(srcPos))) // maybe the names differ
3253  {
3254  if (!srcAName.isEmpty()) // src has its name separated from its type
3255  {
3256  NOMATCH
3257  return FALSE;
3258  }
3259  while (srcPos<srcAType.length() && isId(srcAType.at(srcPos))) srcPos++;
3260  if (srcPos!=srcAType.length())
3261  {
3262  NOMATCH
3263  return FALSE; // more than a difference in name -> no match
3264  }
3265  }
3266  else // maybe src has a name while dst has not
3267  {
3268  srcPos++;
3269  while (srcPos<srcAType.length() && isId(srcAType.at(srcPos))) srcPos++;
3270  if (srcPos!=srcAType.length() || !dstAName.isEmpty())
3271  {
3272  NOMATCH
3273  return FALSE; // nope not a name -> no match
3274  }
3275  }
3276  }
3277  }
3278  MATCH
3279  return TRUE;
3280 }

3347 
3348  if (srcAl->count() != dstAl->count())
3349  {
3350  NOMATCH
3351  return FALSE; // different number of arguments -> no match
3352  }
3353 
3354  if (checkCV)
3355  {
3356  if (srcAl->constSpecifier != dstAl->constSpecifier)
3357  {
3358  NOMATCH
3359  return FALSE; // one member is const, the other not -> no match
3360  }
3361  if (srcAl->volatileSpecifier != dstAl->volatileSpecifier)
3362  {
3363  NOMATCH
3364  return FALSE; // one member is volatile, the other not -> no match
3365  }
3366  }
3367 
3368  if (srcAl->refQualifier != dstAl->refQualifier)
3369  {
3370  NOMATCH
3371  return FALSE; // one member is has a different ref-qualifier than the other
3372  }
3373 
3374  // so far the argument list could match, so we need to compare the types of
3375  // all arguments.
3376  ArgumentListIterator srcAli(*srcAl),dstAli(*dstAl);
3377  Argument *srcA,*dstA;
3378  for (;(srcA=srcAli.current()) && (dstA=dstAli.current());++srcAli,++dstAli)
3379  {
3380  if (!matchArgument(srcA,dstA,className,namespaceName,
3381  usingNamespaces,usingClasses))
3382  {
3383  NOMATCH
3384  return FALSE;
3385  }
3386  }
3387  MATCH
3388  return TRUE; // all arguments match
3389 }
3390 
3391 #endif

3416 static QCString stripDeclKeywords(const QCString &s)
3417 {
3418  int i=s.find(" class ");
3419  if (i!=-1) return s.left(i)+s.mid(i+6);
3420  i=s.find(" typename ");
3421  if (i!=-1) return s.left(i)+s.mid(i+9);
3422  i=s.find(" union ");
3423  if (i!=-1) return s.left(i)+s.mid(i+6);
3424  i=s.find(" struct ");
3425  if (i!=-1) return s.left(i)+s.mid(i+7);
3426  return s;
3427 }

3429 // forward decl for circular dependencies
3430 static QCString extractCanonicalType(Definition *d,FileDef *fs,QCString type);
3431 
3432 QCString getCanonicalTemplateSpec(Definition *d,FileDef *fs,const QCString& spec)
3433 {
3434 
3435  QCString templSpec = spec.stripWhiteSpace();
3436  // this part had been commented out before... but it is needed to match for instance
3437  // std::list<std::string> against list<string> so it is now back again!
3438  if (!templSpec.isEmpty() && templSpec.at(0) == '<')
3439  {
3440  templSpec = "< " + extractCanonicalType(d,fs,templSpec.right(templSpec.length()-1).stripWhiteSpace());
3441  }
3442  QCString resolvedType = resolveTypeDef(d,templSpec);
3443  if (!resolvedType.isEmpty()) // not known as a typedef either
3444  {
3445  templSpec = resolvedType;
3446  }
3447  //printf("getCanonicalTemplateSpec(%s)=%s\n",spec.data(),templSpec.data());
3448  return templSpec;
3449 }

3451 
3452 static QCString getCanonicalTypeForIdentifier(
3453  Definition *d,FileDef *fs,const QCString &word,
3454  QCString *tSpec,int count=0)
3455 {
3456  if (count>10) return word; // oops recursion
3457 
3458  QCString symName,result,templSpec,tmpName;
3459  //DefinitionList *defList=0;
3460  if (tSpec && !tSpec->isEmpty())
3461  templSpec = stripDeclKeywords(getCanonicalTemplateSpec(d,fs,*tSpec));
3462 
3463  if (word.findRev("::")!=-1 && !(tmpName=stripScope(word)).isEmpty())
3464  {
3465  symName=tmpName; // name without scope
3466  }
3467  else
3468  {
3469  symName=word;
3470  }
3471  //printf("getCanonicalTypeForIdentifier(%s,[%s->%s]) start\n",
3472  // word.data(),tSpec?tSpec->data():"<none>",templSpec.data());
3473 
3474  ClassDef *cd = 0;
3475  MemberDef *mType = 0;
3476  QCString ts;
3477  QCString resolvedType;
3478 
3479  // lookup class / class template instance
3480  cd = getResolvedClass(d,fs,word+templSpec,&mType,&ts,TRUE,TRUE,&resolvedType);
3481  bool isTemplInst = cd && !templSpec.isEmpty();
3482  if (!cd && !templSpec.isEmpty())
3483  {
3484  // class template specialization not known, look up class template
3485  cd = getResolvedClass(d,fs,word,&mType,&ts,TRUE,TRUE,&resolvedType);
3486  }
3487  if (cd && cd->isUsedOnly()) cd=0; // ignore types introduced by usage relations
3488 
3489  //printf("cd=%p mtype=%p\n",cd,mType);
3490  //printf(" getCanonicalTypeForIdentifer: symbol=%s word=%s cd=%s d=%s fs=%s cd->isTemplate=%d\n",
3491  // symName.data(),
3492  // word.data(),
3493  // cd?cd->name().data():"<none>",
3494  // d?d->name().data():"<none>",
3495  // fs?fs->name().data():"<none>",
3496  // cd?cd->isTemplate():-1
3497  // );
3498 
3499  //printf(" >>>> word '%s' => '%s' templSpec=%s ts=%s tSpec=%s isTemplate=%d resolvedType=%s\n",
3500  // (word+templSpec).data(),
3501  // cd?cd->qualifiedName().data():"<none>",
3502  // templSpec.data(),ts.data(),
3503  // tSpec?tSpec->data():"<null>",
3504  // cd?cd->isTemplate():FALSE,
3505  // resolvedType.data());
3506 
3507  //printf(" mtype=%s\n",mType?mType->name().data():"<none>");
3508 
3509  if (cd) // resolves to a known class type
3510  {
3511  if (cd==d && tSpec) *tSpec="";
3512 
3513  if (mType && mType->isTypedef()) // but via a typedef
3514  {
3515  result = resolvedType+ts; // the +ts was added for bug 685125
3516  }
3517  else
3518  {
3519  if (isTemplInst)
3520  {
3521  // spec is already part of class type
3522  templSpec="";
3523  if (tSpec) *tSpec="";
3524  }
3525  else if (!ts.isEmpty() && templSpec.isEmpty())
3526  {
3527  // use formal template args for spec
3528  templSpec = stripDeclKeywords(getCanonicalTemplateSpec(d,fs,ts));
3529  }
3530 
3531  result = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(cd->qualifiedName() + templSpec);
3532 
3533  if (cd->isTemplate() && tSpec) //
3534  {
3535  if (!templSpec.isEmpty()) // specific instance
3536  {
3537  result=cd->name()+templSpec;
3538  }
3539  else // use template type
3540  {
3541  result=cd->qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters();
3542  }
3543  // template class, so remove the template part (it is part of the class name)
3544  *tSpec="";
3545  }
3546  else if (ts.isEmpty() && !templSpec.isEmpty() && cd && !cd->isTemplate() && tSpec)
3547  {
3548  // obscure case, where a class is used as a template, but doxygen think it is
3549  // not (could happen when loading the class from a tag file).
3550  *tSpec="";
3551  }
3552  }
3553  }
3554  else if (mType && mType->isEnumerate()) // an enum
3555  {
3556  result = mType->qualifiedName();
3557  }
3558  else if (mType && mType->isTypedef()) // a typedef
3559  {
3560  //result = mType->qualifiedName(); // changed after 1.7.2
3561  //result = mType->typeString();
3562  //printf("word=%s typeString=%s\n",word.data(),mType->typeString());
3563  if (word!=mType->typeString())
3564  {
3565  result = getCanonicalTypeForIdentifier(d,fs,mType->typeString(),tSpec,count+1);
3566  }
3567  else
3568  {
3569  result = mType->typeString();
3570  }
3571  }
3572  else // fallback
3573  {
3574  resolvedType = resolveTypeDef(d,word);
3575  //printf("typedef [%s]->[%s]\n",word.data(),resolvedType.data());
3576  if (resolvedType.isEmpty()) // not known as a typedef either
3577  {
3578  result = word;
3579  }
3580  else
3581  {
3582  result = resolvedType;
3583  }
3584  }
3585  //printf("getCanonicalTypeForIdentifier [%s]->[%s]\n",word.data(),result.data());
3586  return result;
3587 }
3588 
3589 static QCString extractCanonicalType(Definition *d,FileDef *fs,QCString type)
3590 {
3591  type = type.stripWhiteSpace();
3592 
3593  // strip const and volatile keywords that are not relevant for the type
3594  stripIrrelevantConstVolatile(type);
3595 
3596  // strip leading keywords
3597  type.stripPrefix("class ");
3598  type.stripPrefix("struct ");
3599  type.stripPrefix("union ");
3600  type.stripPrefix("enum ");
3601  type.stripPrefix("typename ");
3602 
3603  type = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(type);
3604  //printf("extractCanonicalType(type=%s) start: def=%s file=%s\n",type.data(),
3605  // d ? d->name().data() : "<null>",fs ? fs->name().data() : "<null>");
3606 
3607  //static QRegExp id("[a-z_A-Z\\x80-\\xFF][:a-z_A-Z0-9\\x80-\\xFF]*");
3608 
3609  QCString canType;
3610  QCString templSpec,word;
3611  int i,p=0,pp=0;
3612  while ((i=extractClassNameFromType(type,p,word,templSpec))!=-1)
3613  // foreach identifier in the type
3614  {
3615  //printf(" i=%d p=%d\n",i,p);
3616  if (i>pp) canType += type.mid(pp,i-pp);
3617 
3618 
3619  QCString ct = getCanonicalTypeForIdentifier(d,fs,word,&templSpec);
3620 
3621  // in case the ct is empty it means that "word" represents scope "d"
3622  // and this does not need to be added to the canonical
3623  // type (it is redundant), so/ we skip it. This solves problem 589616.
3624  if (ct.isEmpty() && type.mid(p,2)=="::")
3625  {
3626  p+=2;
3627  }
3628  else
3629  {
3630  canType += ct;
3631  }
3632  //printf(" word=%s templSpec=%s canType=%s ct=%s\n",
3633  // word.data(),templSpec.data(),canType.data(),ct.data());
3634  if (!templSpec.isEmpty()) // if we didn't use up the templSpec already
3635  // (i.e. type is not a template specialization)
3636  // then resolve any identifiers inside.
3637  {
3638  static QRegExp re("[a-z_A-Z\\x80-\\xFF][a-z_A-Z0-9\\x80-\\xFF]*");
3639  int tp=0,tl,ti;
3640  // for each identifier template specifier
3641  //printf("adding resolved %s to %s\n",templSpec.data(),canType.data());
3642  while ((ti=re.match(templSpec,tp,&tl))!=-1)
3643  {
3644  canType += templSpec.mid(tp,ti-tp);
3645  canType += getCanonicalTypeForIdentifier(d,fs,templSpec.mid(ti,tl),0);
3646  tp=ti+tl;
3647  }
3648  canType+=templSpec.right(templSpec.length()-tp);
3649  }
3650 
3651  pp=p;
3652  }
3653  canType += type.right(type.length()-pp);
3654  //printf("extractCanonicalType = '%s'->'%s'\n",type.data(),canType.data());
3655 
3656  return removeRedundantWhiteSpace(canType);
3657 }
3658 
3659 static QCString extractCanonicalArgType(Definition *d,FileDef *fs,const Argument *arg)
3660 {
3661  QCString type = arg->type.stripWhiteSpace();
3662  QCString name = arg->name;
3663  //printf("----- extractCanonicalArgType(type=%s,name=%s)\n",type.data(),name.data());
3664  if ((type=="const" || type=="volatile") && !name.isEmpty())
3665  { // name is part of type => correct
3666  type+=" ";
3667  type+=name;
3668  }
3669  if (name=="const" || name=="volatile")
3670  { // name is part of type => correct
3671  if (!type.isEmpty()) type+=" ";
3672  type+=name;
3673  }
3674  if (!arg->array.isEmpty())
3675  {
3676  type+=arg->array;
3677  }
3678 
3679  return extractCanonicalType(d,fs,type);
3680 }
3681 
3682 static bool matchArgument2(
3683  Definition *srcScope,FileDef *srcFileScope,Argument *srcA,
3684  Definition *dstScope,FileDef *dstFileScope,Argument *dstA
3685  )
3686 {
3687  //printf(">> match argument: %s::`%s|%s' (%s) <-> %s::`%s|%s' (%s)\n",
3688  // srcScope ? srcScope->name().data() : "",
3689  // srcA->type.data(),srcA->name.data(),srcA->canType.data(),
3690  // dstScope ? dstScope->name().data() : "",
3691  // dstA->type.data(),dstA->name.data(),dstA->canType.data());
3692 
3693  //if (srcA->array!=dstA->array) // nomatch for char[] against char
3694  //{
3695  // NOMATCH
3696  // return FALSE;
3697  //}
3698  QCString sSrcName = " "+srcA->name;
3699  QCString sDstName = " "+dstA->name;
3700  QCString srcType = srcA->type;
3701  QCString dstType = dstA->type;
3702  stripIrrelevantConstVolatile(srcType);
3703  stripIrrelevantConstVolatile(dstType);
3704  //printf("'%s'<->'%s'\n",sSrcName.data(),dstType.right(sSrcName.length()).data());
3705  //printf("'%s'<->'%s'\n",sDstName.data(),srcType.right(sDstName.length()).data());
3706  if (sSrcName==dstType.right(sSrcName.length()))
3707  { // case "unsigned int" <-> "unsigned int i"
3708  srcA->type+=sSrcName;
3709  srcA->name="";
3710  srcA->canType=""; // invalidate cached type value
3711  }
3712  else if (sDstName==srcType.right(sDstName.length()))
3713  { // case "unsigned int i" <-> "unsigned int"
3714  dstA->type+=sDstName;
3715  dstA->name="";
3716  dstA->canType=""; // invalidate cached type value
3717  }
3718 
3719  if (srcA->canType.isEmpty())
3720  {
3721  srcA->canType = extractCanonicalArgType(srcScope,srcFileScope,srcA);
3722  }
3723  if (dstA->canType.isEmpty())
3724  {
3725  dstA->canType = extractCanonicalArgType(dstScope,dstFileScope,dstA);
3726  }
3727 
3728  if (srcA->canType==dstA->canType)
3729  {
3730  MATCH
3731  return TRUE;
3732  }
3733  else
3734  {
3735  //printf(" Canonical types do not match [%s]<->[%s]\n",
3736  // srcA->canType.data(),dstA->canType.data());
3737  NOMATCH
3738  return FALSE;
3739  }
3740 }
3741 
3742 
3743 // new algorithm for argument matching
3744 bool matchArguments2(Definition *srcScope,FileDef *srcFileScope,ArgumentList *srcAl,
3745  Definition *dstScope,FileDef *dstFileScope,ArgumentList *dstAl,
3746  bool checkCV
3747  )
3748 {
3749  //printf("*** matchArguments2\n");
3750  ASSERT(srcScope!=0 && dstScope!=0);
3751 
3752  if (srcAl==0 || dstAl==0)
3753  {
3754  bool match = srcAl==dstAl; // at least one of the members is not a function
3755  if (match)
3756  {
3757  MATCH
3758  return TRUE;
3759  }
3760  else
3761  {
3762  NOMATCH
3763  return FALSE;
3764  }
3765  }
3766 
3767  // handle special case with void argument
3768  if ( srcAl->count()==0 && dstAl->count()==1 &&
3769  dstAl->getFirst()->type=="void" )
3770  { // special case for finding match between func() and func(void)
3771  Argument *a=new Argument;
3772  a->type = "void";
3773  srcAl->append(a);
3774  MATCH
3775  return TRUE;
3776  }
3777  if ( dstAl->count()==0 && srcAl->count()==1 &&
3778  srcAl->getFirst()->type=="void" )
3779  { // special case for finding match between func(void) and func()
3780  Argument *a=new Argument;
3781  a->type = "void";
3782  dstAl->append(a);
3783  MATCH
3784  return TRUE;
3785  }
3786 
3787  if (srcAl->count() != dstAl->count())
3788  {
3789  NOMATCH
3790  return FALSE; // different number of arguments -> no match
3791  }
3792 
3793  if (checkCV)
3794  {
3795  if (srcAl->constSpecifier != dstAl->constSpecifier)
3796  {
3797  NOMATCH
3798  return FALSE; // one member is const, the other not -> no match
3799  }
3800  if (srcAl->volatileSpecifier != dstAl->volatileSpecifier)
3801  {
3802  NOMATCH
3803  return FALSE; // one member is volatile, the other not -> no match
3804  }
3805  }
3806 
3807  if (srcAl->refQualifier != dstAl->refQualifier)
3808  {
3809  NOMATCH
3810  return FALSE; // one member is has a different ref-qualifier than the other
3811  }
3812 
3813  // so far the argument list could match, so we need to compare the types of
3814  // all arguments.
3815  ArgumentListIterator srcAli(*srcAl),dstAli(*dstAl);
3816  Argument *srcA,*dstA;
3817  for (;(srcA=srcAli.current()) && (dstA=dstAli.current());++srcAli,++dstAli)
3818  {
3819  if (!matchArgument2(srcScope,srcFileScope,srcA,
3820  dstScope,dstFileScope,dstA)
3821  )
3822  {
3823  NOMATCH
3824  return FALSE;
3825  }
3826  }
3827  MATCH
3828  return TRUE; // all arguments match
3829 }

3831 
3832 
3833 // merges the initializer of two argument lists
3834 // pre: the types of the arguments in the list should match.
3835 void mergeArguments(ArgumentList *srcAl,ArgumentList *dstAl,bool forceNameOverwrite)
3836 {
3837  //printf("mergeArguments `%s', `%s'\n",
3838  // argListToString(srcAl).data(),argListToString(dstAl).data());
3839 
3840  if (srcAl==0 || dstAl==0 || srcAl->count()!=dstAl->count())
3841  {
3842  return; // invalid argument lists -> do not merge
3843  }
3844 
3845  ArgumentListIterator srcAli(*srcAl),dstAli(*dstAl);
3846  Argument *srcA,*dstA;
3847  for (;(srcA=srcAli.current()) && (dstA=dstAli.current());++srcAli,++dstAli)
3848  {
3849  if (srcA->defval.isEmpty() && !dstA->defval.isEmpty())
3850  {
3851  //printf("Defval changing `%s'->`%s'\n",srcA->defval.data(),dstA->defval.data());
3852  srcA->defval=dstA->defval.copy();
3853  }
3854  else if (!srcA->defval.isEmpty() && dstA->defval.isEmpty())
3855  {
3856  //printf("Defval changing `%s'->`%s'\n",dstA->defval.data(),srcA->defval.data());
3857  dstA->defval=srcA->defval.copy();
3858  }
3859 
3860  // fix wrongly detected const or volatile specifiers before merging.
3861  // example: "const A *const" is detected as type="const A *" name="const"
3862  if (srcA->name=="const" || srcA->name=="volatile")
3863  {
3864  srcA->type+=" "+srcA->name;
3865  srcA->name.resize(0);
3866  }
3867  if (dstA->name=="const" || dstA->name=="volatile")
3868  {
3869  dstA->type+=" "+dstA->name;
3870  dstA->name.resize(0);
3871  }
3872 
3873  if (srcA->type==dstA->type)
3874  {
3875  //printf("1. merging %s:%s <-> %s:%s\n",srcA->type.data(),srcA->name.data(),dstA->type.data(),dstA->name.data());
3876  if (srcA->name.isEmpty() && !dstA->name.isEmpty())
3877  {
3878  //printf("type: `%s':=`%s'\n",srcA->type.data(),dstA->type.data());
3879  //printf("name: `%s':=`%s'\n",srcA->name.data(),dstA->name.data());
3880  srcA->type = dstA->type.copy();
3881  srcA->name = dstA->name.copy();
3882  }
3883  else if (!srcA->name.isEmpty() && dstA->name.isEmpty())
3884  {
3885  //printf("type: `%s':=`%s'\n",dstA->type.data(),srcA->type.data());
3886  //printf("name: `%s':=`%s'\n",dstA->name.data(),srcA->name.data());
3887  dstA->type = srcA->type.copy();
3888  dstA->name = dstA->name.copy();
3889  }
3890  else if (!srcA->name.isEmpty() && !dstA->name.isEmpty())
3891  {
3892  //printf("srcA->name=%s dstA->name=%s\n",srcA->name.data(),dstA->name.data());
3893  if (forceNameOverwrite)
3894  {
3895  srcA->name = dstA->name;
3896  }
3897  else
3898  {
3899  if (srcA->docs.isEmpty() && !dstA->docs.isEmpty())
3900  {
3901  srcA->name = dstA->name;
3902  }
3903  else if (!srcA->docs.isEmpty() && dstA->docs.isEmpty())
3904  {
3905  dstA->name = srcA->name;
3906  }
3907  }
3908  }
3909  }
3910  else
3911  {
3912  //printf("2. merging '%s':'%s' <-> '%s':'%s'\n",srcA->type.data(),srcA->name.data(),dstA->type.data(),dstA->name.data());
3913  srcA->type=srcA->type.stripWhiteSpace();
3914  dstA->type=dstA->type.stripWhiteSpace();
3915  if (srcA->type+" "+srcA->name==dstA->type) // "unsigned long:int" <-> "unsigned long int:bla"
3916  {
3917  srcA->type+=" "+srcA->name;
3918  srcA->name=dstA->name;
3919  }
3920  else if (dstA->type+" "+dstA->name==srcA->type) // "unsigned long int bla" <-> "unsigned long int"
3921  {
3922  dstA->type+=" "+dstA->name;
3923  dstA->name=srcA->name;
3924  }
3925  else if (srcA->name.isEmpty() && !dstA->name.isEmpty())
3926  {
3927  srcA->name = dstA->name;
3928  }
3929  else if (dstA->name.isEmpty() && !srcA->name.isEmpty())
3930  {
3931  dstA->name = srcA->name;
3932  }
3933  }
3934  int i1=srcA->type.find("::"),
3935  i2=dstA->type.find("::"),
3936  j1=srcA->type.length()-i1-2,
3937  j2=dstA->type.length()-i2-2;
3938  if (i1!=-1 && i2==-1 && srcA->type.right(j1)==dstA->type)
3939  {
3940  //printf("type: `%s':=`%s'\n",dstA->type.data(),srcA->type.data());
3941  //printf("name: `%s':=`%s'\n",dstA->name.data(),srcA->name.data());
3942  dstA->type = srcA->type.left(i1+2)+dstA->type;
3943  dstA->name = dstA->name.copy();
3944  }
3945  else if (i1==-1 && i2!=-1 && dstA->type.right(j2)==srcA->type)
3946  {
3947  //printf("type: `%s':=`%s'\n",srcA->type.data(),dstA->type.data());
3948  //printf("name: `%s':=`%s'\n",dstA->name.data(),srcA->name.data());
3949  srcA->type = dstA->type.left(i2+2)+srcA->type;
3950  srcA->name = dstA->name.copy();
3951  }
3952  if (srcA->docs.isEmpty() && !dstA->docs.isEmpty())
3953  {
3954  srcA->docs = dstA->docs.copy();
3955  }
3956  else if (dstA->docs.isEmpty() && !srcA->docs.isEmpty())
3957  {
3958  dstA->docs = srcA->docs.copy();
3959  }
3960  //printf("Merge argument `%s|%s' `%s|%s'\n",
3961  // srcA->type.data(),srcA->name.data(),
3962  // dstA->type.data(),dstA->name.data());
3963  }
3964 }
3965 
3966 static void findMembersWithSpecificName(MemberName *mn,
3967  const char *args,
3968  bool checkStatics,
3969  FileDef *currentFile,
3970  bool checkCV,
3971  const char *forceTagFile,
3972  QList<MemberDef> &members)
3973 {
3974  //printf(" Function with global scope name `%s' args=`%s'\n",
3975  // mn->memberName(),args);
3976  MemberNameIterator mli(*mn);
3977  MemberDef *md;
3978  for (mli.toFirst();(md=mli.current());++mli)
3979  {
3980  FileDef *fd=md->getFileDef();
3981  GroupDef *gd=md->getGroupDef();
3982  //printf(" md->name()=`%s' md->args=`%s' fd=%p gd=%p current=%p ref=%s\n",
3983  // md->name().data(),args,fd,gd,currentFile,md->getReference().data());
3984  if (
3985  ((gd && gd->isLinkable()) || (fd && fd->isLinkable()) || md->isReference()) &&
3986  md->getNamespaceDef()==0 && md->isLinkable() &&
3987  (!checkStatics || (!md->isStatic() && !md->isDefine()) ||
3988  currentFile==0 || fd==currentFile) // statics must appear in the same file
3989  )
3990  {
3991  bool match=TRUE;
3992  ArgumentList *argList=0;
3993  if (args && !md->isDefine() && qstrcmp(args,"()")!=0)
3994  {
3995  argList=new ArgumentList;
3996  ArgumentList *mdAl = md->argumentList();
3997  stringToArgumentList(args,argList);
3998  match=matchArguments2(
3999  md->getOuterScope(),fd,mdAl,
4000  Doxygen::globalScope,fd,argList,
4001  checkCV);
4002  delete argList; argList=0;
4003  }
4004  if (match && (forceTagFile==0 || md->getReference()==forceTagFile))
4005  {
4006  //printf("Found match!\n");
4007  members.append(md);
4008  }
4009  }
4010  }
4011 }
4012 
4035 bool getDefs(const QCString &scName,
4036  const QCString &mbName,
4037  const char *args,
4038  MemberDef *&md,
4039  ClassDef *&cd,
4040  FileDef *&fd,
4041  NamespaceDef *&nd,
4042  GroupDef *&gd,
4043  bool forceEmptyScope,
4044  FileDef *currentFile,
4045  bool checkCV,
4046  const char *forceTagFile
4047  )
4048 {
4049  fd=0, md=0, cd=0, nd=0, gd=0;
4050  if (mbName.isEmpty()) return FALSE; /* empty name => nothing to link */
4051 
4052  QCString scopeName=scName;
4053  QCString memberName=mbName;
4054  scopeName = substitute(scopeName,"\\","::"); // for PHP
4055  memberName = substitute(memberName,"\\","::"); // for PHP
4056  //printf("Search for name=%s args=%s in scope=%s forceEmpty=%d\n",
4057  // memberName.data(),args,scopeName.data(),forceEmptyScope);
4058 
4059  int is,im=0,pm=0;
4060  // strip common part of the scope from the scopeName
4061  while ((is=scopeName.findRev("::"))!=-1 &&
4062  (im=memberName.find("::",pm))!=-1 &&
4063  (scopeName.right(scopeName.length()-is-2)==memberName.mid(pm,im-pm))
4064  )
4065  {
4066  scopeName=scopeName.left(is);
4067  pm=im+2;
4068  }
4069  //printf("result after scope corrections scope=%s name=%s\n",
4070  // scopeName.data(),memberName.data());
4071 
4072  QCString mName=memberName;
4073  QCString mScope;
4074  if (memberName.left(9)!="operator " && // treat operator conversion methods
4075  // as a special case
4076  (im=memberName.findRev("::"))!=-1 &&
4077  im<(int)memberName.length()-2 // not A::
4078  )
4079  {
4080  mScope=memberName.left(im);
4081  mName=memberName.right(memberName.length()-im-2);
4082  }
4083 
4084  // handle special the case where both scope name and member scope are equal
4085  if (mScope==scopeName) scopeName.resize(0);
4086 
4087  //printf("mScope=`%s' mName=`%s'\n",mScope.data(),mName.data());
4088 
4089  MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameSDict->find(mName);
4090  //printf("mName=%s mn=%p\n",mName.data(),mn);
4091 
4092  if ((!forceEmptyScope || scopeName.isEmpty()) && // this was changed for bug638856, forceEmptyScope => empty scopeName
4093  mn && !(scopeName.isEmpty() && mScope.isEmpty()))
4094  {
4095  //printf(" >member name '%s' found\n",mName.data());
4096  int scopeOffset=scopeName.length();
4097  do
4098  {
4099  QCString className = scopeName.left(scopeOffset);
4100  if (!className.isEmpty() && !mScope.isEmpty())
4101  {
4102  className+="::"+mScope;
4103  }
4104  else if (!mScope.isEmpty())
4105  {
4106  className=mScope;
4107  }
4108 
4109  MemberDef *tmd=0;
4110  ClassDef *fcd=getResolvedClass(Doxygen::globalScope,0,className,&tmd);
4111  if (fcd==0 && className.find('<')!=-1) // try without template specifiers as well
4112  {
4113  QCString nameWithoutTemplates = stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(className,FALSE);
4114  fcd=getResolvedClass(Doxygen::globalScope,0,nameWithoutTemplates,&tmd);
4115  }
4116  //printf("Trying class scope %s: fcd=%p tmd=%p\n",className.data(),fcd,tmd);
4117  // todo: fill in correct fileScope!
4118  if (fcd && // is it a documented class
4119  fcd->isLinkable()
4120  )
4121  {
4122  //printf(" Found fcd=%p\n",fcd);
4123  MemberNameIterator mmli(*mn);
4124  MemberDef *mmd;
4125  int mdist=maxInheritanceDepth;
4126  ArgumentList *argList=0;
4127  if (args)
4128  {
4129  argList=new ArgumentList;
4130  stringToArgumentList(args,argList);
4131  }
4132  for (mmli.toFirst();(mmd=mmli.current());++mmli)
4133  {
4134  if (!mmd->isStrongEnumValue())
4135  {
4136  ArgumentList *mmdAl = mmd->argumentList();
4137  bool match=args==0 ||
4138  matchArguments2(mmd->getOuterScope(),mmd->getFileDef(),mmdAl,
4139  fcd,fcd->getFileDef(),argList,
4140  checkCV
4141  );
4142  //printf("match=%d\n",match);
4143  if (match)
4144  {
4145  ClassDef *mcd=mmd->getClassDef();
4146  if (mcd)
4147  {
4148  int m=minClassDistance(fcd,mcd);
4149  if (m<mdist && mcd->isLinkable())
4150  {
4151  mdist=m;
4152  cd=mcd;
4153  md=mmd;
4154  }
4155  }
4156  }
4157  }
4158  }
4159  if (argList)
4160  {
4161  delete argList; argList=0;
4162  }
4163  if (mdist==maxInheritanceDepth && args && qstrcmp(args,"()")==0)
4164  // no exact match found, but if args="()" an arbitrary member will do
4165  {
4166  //printf(" >Searching for arbitrary member\n");
4167  for (mmli.toFirst();(mmd=mmli.current());++mmli)
4168  {
4169  //if (mmd->isLinkable())
4170  //{
4171  ClassDef *mcd=mmd->getClassDef();
4172  //printf(" >Class %s found\n",mcd->name().data());
4173  if (mcd)
4174  {
4175  int m=minClassDistance(fcd,mcd);
4176  if (m<mdist /* && mcd->isLinkable()*/ )
4177  {
4178  //printf("Class distance %d\n",m);
4179  mdist=m;
4180  cd=mcd;
4181  md=mmd;
4182  }
4183  }
4184  //}
4185  }
4186  }
4187  //printf(" >Succes=%d\n",mdist<maxInheritanceDepth);
4188  if (mdist<maxInheritanceDepth)
4189  {
4190  if (!md->isLinkable() || md->isStrongEnumValue())
4191  {
4192  md=0; // avoid returning things we cannot link to
4193  cd=0;
4194  return FALSE; // match found, but was not linkable
4195  }
4196  else
4197  {
4198  gd=md->getGroupDef();
4199  if (gd) cd=0;
4200  return TRUE; /* found match */
4201  }
4202  }
4203  }
4204  if (tmd && tmd->isEnumerate() && tmd->isStrong()) // scoped enum
4205  {
4206  //printf("Found scoped enum!\n");
4207  MemberList *tml = tmd->enumFieldList();
4208  if (tml)
4209  {
4210  MemberListIterator tmi(*tml);
4211  MemberDef *emd;
4212  for (;(emd=tmi.current());++tmi)
4213  {
4214  if (emd->localName()==mName)
4215  {
4216  if (emd->isLinkable())
4217  {
4218  cd=tmd->getClassDef();
4219  md=emd;
4220  return TRUE;
4221  }
4222  else
4223  {
4224  cd=0;
4225  md=0;
4226  return FALSE;
4227  }
4228  }
4229  }
4230  }
4231  }
4232  /* go to the parent scope */
4233  if (scopeOffset==0)
4234  {
4235  scopeOffset=-1;
4236  }
4237  else if ((scopeOffset=scopeName.findRev("::",scopeOffset-1))==-1)
4238  {
4239  scopeOffset=0;
4240  }
4241  } while (scopeOffset>=0);
4242 
4243  }
4244  if (mn && scopeName.isEmpty() && mScope.isEmpty()) // Maybe a related function?
4245  {
4246  //printf("Global symbol\n");
4247  MemberNameIterator mmli(*mn);
4248  MemberDef *mmd, *fuzzy_mmd = 0;
4249  ArgumentList *argList = 0;
4250  bool hasEmptyArgs = args && qstrcmp(args, "()") == 0;
4251 
4252  if (args)
4253  stringToArgumentList(args, argList = new ArgumentList);
4254 
4255  for (mmli.toFirst(); (mmd = mmli.current()); ++mmli)
4256  {
4257  if (!mmd->isLinkable() || (!mmd->isRelated() && !mmd->isForeign()) ||
4258  !mmd->getClassDef())
4259  continue;
4260 
4261  if (!args) break;
4262 
4263  ArgumentList *mmdAl = mmd->argumentList();
4264  if (matchArguments2(mmd->getOuterScope(),mmd->getFileDef(),mmdAl,
4265  Doxygen::globalScope,mmd->getFileDef(),argList,
4266  checkCV
4267  )
4268  ) break;
4269 
4270  if (!fuzzy_mmd && hasEmptyArgs)
4271  fuzzy_mmd = mmd;
4272  }
4273 
4274  if (argList) delete argList, argList = 0;
4275 
4276  mmd = mmd ? mmd : fuzzy_mmd;
4277 
4278  if (mmd && !mmd->isStrongEnumValue())
4279  {
4280  md = mmd;
4281  cd = mmd->getClassDef();
4282  return TRUE;
4283  }
4284  }
4285 
4286 
4287  // maybe an namespace, file or group member ?
4288  //printf("Testing for global symbol scopeName=`%s' mScope=`%s' :: mName=`%s'\n",
4289  // scopeName.data(),mScope.data(),mName.data());
4290  if ((mn=Doxygen::functionNameSDict->find(mName))) // name is known
4291  {
4292  //printf(" >symbol name found\n");
4293  NamespaceDef *fnd=0;
4294  int scopeOffset=scopeName.length();
4295  do
4296  {
4297  QCString namespaceName = scopeName.left(scopeOffset);
4298  if (!namespaceName.isEmpty() && !mScope.isEmpty())
4299  {
4300  namespaceName+="::"+mScope;
4301  }
4302  else if (!mScope.isEmpty())
4303  {
4304  namespaceName=mScope.copy();
4305  }
4306  //printf("Trying namespace %s\n",namespaceName.data());
4307  if (!namespaceName.isEmpty() &&
4308  (fnd=Doxygen::namespaceSDict->find(namespaceName)) &&
4309  fnd->isLinkable()
4310  )
4311  {
4312  //printf("Symbol inside existing namespace `%s' count=%d\n",
4313  // namespaceName.data(),mn->count());
4314  bool found=FALSE;
4315  MemberNameIterator mmli(*mn);
4316  MemberDef *mmd;
4317  for (mmli.toFirst();((mmd=mmli.current()) && !found);++mmli)
4318  {
4319  //printf("mmd->getNamespaceDef()=%p fnd=%p\n",
4320  // mmd->getNamespaceDef(),fnd);
4321  MemberDef *emd = mmd->getEnumScope();
4322  if (emd && emd->isStrong())
4323  {
4324  //printf("yes match %s<->%s!\n",mScope.data(),emd->localName().data());
4325  if (emd->getNamespaceDef()==fnd &&
4326  rightScopeMatch(mScope,emd->localName()))
4327  {
4328  //printf("found it!\n");
4329  nd=fnd;
4330  md=mmd;
4331  found=TRUE;
4332  }
4333  else
4334  {
4335  md=0;
4336  cd=0;
4337  return FALSE;
4338  }
4339  }
4340  else if (mmd->getNamespaceDef()==fnd /* && mmd->isLinkable() */ )
4341  { // namespace is found
4342  bool match=TRUE;
4343  ArgumentList *argList=0;
4344  if (args && qstrcmp(args,"()")!=0)
4345  {
4346  argList=new ArgumentList;
4347  ArgumentList *mmdAl = mmd->argumentList();
4348  stringToArgumentList(args,argList);
4349  match=matchArguments2(
4350  mmd->getOuterScope(),mmd->getFileDef(),mmdAl,
4351  fnd,mmd->getFileDef(),argList,
4352  checkCV);
4353  }
4354  if (match)
4355  {
4356  nd=fnd;
4357  md=mmd;
4358  found=TRUE;
4359  }
4360  if (args)
4361  {
4362  delete argList; argList=0;
4363  }
4364  }
4365  }
4366  if (!found && args && !qstrcmp(args,"()"))
4367  // no exact match found, but if args="()" an arbitrary
4368  // member will do
4369  {
4370  for (mmli.toFirst();((mmd=mmli.current()) && !found);++mmli)
4371  {
4372  if (mmd->getNamespaceDef()==fnd /*&& mmd->isLinkable() */ )
4373  {
4374  nd=fnd;
4375  md=mmd;
4376  found=TRUE;
4377  }
4378  }
4379  }
4380  if (found)
4381  {
4382  if (!md->isLinkable())
4383  {
4384  md=0; // avoid returning things we cannot link to
4385  nd=0;
4386  return FALSE; // match found but not linkable
4387  }
4388  else
4389  {
4390  gd=md->getGroupDef();
4391  if (gd && gd->isLinkable()) nd=0; else gd=0;
4392  return TRUE;
4393  }
4394  }
4395  }
4396  else
4397  {
4398  //printf("not a namespace\n");
4399  MemberNameIterator mmli(*mn);
4400  MemberDef *mmd;
4401  for (mmli.toFirst();(mmd=mmli.current());++mmli)
4402  {
4403  MemberDef *tmd = mmd->getEnumScope();
4404  //printf("try member %s tmd=%s\n",mmd->name().data(),tmd?tmd->name().data():"<none>");
4405  int ni=namespaceName.findRev("::");
4406  //printf("namespaceName=%s ni=%d\n",namespaceName.data(),ni);
4407  bool notInNS = tmd && ni==-1 && tmd->getNamespaceDef()==0 && (mScope.isEmpty() || mScope==tmd->name());
4408  bool sameNS = tmd && tmd->getNamespaceDef() && namespaceName.left(ni)==tmd->getNamespaceDef()->name();
4409  //printf("notInNS=%d sameNS=%d\n",notInNS,sameNS);
4410  if (tmd && tmd->isStrong() && // C++11 enum class
4411  (notInNS || sameNS) &&
4412  namespaceName.length()>0 // enum is part of namespace so this should not be empty
4413  )
4414  {
4415  md=mmd;
4416  fd=mmd->getFileDef();
4417  gd=mmd->getGroupDef();
4418  if (gd && gd->isLinkable()) fd=0; else gd=0;
4419  //printf("Found scoped enum %s fd=%p gd=%p\n",
4420  // mmd->name().data(),fd,gd);
4421  return TRUE;
4422  }
4423  }
4424  }
4425  if (scopeOffset==0)
4426  {
4427  scopeOffset=-1;
4428  }
4429  else if ((scopeOffset=scopeName.findRev("::",scopeOffset-1))==-1)
4430  {
4431  scopeOffset=0;
4432  }
4433  } while (scopeOffset>=0);
4434 
4435  //else // no scope => global function
4436  {
4437  QList<MemberDef> members;
4438  // search for matches with strict static checking
4439  findMembersWithSpecificName(mn,args,TRUE,currentFile,checkCV,forceTagFile,members);
4440  if (members.count()==0) // nothing found
4441  {
4442  // search again without strict static checking
4443  findMembersWithSpecificName(mn,args,FALSE,currentFile,checkCV,forceTagFile,members);
4444  }
4445  //printf("found %d members\n",members.count());
4446  if (members.count()!=1 && args && !qstrcmp(args,"()"))
4447  {
4448  // no exact match found, but if args="()" an arbitrary
4449  // member will do
4450  MemberNameIterator mni(*mn);
4451  for (mni.toLast();(md=mni.current());--mni)
4452  {
4453  //printf("Found member `%s'\n",md->name().data());
4454  //printf("member is linkable md->name()=`%s'\n",md->name().data());
4455  fd=md->getFileDef();
4456  gd=md->getGroupDef();
4457  MemberDef *tmd = md->getEnumScope();
4458  if (
4459  (gd && gd->isLinkable()) || (fd && fd->isLinkable()) ||
4460  (tmd && tmd->isStrong())
4461  )
4462  {
4463  members.append(md);
4464  }
4465  }
4466  }
4467  //printf("found %d candidate members\n",members.count());
4468  if (members.count()>0) // at least one match
4469  {
4470  if (currentFile)
4471  {
4472  //printf("multiple results; pick one from file:%s\n", currentFile->name().data());
4473  QListIterator<MemberDef> mit(members);
4474  for (mit.toFirst();(md=mit.current());++mit)
4475  {
4476  if (md->getFileDef() && md->getFileDef()->name() == currentFile->name())
4477  {
4478  break; // found match in the current file
4479  }
4480  }
4481  if (!md) // member not in the current file
4482  {
4483  md=members.getLast();
4484  }
4485  }
4486  else
4487  {
4488  md=members.getLast();
4489  }
4490  }
4491  if (md && (md->getEnumScope()==0 || !md->getEnumScope()->isStrong()))
4492  // found a matching global member, that is not a scoped enum value (or uniquely matches)
4493  {
4494  fd=md->getFileDef();
4495  gd=md->getGroupDef();
4496  //printf("fd=%p gd=%p gd->isLinkable()=%d\n",fd,gd,gd->isLinkable());
4497  if (gd && gd->isLinkable()) fd=0; else gd=0;
4498  return TRUE;
4499  }
4500  }
4501  }
4502 
4503  // no nothing found
4504  return FALSE;
4505 }
4506 
4521 static bool getScopeDefs(const char *docScope,const char *scope,
4522  ClassDef *&cd, NamespaceDef *&nd)
4523 {
4524  cd=0;nd=0;
4525 
4526  QCString scopeName=scope;
4527  //printf("getScopeDefs: docScope=`%s' scope=`%s'\n",docScope,scope);
4528  if (scopeName.isEmpty()) return FALSE;
4529 
4530  bool explicitGlobalScope=FALSE;
4531  if (scopeName.at(0)==':' && scopeName.at(1)==':')
4532  {
4533  scopeName=scopeName.right(scopeName.length()-2);
4534  explicitGlobalScope=TRUE;
4535  }
4536 
4537  QCString docScopeName=docScope;
4538  int scopeOffset=explicitGlobalScope ? 0 : docScopeName.length();
4539 
4540  do // for each possible docScope (from largest to and including empty)
4541  {
4542  QCString fullName=scopeName.copy();
4543  if (scopeOffset>0) fullName.prepend(docScopeName.left(scopeOffset)+"::");
4544 
4545  if (((cd=getClass(fullName)) || // normal class
4546  (cd=getClass(fullName+"-p")) //|| // ObjC protocol
4547  //(cd=getClass(fullName+"-g")) // C# generic
4548  ) && cd->isLinkable())
4549  {
4550  return TRUE; // class link written => quit
4551  }
4552  else if ((nd=Doxygen::namespaceSDict->find(fullName)) && nd->isLinkable())
4553  {
4554  return TRUE; // namespace link written => quit
4555  }
4556  if (scopeOffset==0)
4557  {
4558  scopeOffset=-1;
4559  }
4560  else if ((scopeOffset=docScopeName.findRev("::",scopeOffset-1))==-1)
4561  {
4562  scopeOffset=0;
4563  }
4564  } while (scopeOffset>=0);
4565 
4566  return FALSE;
4567 }
4568 
4569 static bool isLowerCase(QCString &s)
4570 {
4571  uchar *p=(uchar*)s.data();
4572  if (p==0) return TRUE;
4573  int c;
4574  while ((c=*p++)) if (!islower(c)) return FALSE;
4575  return TRUE;
4576 }
4577 
4581 bool resolveRef(/* in */ const char *scName,
4582  /* in */ const char *name,
4583  /* in */ bool inSeeBlock,
4584  /* out */ Definition **resContext,
4585  /* out */ MemberDef **resMember,
4586  bool lookForSpecialization,
4587  FileDef *currentFile,
4588  bool checkScope
4589  )
4590 {
4591  //printf("resolveRef(scope=%s,name=%s,inSeeBlock=%d)\n",scName,name,inSeeBlock);
4592  QCString tsName = name;
4593  //bool memberScopeFirst = tsName.find('#')!=-1;
4594  QCString fullName = substitute(tsName,"#","::");
4595  if (fullName.find("anonymous_namespace{")==-1)
4596  {
4597  fullName = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(substitute(fullName,".","::"));
4598  }
4599  else
4600  {
4601  fullName = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(fullName);
4602  }
4603 
4604  int bracePos=findParameterList(fullName);
4605  int endNamePos=bracePos!=-1 ? bracePos : fullName.length();
4606  int scopePos=fullName.findRev("::",endNamePos);
4607  bool explicitScope = fullName.left(2)=="::" && // ::scope or #scope
4608  (scopePos>2 || // ::N::A
4609  tsName.left(2)=="::" || // ::foo in local scope
4610  scName==0 // #foo in global scope
4611  );
4612 
4613  // default result values
4614  *resContext=0;
4615  *resMember=0;
4616 
4617  if (bracePos==-1) // simple name
4618  {
4619  ClassDef *cd=0;
4620  NamespaceDef *nd=0;
4621 
4622  // the following if() was commented out for releases in the range
4623  // 1.5.2 to 1.6.1, but has been restored as a result of bug report 594787.
4624  if (!inSeeBlock && scopePos==-1 && isLowerCase(tsName))
4625  { // link to lower case only name => do not try to autolink
4626  return FALSE;
4627  }
4628 
4629  //printf("scName=%s fullName=%s\n",scName,fullName.data());
4630 
4631  // check if this is a class or namespace reference
4632  if (scName!=fullName && getScopeDefs(scName,fullName,cd,nd))
4633  {
4634  if (cd) // scope matches that of a class
4635  {
4636  *resContext = cd;
4637  }
4638  else // scope matches that of a namespace
4639  {
4640  ASSERT(nd!=0);
4641  *resContext = nd;
4642  }
4643  return TRUE;
4644  }
4645  else if (scName==fullName || (!inSeeBlock && scopePos==-1))
4646  // nothing to link => output plain text
4647  {
4648  //printf("found scName=%s fullName=%s scName==fullName=%d "
4649  // "inSeeBlock=%d scopePos=%d!\n",
4650  // scName,fullName.data(),scName==fullName,inSeeBlock,scopePos);
4651  return FALSE;
4652  }
4653  // continue search...
4654  }
4655 
4656  // extract userscope+name
4657  QCString nameStr=fullName.left(endNamePos);
4658  if (explicitScope) nameStr=nameStr.mid(2);
4659 
4660  // extract arguments
4661  QCString argsStr;
4662  if (bracePos!=-1) argsStr=fullName.right(fullName.length()-bracePos);
4663 
4664  // strip template specifier
4665  // TODO: match against the correct partial template instantiation
4666  int templPos=nameStr.find('<');
4667  bool tryUnspecializedVersion = FALSE;
4668  if (templPos!=-1 && nameStr.find("operator")==-1)
4669  {
4670  int endTemplPos=nameStr.findRev('>');
4671  if (endTemplPos!=-1)
4672  {
4673  if (!lookForSpecialization)
4674  {
4675  nameStr=nameStr.left(templPos)+nameStr.right(nameStr.length()-endTemplPos-1);
4676  }
4677  else
4678  {
4679  tryUnspecializedVersion = TRUE;
4680  }
4681  }
4682  }
4683 
4684  QCString scopeStr=scName;
4685 
4686  MemberDef *md = 0;
4687  ClassDef *cd = 0;
4688  FileDef *fd = 0;
4689  NamespaceDef *nd = 0;
4690  GroupDef *gd = 0;
4691 
4692  // check if nameStr is a member or global.
4693  //printf("getDefs(scope=%s,name=%s,args=%s checkScope=%d)\n",
4694  // scopeStr.data(),nameStr.data(),argsStr.data(),checkScope);
4695  if (getDefs(scopeStr,nameStr,argsStr,
4696  md,cd,fd,nd,gd,
4697  //scopePos==0 && !memberScopeFirst, // forceEmptyScope
4698  explicitScope, // replaces prev line due to bug 600829
4699  currentFile,
4700  TRUE // checkCV
4701  )
4702  )
4703  {
4704  //printf("after getDefs checkScope=%d nameStr=%s cd=%p nd=%p\n",checkScope,nameStr.data(),cd,nd);
4705  if (checkScope && md && md->getOuterScope()==Doxygen::globalScope &&
4706  !md->isStrongEnumValue() &&
4707  (!scopeStr.isEmpty() || nameStr.find("::")>0))
4708  {
4709  // we did find a member, but it is a global one while we were explicitly
4710  // looking for a scoped variable. See bug 616387 for an example why this check is needed.
4711  // note we do need to support autolinking to "::symbol" hence the >0
4712  //printf("not global member!\n");
4713  *resContext=0;
4714  *resMember=0;
4715  return FALSE;
4716  }
4717  //printf("after getDefs md=%p cd=%p fd=%p nd=%p gd=%p\n",md,cd,fd,nd,gd);
4718  if (md) { *resMember=md; *resContext=md; }
4719  else if (cd) *resContext=cd;
4720  else if (nd) *resContext=nd;
4721  else if (fd) *resContext=fd;
4722  else if (gd) *resContext=gd;
4723  else { *resContext=0; *resMember=0; return FALSE; }
4724  //printf("member=%s (md=%p) anchor=%s linkable()=%d context=%s\n",
4725  // md->name().data(),md,md->anchor().data(),md->isLinkable(),(*resContext)->name().data());
4726  return TRUE;
4727  }
4728  else if (inSeeBlock && !nameStr.isEmpty() && (gd=Doxygen::groupSDict->find(nameStr)))
4729  { // group link
4730  *resContext=gd;
4731  return TRUE;
4732  }
4733  else if (tsName.find('.')!=-1) // maybe a link to a file
4734  {
4735  bool ambig;
4736  fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameDict,tsName,ambig);
4737  if (fd && !ambig)
4738  {
4739  *resContext=fd;
4740  return TRUE;
4741  }
4742  }
4743 
4744  if (tryUnspecializedVersion)
4745  {
4746  return resolveRef(scName,name,inSeeBlock,resContext,resMember,FALSE,0,checkScope);
4747  }
4748  if (bracePos!=-1) // Try without parameters as well, could be a contructor invocation
4749  {
4750  *resContext=getClass(fullName.left(bracePos));
4751  if (*resContext)
4752  {
4753  return TRUE;
4754  }
4755  }
4756  //printf("resolveRef: %s not found!\n",name);
4757 
4758  return FALSE;
4759 }
4760 
4761 QCString linkToText(SrcLangExt lang,const char *link,bool isFileName)
4762 {
4763  //static bool optimizeOutputJava = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_JAVA);
4764  QCString result=link;
4765  if (!result.isEmpty())
4766  {
4767  // replace # by ::
4768  result=substitute(result,"#","::");
4769  // replace . by ::
4770  if (!isFileName && result.find('<')==-1) result=substitute(result,".","::");
4771  // strip leading :: prefix if present
4772  if (result.at(0)==':' && result.at(1)==':')
4773  {
4774  result=result.right(result.length()-2);
4775  }
4776  QCString sep = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang);
4777  if (sep!="::")
4778  {
4779  result=substitute(result,"::",sep);
4780  }
4781  }
4782  return result;
4783 }

4786 /*
4787  * generate a reference to a class, namespace or member.
4788  * `scName' is the name of the scope that contains the documentation
4789  * string that is returned.
4790  * `name' is the name that we want to link to.
4791  * `name' may have five formats:
4792  * 1) "ScopeName"
4793  * 2) "memberName()" one of the (overloaded) function or define
4794  * with name memberName.
4795  * 3) "memberName(...)" a specific (overloaded) function or define
4796  * with name memberName

4798  * 4) "\#memberName member variable, global variable or define
4799  * 5) ("ScopeName::")+"memberName()"
4800  * 6) ("ScopeName::")+"memberName(...)"
4801  * 7) ("ScopeName::")+"memberName"
4802  * instead of :: the \# symbol may also be used.
4803  */

4805 bool generateRef(OutputDocInterface &od,const char *scName,
4806  const char *name,bool inSeeBlock,const char *rt)
4807 {
4808  //printf("generateRef(scName=%s,name=%s,inSee=%d,rt=%s)\n",scName,name,inSeeBlock,rt);

4811  MemberDef *md;

4835  }

4841  compound->getOutputFileBase(),
4842  0,linkText);

4854 
4855 bool resolveLink(/* in */ const char *scName,
4856  /* in */ const char *lr,
4857  /* in */ bool /*inSeeBlock*/,
4858  /* out */ Definition **resContext,
4859  /* out */ QCString &resAnchor
4860  )
4861 {
4862  *resContext=0;
4863 
4864  QCString linkRef=lr;
4865  QCString linkRefWithoutTemplates = stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(linkRef,FALSE);
4866  //printf("ResolveLink linkRef=%s\n",lr);
4867  FileDef *fd;
4868  GroupDef *gd;
4869  PageDef *pd;
4870  ClassDef *cd;
4871  DirDef *dir;
4872  NamespaceDef *nd;
4873  SectionInfo *si=0;
4874  bool ambig;
4875  if (linkRef.isEmpty()) // no reference name!
4876  {
4877  return FALSE;
4878  }
4879  else if ((pd=Doxygen::pageSDict->find(linkRef))) // link to a page
4880  {
4881  GroupDef *gd = pd->getGroupDef();
4882  if (gd)
4883  {
4884  if (!pd->name().isEmpty()) si=Doxygen::sectionDict->find(pd->name());
4885  *resContext=gd;
4886  if (si) resAnchor = si->label;
4887  }
4888  else
4889  {
4890  *resContext=pd;
4891  }
4892  return TRUE;
4893  }
4894  else if ((si=Doxygen::sectionDict->find(linkRef)))
4895  {
4896  *resContext=si->definition;
4897  resAnchor = si->label;
4898  return TRUE;
4899  }
4900  else if ((pd=Doxygen::exampleSDict->find(linkRef))) // link to an example
4901  {
4902  *resContext=pd;
4903  return TRUE;
4904  }
4905  else if ((gd=Doxygen::groupSDict->find(linkRef))) // link to a group
4906  {
4907  *resContext=gd;
4908  return TRUE;
4909  }
4910  else if ((fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameDict,linkRef,ambig)) // file link
4911  && fd->isLinkable())
4912  {
4913  *resContext=fd;
4914  return TRUE;
4915  }
4916  else if ((cd=getClass(linkRef))) // class link
4917  {
4918  *resContext=cd;
4919  resAnchor=cd->anchor();
4920  return TRUE;
4921  }
4922  else if ((cd=getClass(linkRefWithoutTemplates))) // C#/Java generic class link
4923  {
4924  *resContext=cd;
4925  resAnchor=cd->anchor();
4926  return TRUE;
4927  }
4928  else if ((cd=getClass(linkRef+"-p"))) // Obj-C protocol link
4929  {
4930  *resContext=cd;
4931  resAnchor=cd->anchor();
4932  return TRUE;
4933  }
4934 // else if ((cd=getClass(linkRef+"-g"))) // C# generic link
4935 // {
4936 // *resContext=cd;
4937 // resAnchor=cd->anchor();
4938 // return TRUE;
4939 // }
4940  else if ((nd=Doxygen::namespaceSDict->find(linkRef)))
4941  {
4942  *resContext=nd;
4943  return TRUE;
4944  }
4945  else if ((dir=Doxygen::directories->find(QFileInfo(linkRef).absFilePath().utf8()+"/"))
4946  && dir->isLinkable()) // TODO: make this location independent like filedefs
4947  {
4948  *resContext=dir;
4949  return TRUE;
4950  }
4951  else // probably a member reference
4952  {
4953  MemberDef *md;
4954  bool res = resolveRef(scName,lr,TRUE,resContext,&md);
4955  if (md) resAnchor=md->anchor();
4956  return res;
4957  }
4958 }
4959

4961 //----------------------------------------------------------------------
4962 // General function that generates the HTML code for a reference to some
4963 // file, class or member from text `lr' within the context of class `clName'.
4964 // This link has the text 'lt' (if not 0), otherwise `lr' is used as a
4965 // basis for the link's text.
4966 // returns TRUE if a link could be generated.
4967 
4968 bool generateLink(OutputDocInterface &od,const char *clName,
4969  const char *lr,bool inSeeBlock,const char *lt)
4970 {
4971  //printf("generateLink(clName=%s,lr=%s,lr=%s)\n",clName,lr,lt);
4972  Definition *compound;
4973  //PageDef *pageDef=0;
4974  QCString anchor,linkText=linkToText(SrcLangExt_Unknown,lt,FALSE);
4975  //printf("generateLink linkText=%s\n",linkText.data());
4976  if (resolveLink(clName,lr,inSeeBlock,&compound,anchor))
4977  {
4978  if (compound) // link to compound
4979  {
4980  if (lt==0 && anchor.isEmpty() && /* compound link */
4981  compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypeGroup /* is group */
4982  )
4983  {
4984  linkText=((GroupDef *)compound)->groupTitle(); // use group's title as link
4985  }
4986  else if (compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypeFile)
4987  {
4988  linkText=linkToText(compound->getLanguage(),lt,TRUE);
4989  }
4990  od.writeObjectLink(compound->getReference(),
4991  compound->getOutputFileBase(),anchor,linkText);
4992  if (!compound->isReference())
4993  {
4994  writePageRef(od,compound->getOutputFileBase(),anchor);
4995  }
4996  }
4997  else
4998  {
4999  err("%s:%d: Internal error: resolveLink successful but no compound found!",__FILE__,__LINE__);
5000  }
5001  return TRUE;
5002  }
5003  else // link could not be found
5004  {
5005  od.docify(linkText);
5006  return FALSE;
5007  }
5008 }

5010 void generateFileRef(OutputDocInterface &od,const char *name,const char *text)
5011 {
5012  //printf("generateFileRef(%s,%s)\n",name,text);
5013  QCString linkText = text ? text : name;
5014  //FileInfo *fi;
5015  FileDef *fd;
5016  bool ambig;
5017  if ((fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameDict,name,ambig)) &&
5018  fd->isLinkable())
5019  // link to documented input file
5020  od.writeObjectLink(fd->getReference(),fd->getOutputFileBase(),0,linkText);
5021  else
5022  od.docify(linkText);
5023 }

5056 struct FindFileCacheElem
5057 {
5058  FindFileCacheElem(FileDef *fd,bool ambig) : fileDef(fd), isAmbig(ambig) {}
5059  FileDef *fileDef;
5060  bool isAmbig;
5061 };
5062 
5063 static QCache<FindFileCacheElem> g_findFileDefCache(5000);
5064 
5065 FileDef *findFileDef(const FileNameDict *fnDict,const char *n,bool &ambig)
5066 {
5067  ambig=FALSE;
5068  if (n==0) return 0;
5069 
5070  const int maxAddrSize = 20;
5071  char addr[maxAddrSize];
5072  qsnprintf(addr,maxAddrSize,"%p:",fnDict);
5073  QCString key = addr;
5074  key+=n;
5075 
5076  g_findFileDefCache.setAutoDelete(TRUE);
5077  FindFileCacheElem *cachedResult = g_findFileDefCache.find(key);
5078  //printf("key=%s cachedResult=%p\n",key.data(),cachedResult);
5079  if (cachedResult)
5080  {
5081  ambig = cachedResult->isAmbig;
5082  //printf("cached: fileDef=%p\n",cachedResult->fileDef);
5083  return cachedResult->fileDef;
5084  }
5085  else
5086  {
5087  cachedResult = new FindFileCacheElem(0,FALSE);
5088  }
5089 
5090  QCString name=QDir::cleanDirPath(n).utf8();
5091  QCString path;
5092  int slashPos;
5093  FileName *fn;
5094  if (name.isEmpty()) goto exit;
5095  slashPos=QMAX(name.findRev('/'),name.findRev('\\'));
5096  if (slashPos!=-1)
5097  {
5098  path=name.left(slashPos+1);
5099  name=name.right(name.length()-slashPos-1);
5100  //printf("path=%s name=%s\n",path.data(),name.data());
5101  }
5102  if (name.isEmpty()) goto exit;
5103  if ((fn=(*fnDict)[name]))
5104  {
5105  //printf("fn->count()=%d\n",fn->count());
5106  if (fn->count()==1)
5107  {
5108  FileDef *fd = fn->getFirst();
5109 #if defined(_WIN32) || defined(__MACOSX__) // Windows or MacOSX
5110  bool isSamePath = fd->getPath().right(path.length()).lower()==path.lower();
5111 #else // Unix
5112  bool isSamePath = fd->getPath().right(path.length())==path;
5113 #endif
5114  if (path.isEmpty() || isSamePath)
5115  {
5116  cachedResult->fileDef = fd;
5117  g_findFileDefCache.insert(key,cachedResult);
5118  //printf("=1 ===> add to cache %p\n",fd);
5119  return fd;
5120  }
5121  }
5122  else // file name alone is ambiguous
5123  {
5124  int count=0;
5125  FileNameIterator fni(*fn);
5126  FileDef *fd;
5127  FileDef *lastMatch=0;
5128  QCString pathStripped = stripFromIncludePath(path);
5129  for (fni.toFirst();(fd=fni.current());++fni)
5130  {
5131  QCString fdStripPath = stripFromIncludePath(fd->getPath());
5132  if (path.isEmpty() || fdStripPath.right(pathStripped.length())==pathStripped)
5133  {
5134  count++;
5135  lastMatch=fd;
5136  }
5137  }
5138  //printf(">1 ===> add to cache %p\n",fd);
5139 
5140  ambig=(count>1);
5141  cachedResult->isAmbig = ambig;
5142  cachedResult->fileDef = lastMatch;
5143  g_findFileDefCache.insert(key,cachedResult);
5144  return lastMatch;
5145  }
5146  }
5147  else
5148  {
5149  //printf("not found!\n");
5150  }
5151 exit:
5152  //printf("0 ===> add to cache %p: %s\n",cachedResult,n);
5153  g_findFileDefCache.insert(key,cachedResult);
5154  //delete cachedResult;
5155  return 0;
5156 }

5160 QCString showFileDefMatches(const FileNameDict *fnDict,const char *n)
5161 {
5162  QCString result;
5163  QCString name=n;
5164  QCString path;
5165  int slashPos=QMAX(name.findRev('/'),name.findRev('\\'));
5166  if (slashPos!=-1)
5167  {
5168  path=name.left(slashPos+1);
5169  name=name.right(name.length()-slashPos-1);
5170  }
5171  FileName *fn;
5172  if ((fn=(*fnDict)[name]))
5173  {
5174  FileNameIterator fni(*fn);
5175  FileDef *fd;
5176  for (fni.toFirst();(fd=fni.current());++fni)
5177  {
5178  if (path.isEmpty() || fd->getPath().right(path.length())==path)
5179  {
5180  result+=" "+fd->absFilePath()+"\n";
5181  }
5182  }
5183  }
5184  return result;

5187 //----------------------------------------------------------------------
5188 
5190 QCString substitute(const QCString &s,const QCString &src,const QCString &dst)
5191 {
5192  if (s.isEmpty() || src.isEmpty()) return s;
5193  const char *p, *q;
5194  int srcLen = src.length();
5195  int dstLen = dst.length();
5196  int resLen;
5197  if (srcLen!=dstLen)
5198  {
5199  int count;
5200  for (count=0, p=s.data(); (q=strstr(p,src))!=0; p=q+srcLen) count++;
5201  resLen = s.length()+count*(dstLen-srcLen);
5202  }
5203  else // result has same size as s
5204  {
5205  resLen = s.length();
5206  }
5207  QCString result(resLen+1);
5208  char *r;
5209  for (r=result.rawData(), p=s; (q=strstr(p,src))!=0; p=q+srcLen)
5210  {
5211  int l = (int)(q-p);
5212  memcpy(r,p,l);
5213  r+=l;
5214  if (dst) memcpy(r,dst,dstLen);
5215  r+=dstLen;
5216  }
5217  qstrcpy(r,p);
5218  //printf("substitute(%s,%s,%s)->%s\n",s,src,dst,result.data());
5219  return result;
5220 }

5224 QCString substituteKeywords(const QCString &s,const char *title,
5225  const char *projName,const char *projNum,const char *projBrief)
5226 {
5227  QCString result = s;
5228  if (title) result = substitute(result,"$title",title);
5229  result = substitute(result,"$datetime",dateToString(TRUE));
5230  result = substitute(result,"$date",dateToString(FALSE));
5231  result = substitute(result,"$year",yearToString());
5232  result = substitute(result,"$doxygenversion",versionString);
5233  result = substitute(result,"$projectname",projName);
5234  result = substitute(result,"$projectnumber",projNum);
5235  result = substitute(result,"$projectbrief",projBrief);
5236  result = substitute(result,"$projectlogo",stripPath(Config_getString(PROJECT_LOGO)));
5237  return result;
5238 }

5246 int getPrefixIndex(const QCString &name)
5247 {
5248  if (name.isEmpty()) return 0;
5249  static QStrList &sl = Config_getList(IGNORE_PREFIX);
5250  char *s = sl.first();
5251  while (s)
5252  {
5253  const char *ps=s;
5254  const char *pd=name.data();
5255  int i=0;
5256  while (*ps!=0 && *pd!=0 && *ps==*pd) ps++,pd++,i++;
5257  if (*ps==0 && *pd!=0)
5258  {
5259  return i;
5260  }
5261  s = sl.next();
5262  }
5263  return 0;
5264 }

5268 static void initBaseClassHierarchy(BaseClassList *bcl)
5269 {
5270  if (bcl==0) return;
5271  BaseClassListIterator bcli(*bcl);
5272  for ( ; bcli.current(); ++bcli)
5273  {
5274  ClassDef *cd=bcli.current()->classDef;
5275  if (cd->baseClasses()==0) // no base classes => new root
5276  {
5277  initBaseClassHierarchy(cd->baseClasses());
5278  }
5279  cd->visited=FALSE;
5280  }
5281 }

5284 bool classHasVisibleChildren(ClassDef *cd)
5285 {
5286  BaseClassList *bcl;
5287 
5288  if (cd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_VHDL) // reverse baseClass/subClass relation
5289  {
5290  if (cd->baseClasses()==0) return FALSE;
5291  bcl=cd->baseClasses();
5292  }
5293  else
5294  {
5295  if (cd->subClasses()==0) return FALSE;
5296  bcl=cd->subClasses();
5297  }
5298 
5299  BaseClassListIterator bcli(*bcl);
5300  for ( ; bcli.current() ; ++bcli)
5301  {
5302  if (bcli.current()->classDef->isVisibleInHierarchy())
5303  {
5304  return TRUE;
5305  }
5306  }
5307  return FALSE;
5308 }

5341 //----------------------------------------------------------------------
5342 
5343 // note that this function is not reentrant due to the use of static growBuf!
5344 QCString escapeCharsInString(const char *name,bool allowDots,bool allowUnderscore)
5345 {
5346  static bool caseSenseNames = Config_getBool(CASE_SENSE_NAMES);
5347  static bool allowUnicodeNames = Config_getBool(ALLOW_UNICODE_NAMES);
5348  static GrowBuf growBuf;
5349  growBuf.clear();
5350  char c;
5351  const char *p=name;
5352  while ((c=*p++)!=0)
5353  {
5354  switch(c)
5355  {
5356  case '_': if (allowUnderscore) growBuf.addChar('_'); else growBuf.addStr("__"); break;
5357  case '-': growBuf.addChar('-'); break;
5358  case ':': growBuf.addStr("_1"); break;
5359  case '/': growBuf.addStr("_2"); break;
5360  case '<': growBuf.addStr("_3"); break;
5361  case '>': growBuf.addStr("_4"); break;
5362  case '*': growBuf.addStr("_5"); break;
5363  case '&': growBuf.addStr("_6"); break;
5364  case '|': growBuf.addStr("_7"); break;
5365  case '.': if (allowDots) growBuf.addChar('.'); else growBuf.addStr("_8"); break;
5366  case '!': growBuf.addStr("_9"); break;
5367  case ',': growBuf.addStr("_00"); break;
5368  case ' ': growBuf.addStr("_01"); break;
5369  case '{': growBuf.addStr("_02"); break;
5370  case '}': growBuf.addStr("_03"); break;
5371  case '?': growBuf.addStr("_04"); break;
5372  case '^': growBuf.addStr("_05"); break;
5373  case '%': growBuf.addStr("_06"); break;
5374  case '(': growBuf.addStr("_07"); break;
5375  case ')': growBuf.addStr("_08"); break;
5376  case '+': growBuf.addStr("_09"); break;
5377  case '=': growBuf.addStr("_0A"); break;
5378  case '$': growBuf.addStr("_0B"); break;
5379  case '\\': growBuf.addStr("_0C"); break;
5380  case '@': growBuf.addStr("_0D"); break;
5381  default:
5382  if (c<0)
5383  {
5384  char ids[5];
5385  const unsigned char uc = (unsigned char)c;
5386  bool doEscape = TRUE;
5387  if (allowUnicodeNames && uc <= 0xf7)
5388  {
5389  const char* pt = p;
5390  ids[ 0 ] = c;
5391  int l = 0;
5392  if ((uc&0xE0)==0xC0)
5393  {
5394  l=2; // 11xx.xxxx: >=2 byte character
5395  }
5396  if ((uc&0xF0)==0xE0)
5397  {
5398  l=3; // 111x.xxxx: >=3 byte character
5399  }
5400  if ((uc&0xF8)==0xF0)
5401  {
5402  l=4; // 1111.xxxx: >=4 byte character
5403  }
5404  doEscape = l==0;
5405  for (int m=1; m<l && !doEscape; ++m)
5406  {
5407  unsigned char ct = (unsigned char)*pt;
5408  if (ct==0 || (ct&0xC0)!=0x80) // invalid unicode character
5409  {
5410  doEscape=TRUE;
5411  }
5412  else
5413  {
5414  ids[ m ] = *pt++;
5415  }
5416  }
5417  if ( !doEscape ) // got a valid unicode character
5418  {
5419  ids[ l ] = 0;
5420  growBuf.addStr( ids );
5421  p += l - 1;
5422  }
5423  }
5424  if (doEscape) // not a valid unicode char or escaping needed
5425  {
5426  static char map[] = "0123456789ABCDEF";
5427  unsigned char id = (unsigned char)c;
5428  ids[0]='_';
5429  ids[1]='x';
5430  ids[2]=map[id>>4];
5431  ids[3]=map[id&0xF];
5432  ids[4]=0;
5433  growBuf.addStr(ids);
5434  }
5435  }
5436  else if (caseSenseNames || !isupper(c))
5437  {
5438  growBuf.addChar(c);
5439  }
5440  else
5441  {
5442  growBuf.addChar('_');
5443  growBuf.addChar(tolower(c));
5444  }
5445  break;
5446  }
5447  }
5448  growBuf.addChar(0);
5449  return growBuf.get();
5450 }
5451 
5456 QCString convertNameToFile(const char *name,bool allowDots,bool allowUnderscore)
5457 {
5458  if (name==0 || name[0]=='\0') return "";
5459  static bool shortNames = Config_getBool(SHORT_NAMES);
5460  static bool createSubdirs = Config_getBool(CREATE_SUBDIRS);
5461  QCString result;
5462  if (shortNames) // use short names only
5463  {
5464  static QDict<int> usedNames(10007);
5465  usedNames.setAutoDelete(TRUE);
5466  static int count=1;
5467 
5468  int *value=usedNames.find(name);
5469  int num;
5470  if (value==0)
5471  {
5472  usedNames.insert(name,new int(count));
5473  num = count++;
5474  }
5475  else
5476  {
5477  num = *value;
5478  }
5479  result.sprintf("a%05d",num);
5480  }
5481  else // long names
5482  {
5483  result=escapeCharsInString(name,allowDots,allowUnderscore);
5484  int resultLen = result.length();
5485  if (resultLen>=128) // prevent names that cannot be created!
5486  {
5487  // third algorithm based on MD5 hash
5488  uchar md5_sig[16];
5489  QCString sigStr(33);
5490  MD5Buffer((const unsigned char *)result.data(),resultLen,md5_sig);
5491  MD5SigToString(md5_sig,sigStr.rawData(),33);
5492  result=result.left(128-32)+sigStr;
5493  }
5494  }
5495  if (createSubdirs)
5496  {
5497  int l1Dir=0,l2Dir=0;
5498 
5499 #if MAP_ALGO==ALGO_COUNT
5500  // old algorithm, has the problem that after regeneration the
5501  // output can be located in a different dir.
5502  if (Doxygen::htmlDirMap==0)
5503  {
5504  Doxygen::htmlDirMap=new QDict<int>(100003);
5505  Doxygen::htmlDirMap->setAutoDelete(TRUE);
5506  }
5507  static int curDirNum=0;
5508  int *dirNum = Doxygen::htmlDirMap->find(result);
5509  if (dirNum==0) // new name
5510  {
5511  Doxygen::htmlDirMap->insert(result,new int(curDirNum));
5512  l1Dir = (curDirNum)&0xf; // bits 0-3
5513  l2Dir = (curDirNum>>4)&0xff; // bits 4-11
5514  curDirNum++;
5515  }
5516  else // existing name
5517  {
5518  l1Dir = (*dirNum)&0xf; // bits 0-3
5519  l2Dir = ((*dirNum)>>4)&0xff; // bits 4-11
5520  }
5521 #elif MAP_ALGO==ALGO_CRC16
5522  // second algorithm based on CRC-16 checksum
5523  int dirNum = qChecksum(result,result.length());
5524  l1Dir = dirNum&0xf;
5525  l2Dir = (dirNum>>4)&0xff;
5526 #elif MAP_ALGO==ALGO_MD5
5527  // third algorithm based on MD5 hash
5528  uchar md5_sig[16];
5529  MD5Buffer((const unsigned char *)result.data(),result.length(),md5_sig);
5530  l1Dir = md5_sig[14]&0xf;
5531  l2Dir = md5_sig[15];
5532 #endif
5533  result.prepend(QCString().sprintf("d%x/d%02x/",l1Dir,l2Dir));
5534  }
5535  //printf("*** convertNameToFile(%s)->%s\n",name,result.data());
5536  return result;
5537 }
5538 
5539 QCString relativePathToRoot(const char *name)
5540 {
5541  QCString result;
5542  if (Config_getBool(CREATE_SUBDIRS))
5543  {
5544  if (name==0)
5545  {
5546  return REL_PATH_TO_ROOT;
5547  }
5548  else
5549  {
5550  QCString n = name;
5551  int i = n.findRev('/');
5552  if (i!=-1)
5553  {
5554  result=REL_PATH_TO_ROOT;
5555  }
5556  }
5557  }
5558  return result;
5559 }

5561 void createSubDirs(QDir &d)
5562 {
5563  if (Config_getBool(CREATE_SUBDIRS))
5564  {
5565  // create 4096 subdirectories
5566  int l1,l2;
5567  for (l1=0;l1<16;l1++)
5568  {
5569  d.mkdir(QCString().sprintf("d%x",l1));
5570  for (l2=0;l2<256;l2++)
5571  {
5572  d.mkdir(QCString().sprintf("d%x/d%02x",l1,l2));
5573  }
5574  }
5575  }

5577 
5581 void extractNamespaceName(const QCString &scopeName,
5582  QCString &className,QCString &namespaceName,
5583  bool allowEmptyClass)
5584 {
5585  int i,p;
5586  QCString clName=scopeName;
5587  NamespaceDef *nd = 0;
5588  if (!clName.isEmpty() && (nd=getResolvedNamespace(clName)) && getClass(clName)==0)
5589  { // the whole name is a namespace (and not a class)
5590  namespaceName=nd->name().copy();
5591  className.resize(0);
5592  goto done;
5593  }
5594  p=clName.length()-2;
5595  while (p>=0 && (i=clName.findRev("::",p))!=-1)
5596  // see if the first part is a namespace (and not a class)
5597  {
5598  //printf("Trying %s\n",clName.left(i).data());
5599  if (i>0 && (nd=getResolvedNamespace(clName.left(i))) && getClass(clName.left(i))==0)
5600  {
5601  //printf("found!\n");
5602  namespaceName=nd->name().copy();
5603  className=clName.right(clName.length()-i-2);
5604  goto done;
5605  }
5606  p=i-2; // try a smaller piece of the scope
5607  }
5608  //printf("not found!\n");
5609 
5610  // not found, so we just have to guess.
5611  className=scopeName.copy();
5612  namespaceName.resize(0);
5613 
5614 done:
5615  if (className.isEmpty() && !namespaceName.isEmpty() && !allowEmptyClass)
5616  {
5617  // class and namespace with the same name, correct to return the class.
5618  className=namespaceName.copy();
5619  namespaceName.resize(0);
5620  }
5621  //printf("extractNamespace `%s' => `%s|%s'\n",scopeName.data(),
5622  // className.data(),namespaceName.data());
5623  if (/*className.right(2)=="-g" ||*/ className.right(2)=="-p")
5624  {
5625  className = className.left(className.length()-2);
5626  }
5627  return;
5628 }
5629 
5630 QCString insertTemplateSpecifierInScope(const QCString &scope,const QCString &templ)
5631 {
5632  QCString result=scope.copy();
5633  if (!templ.isEmpty() && scope.find('<')==-1)
5634  {
5635  int si,pi=0;
5636  ClassDef *cd=0;
5637  while (
5638  (si=scope.find("::",pi))!=-1 && !getClass(scope.left(si)+templ) &&
5639  ((cd=getClass(scope.left(si)))==0 || cd->templateArguments()==0)
5640  )
5641  {
5642  //printf("Tried `%s'\n",(scope.left(si)+templ).data());
5643  pi=si+2;
5644  }
5645  if (si==-1) // not nested => append template specifier
5646  {
5647  result+=templ;
5648  }
5649  else // nested => insert template specifier before after first class name
5650  {
5651  result=scope.left(si) + templ + scope.right(scope.length()-si);
5652  }
5653  }
5654  //printf("insertTemplateSpecifierInScope(`%s',`%s')=%s\n",
5655  // scope.data(),templ.data(),result.data());
5656  return result;
5657 }

5706 
5707 // new version by Davide Cesari which also works for Fortran
5708 QCString stripScope(const char *name)
5709 {
5710  QCString result = name;
5711  int l=result.length();
5712  int p;
5713  bool done = FALSE;
5714  bool skipBracket=FALSE; // if brackets do not match properly, ignore them altogether
5715  int count=0;
5716 
5717  do
5718  {
5719  p=l-1; // start at the end of the string
5720  while (p>=0 && count>=0)
5721  {
5722  char c=result.at(p);
5723  switch (c)
5724  {
5725  case ':':
5726  // only exit in the case of ::
5727  //printf("stripScope(%s)=%s\n",name,result.right(l-p-1).data());
5728  if (p>0 && result.at(p-1)==':') return result.right(l-p-1);
5729  p--;
5730  break;
5731  case '>':
5732  if (skipBracket) // we don't care about brackets
5733  {
5734  p--;
5735  }
5736  else // count open/close brackets
5737  {
5738  if (p>0 && result.at(p-1)=='>') // skip >> operator
5739  {
5740  p-=2;
5741  break;
5742  }
5743  count=1;
5744  //printf("pos < = %d\n",p);
5745  p--;
5746  bool foundMatch=false;
5747  while (p>=0 && !foundMatch)
5748  {
5749  c=result.at(p--);
5750  switch (c)
5751  {
5752  case '>':
5753  count++;
5754  break;
5755  case '<':
5756  if (p>0)
5757  {
5758  if (result.at(p-1) == '<') // skip << operator
5759  {
5760  p--;
5761  break;
5762  }
5763  }
5764  count--;
5765  foundMatch = count==0;
5766  break;
5767  default:
5768  //printf("c=%c count=%d\n",c,count);
5769  break;
5770  }
5771  }
5772  }
5773  //printf("pos > = %d\n",p+1);
5774  break;
5775  default:
5776  p--;
5777  }
5778  }
5779  done = count==0 || skipBracket; // reparse if brackets do not match
5780  skipBracket=TRUE;
5781  }
5782  while (!done); // if < > unbalanced repeat ignoring them
5783  //printf("stripScope(%s)=%s\n",name,name);
5784  return name;
5785 }
