5788 QCString convertToId(const char *s)
5789 {
5790  static const char hex[] = "0123456789ABCDEF";
5791  static GrowBuf growBuf;
5792  growBuf.clear();
5793  if (s==0) return "";
5794  const char *p=s;
5795  char c;
5796  bool first=TRUE;
5797  while ((c=*p++))
5798  {
5799  char encChar[4];
5800  if ((c>='0' && c<='9') || (c>='a' && c<='z') || (c>='A' && c<='Z') || c=='-' || c==':' || c=='.')
5801  { // any permissive character except _
5802  if (first && c>='0' && c<='9') growBuf.addChar('a'); // don't start with a digit
5803  growBuf.addChar(c);
5804  }
5805  else
5806  {
5807  encChar[0]='_';
5808  encChar[1]=hex[((unsigned char)c)>>4];
5809  encChar[2]=hex[((unsigned char)c)&0xF];
5810  encChar[3]=0;
5811  growBuf.addStr(encChar);
5812  }
5813  first=FALSE;
5814  }
5815  growBuf.addChar(0);
5816  return growBuf.get();
5817 }

5820 QCString convertToXML(const char *s)
5821 {

5823  growBuf.clear();
5824  if (s==0) return "";
5825  const char *p=s;
5826  char c;
5827  while ((c=*p++))
5828  {
5829  switch (c)
5830  {
5831  case '<': growBuf.addStr("&lt;"); break;
5832  case '>': growBuf.addStr("&gt;"); break;
5833  case '&': growBuf.addStr("&amp;"); break;
5834  case '\'': growBuf.addStr("&apos;"); break;
5835  case '"': growBuf.addStr("&quot;"); break;
5836  case 1: case 2: case 3: case 4: case 5: case 6: case 7: case 8:
5837  case 11: case 12: case 13: case 14: case 15: case 16: case 17: case 18:
5838  case 19: case 20: case 21: case 22: case 23: case 24: case 25: case 26:
5839  case 27: case 28: case 29: case 30: case 31:
5840  break; // skip invalid XML characters (see http://www.w3.org/TR/2000/REC-xml-20001006#NT-Char)
5841  default: growBuf.addChar(c); break;
5842  }
5843  }
5844  growBuf.addChar(0);
5845  return growBuf.get();

5849 QCString convertToHtml(const char *s,bool keepEntities)
5850 {
5851  static GrowBuf growBuf;
5852  growBuf.clear();
5853  if (s==0) return "";
5854  const char *p=s;
5855  char c;
5856  while ((c=*p++))
5857  {
5858  switch (c)
5859  {
5860  case '<': growBuf.addStr("&lt;"); break;
5861  case '>': growBuf.addStr("&gt;"); break;
5862  case '&': if (keepEntities)
5863  {
5864  const char *e=p;
5865  char ce;
5866  while ((ce=*e++))
5867  {
5868  if (ce==';' || (!(isId(ce) || ce=='#'))) break;
5869  }
5870  if (ce==';') // found end of an entity
5871  {
5872  // copy entry verbatim
5873  growBuf.addChar(c);
5874  while (p<e) growBuf.addChar(*p++);
5875  }
5876  else
5877  {
5878  growBuf.addStr("&amp;");
5879  }
5880  }
5881  else
5882  {
5883  growBuf.addStr("&amp;");
5884  }
5885  break;
5886  case '\'': growBuf.addStr("&#39;"); break;
5887  case '"': growBuf.addStr("&quot;"); break;
5888  default: growBuf.addChar(c); break;
5889  }
5890  }
5891  growBuf.addChar(0);
5892  return growBuf.get();
5893 }

5925 QCString convertCharEntitiesToUTF8(const QCString &s)
5926 {
5927  QCString result;
5928  static QRegExp entityPat("&[a-zA-Z]+[0-9]*;");
5929 
5930  if (s.length()==0) return result;
5931  static GrowBuf growBuf;
5932  growBuf.clear();
5933  int p,i=0,l;
5934  while ((p=entityPat.match(s,i,&l))!=-1)
5935  {
5936  if (p>i)
5937  {
5938  growBuf.addStr(s.mid(i,p-i));
5939  }
5940  QCString entity = s.mid(p,l);
5941  DocSymbol::SymType symType = HtmlEntityMapper::instance()->name2sym(entity);
5942  const char *code=0;
5943  if (symType!=DocSymbol::Sym_Unknown && (code=HtmlEntityMapper::instance()->utf8(symType)))
5944  {
5945  growBuf.addStr(code);
5946  }
5947  else
5948  {
5949  growBuf.addStr(s.mid(p,l));
5950  }
5951  i=p+l;
5952  }
5953  growBuf.addStr(s.mid(i,s.length()-i));
5954  growBuf.addChar(0);
5955  //printf("convertCharEntitiesToUTF8(%s)->%s\n",s.data(),growBuf.get());
5956  return growBuf.get();
5957 }

5962 QCString getOverloadDocs()
5963 {
5964  return theTranslator->trOverloadText();
5965  //"This is an overloaded member function, "
5966  // "provided for convenience. It differs from the above "
5967  // "function only in what argument(s) it accepts.";
5968 }

5970 void addMembersToMemberGroup(MemberList *ml,
5971  MemberGroupSDict **ppMemberGroupSDict,
5972  Definition *context)
5973 {
5974  ASSERT(context!=0);
5975  //printf("addMemberToMemberGroup()\n");
5976  if (ml==0) return;
5977  MemberListIterator mli(*ml);
5978  MemberDef *md;
5979  uint index;
5980  for (index=0;(md=mli.current());)
5981  {
5982  if (md->isEnumerate()) // insert enum value of this enum into groups
5983  {
5984  MemberList *fmdl=md->enumFieldList();
5985  if (fmdl!=0)
5986  {
5987  MemberListIterator fmli(*fmdl);
5988  MemberDef *fmd;
5989  for (fmli.toFirst();(fmd=fmli.current());++fmli)
5990  {
5991  int groupId=fmd->getMemberGroupId();
5992  if (groupId!=-1)

5995  //QCString *pGrpHeader = Doxygen::memberHeaderDict[groupId];
5996  //QCString *pDocs = Doxygen::memberDocDict[groupId];
5997  if (info)
5998  {
5999  if (*ppMemberGroupSDict==0)
6000  {
6001  *ppMemberGroupSDict = new MemberGroupSDict;
6002  (*ppMemberGroupSDict)->setAutoDelete(TRUE);
6003  }

6005  if (mg==0)

6012  info->docFile,
6013  info->docLine
6014  );
6015  (*ppMemberGroupSDict)->append(groupId,mg);
6016  }
6017  mg->insertMember(fmd); // insert in member group
6018  fmd->setMemberGroup(mg);
6019  }
6020  }
6021  }
6022  }
6023  }
6024  int groupId=md->getMemberGroupId();
6025  if (groupId!=-1)
6026  {
6027  MemberGroupInfo *info = Doxygen::memGrpInfoDict[groupId];
6028  //QCString *pGrpHeader = Doxygen::memberHeaderDict[groupId];
6029  //QCString *pDocs = Doxygen::memberDocDict[groupId];
6030  if (info)
6031  {
6032  if (*ppMemberGroupSDict==0)
6033  {
6034  *ppMemberGroupSDict = new MemberGroupSDict;
6035  (*ppMemberGroupSDict)->setAutoDelete(TRUE);
6036  }
6037  MemberGroup *mg = (*ppMemberGroupSDict)->find(groupId);
6038  if (mg==0)
6039  {

6041  context,
6042  groupId,
6043  info->header,
6044  info->doc,
6045  info->docFile,
6046  info->docLine
6047  );
6048  (*ppMemberGroupSDict)->append(groupId,mg);
6049  }
6050  md = ml->take(index); // remove from member list
6051  mg->insertMember(md); // insert in member group
6052  mg->setRefItems(info->m_sli);
6053  md->setMemberGroup(mg);
6054  continue;
6055  }
6056  }
6057  ++mli;++index;
6058  }
6059 }
6060 
6066 int extractClassNameFromType(const QCString &type,int &pos,QCString &name,QCString &templSpec,SrcLangExt lang)
6067 {
6068  static const QRegExp re_norm("[a-z_A-Z\\x80-\\xFF][a-z_A-Z0-9:\\x80-\\xFF]*");
6069  static const QRegExp re_ftn("[a-z_A-Z\\x80-\\xFF][()=_a-z_A-Z0-9:\\x80-\\xFF]*");
6070  QRegExp re;
6071 
6072  name.resize(0);
6073  templSpec.resize(0);
6074  int i,l;
6075  int typeLen=type.length();
6076  if (typeLen>0)
6077  {
6078  if (lang == SrcLangExt_Fortran)
6079  {
6080  if (type.at(pos)==',') return -1;
6081  if (type.left(4).lower()=="type")
6082  {
6083  re = re_norm;
6084  }
6085  else
6086  {
6087  re = re_ftn;
6088  }
6089  }
6090  else
6091  {
6092  re = re_norm;
6093  }
6094 
6095  if ((i=re.match(type,pos,&l))!=-1) // for each class name in the type
6096  {
6097  int ts=i+l;
6098  int te=ts;
6099  int tl=0;
6100  while (type.at(ts)==' ' && ts<typeLen) ts++,tl++; // skip any whitespace
6101  if (type.at(ts)=='<') // assume template instance
6102  {
6103  // locate end of template
6104  te=ts+1;
6105  int brCount=1;
6106  while (te<typeLen && brCount!=0)
6107  {
6108  if (type.at(te)=='<')
6109  {
6110  if (te<typeLen-1 && type.at(te+1)=='<') te++; else brCount++;
6111  }
6112  if (type.at(te)=='>')
6113  {
6114  if (te<typeLen-1 && type.at(te+1)=='>') te++; else brCount--;
6115  }
6116  te++;
6117  }
6118  }
6119  name = type.mid(i,l);
6120  if (te>ts)
6121  {
6122  templSpec = type.mid(ts,te-ts),tl+=te-ts;
6123  pos=i+l+tl;
6124  }
6125  else // no template part
6126  {
6127  pos=i+l;
6128  }
6129  //printf("extractClassNameFromType([in] type=%s,[out] pos=%d,[out] name=%s,[out] templ=%s)=TRUE\n",
6130  // type.data(),pos,name.data(),templSpec.data());
6131  return i;
6132  }
6133  }
6134  pos = typeLen;
6135  //printf("extractClassNameFromType([in] type=%s,[out] pos=%d,[out] name=%s,[out] templ=%s)=FALSE\n",
6136  // type.data(),pos,name.data(),templSpec.data());
6137  return -1;
6138 }
6139 
6140 QCString normalizeNonTemplateArgumentsInString(
6141  const QCString &name,
6142  Definition *context,
6143  const ArgumentList * formalArgs)
6144 {
6145  // skip until <
6146  int p=name.find('<');
6147  if (p==-1) return name;
6148  p++;
6149  QCString result = name.left(p);
6150 
6151  static QRegExp re("[a-z:_A-Z\\x80-\\xFF][a-z:_A-Z0-9\\x80-\\xFF]*");
6152  int l,i;
6153  // for each identifier in the template part (e.g. B<T> -> T)
6154  while ((i=re.match(name,p,&l))!=-1)
6155  {
6156  result += name.mid(p,i-p);
6157  QCString n = name.mid(i,l);
6158  bool found=FALSE;
6159  if (formalArgs) // check that n is not a formal template argument
6160  {
6161  ArgumentListIterator formAli(*formalArgs);
6162  Argument *formArg;
6163  for (formAli.toFirst();
6164  (formArg=formAli.current()) && !found;
6165  ++formAli
6166  )
6167  {
6168  found = formArg->name==n;
6169  }
6170  }
6171  if (!found)
6172  {
6173  // try to resolve the type
6174  ClassDef *cd = getResolvedClass(context,0,n);
6175  if (cd)
6176  {
6177  result+=cd->name();
6178  }
6179  else
6180  {
6181  result+=n;
6182  }
6183  }
6184  else
6185  {
6186  result+=n;
6187  }
6188  p=i+l;
6189  }
6190  result+=name.right(name.length()-p);
6191  //printf("normalizeNonTemplateArgumentInString(%s)=%s\n",name.data(),result.data());
6192  return removeRedundantWhiteSpace(result);
6193 }
6194 
6195 
6202 QCString substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(
6203  const QCString &name,
6204  ArgumentList *formalArgs,
6205  ArgumentList *actualArgs)
6206 {
6207  //printf("substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(name=%s formal=%s actualArg=%s)\n",
6208  // name.data(),argListToString(formalArgs).data(),argListToString(actualArgs).data());
6209  if (formalArgs==0) return name;
6210  QCString result;
6211  static QRegExp re("[a-z_A-Z\\x80-\\xFF][a-z_A-Z0-9\\x80-\\xFF]*");
6212  int p=0,l,i;
6213  // for each identifier in the base class name (e.g. B<T> -> B and T)
6214  while ((i=re.match(name,p,&l))!=-1)
6215  {
6216  result += name.mid(p,i-p);
6217  QCString n = name.mid(i,l);
6218  ArgumentListIterator formAli(*formalArgs);
6219  ArgumentListIterator actAli(*actualArgs);
6220  Argument *formArg;
6221  Argument *actArg;
6222 
6223  // if n is a template argument, then we substitute it
6224  // for its template instance argument.
6225  bool found=FALSE;
6226  for (formAli.toFirst();
6227  (formArg=formAli.current()) && !found;
6228  ++formAli,++actAli
6229  )
6230  {
6231  actArg = actAli.current();
6232  if (formArg->type.left(6)=="class " && formArg->name.isEmpty())
6233  {
6234  formArg->name = formArg->type.mid(6);
6235  formArg->type = "class";
6236  }
6237  if (formArg->type.left(9)=="typename " && formArg->name.isEmpty())
6238  {
6239  formArg->name = formArg->type.mid(9);
6240  formArg->type = "typename";
6241  }
6242  if (formArg->type=="class" || formArg->type=="typename" || formArg->type.left(8)=="template")
6243  {
6244  //printf("n=%s formArg->type='%s' formArg->name='%s' formArg->defval='%s'\n",
6245  // n.data(),formArg->type.data(),formArg->name.data(),formArg->defval.data());
6246  //printf(">> formArg->name='%s' actArg->type='%s' actArg->name='%s'\n",
6247  // formArg->name.data(),actArg ? actArg->type.data() : "",actArg ? actArg->name.data() : ""
6248  // );
6249  if (formArg->name==n && actArg && !actArg->type.isEmpty()) // base class is a template argument
6250  {
6251  // replace formal argument with the actual argument of the instance
6252  if (!leftScopeMatch(actArg->type,n))
6253  // the scope guard is to prevent recursive lockup for
6254  // template<class A> class C : public<A::T>,
6255  // where A::T would become A::T::T here,
6256  // since n==A and actArg->type==A::T
6257  // see bug595833 for an example
6258  {
6259  if (actArg->name.isEmpty())
6260  {
6261  result += actArg->type+" ";
6262  found=TRUE;
6263  }
6264  else
6265  // for case where the actual arg is something like "unsigned int"
6266  // the "int" part is in actArg->name.
6267  {
6268  result += actArg->type+" "+actArg->name+" ";
6269  found=TRUE;
6270  }
6271  }
6272  }
6273  else if (formArg->name==n &&
6274  actArg==0 &&
6275  !formArg->defval.isEmpty() &&
6276  formArg->defval!=name /* to prevent recursion */
6277  )
6278  {
6279  result += substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(formArg->defval,formalArgs,actualArgs)+" ";
6280  found=TRUE;
6281  }
6282  }
6283  else if (formArg->name==n &&
6284  actArg==0 &&
6285  !formArg->defval.isEmpty() &&
6286  formArg->defval!=name /* to prevent recursion */
6287  )
6288  {
6289  result += substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(formArg->defval,formalArgs,actualArgs)+" ";
6290  found=TRUE;
6291  }
6292  }
6293  if (!found)
6294  {
6295  result += n;
6296  }
6297  p=i+l;
6298  }
6299  result+=name.right(name.length()-p);
6300  //printf(" Inheritance relation %s -> %s\n",
6301  // name.data(),result.data());
6302  return result.stripWhiteSpace();
6303 }

6308 QList<ArgumentList> *copyArgumentLists(const QList<ArgumentList> *srcLists)
6309 {
6310  ASSERT(srcLists!=0);
6311  QList<ArgumentList> *dstLists = new QList<ArgumentList>;
6312  dstLists->setAutoDelete(TRUE);
6313  QListIterator<ArgumentList> sli(*srcLists);
6314  ArgumentList *sl;
6315  for (;(sl=sli.current());++sli)
6316  {
6317  dstLists->append(sl->deepCopy());
6318  }
6319  return dstLists;
6320 }
6321 
6329 QCString stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(const QCString &fullName,
6330  bool parentOnly,
6331  QCString *pLastScopeStripped)
6332 {
6333  QCString result;
6334  int p=0;
6335  int l=fullName.length();
6336  int i=fullName.find('<');
6337  while (i!=-1)
6338  {
6339  //printf("1:result+=%s\n",fullName.mid(p,i-p).data());
6340  int e=i+1;
6341  bool done=FALSE;
6342  int count=1;
6343  while (e<l && !done)
6344  {
6345  char c=fullName.at(e++);
6346  if (c=='<')
6347  {
6348  count++;
6349  }
6350  else if (c=='>')
6351  {
6352  count--;
6353  done = count==0;
6354  }
6355  }
6356  int si= fullName.find("::",e);
6357 
6358  if (parentOnly && si==-1) break;
6359  // we only do the parent scope, so we stop here if needed
6360 
6361  result+=fullName.mid(p,i-p);
6362  //printf(" trying %s\n",(result+fullName.mid(i,e-i)).data());
6363  if (getClass(result+fullName.mid(i,e-i))!=0)
6364  {
6365  result+=fullName.mid(i,e-i);
6366  //printf(" 2:result+=%s\n",fullName.mid(i,e-i-1).data());
6367  }
6368  else if (pLastScopeStripped)
6369  {
6370  //printf(" last stripped scope '%s'\n",fullName.mid(i,e-i).data());
6371  *pLastScopeStripped=fullName.mid(i,e-i);
6372  }
6373  p=e;
6374  i=fullName.find('<',p);
6375  }
6376  result+=fullName.right(l-p);
6377  //printf("3:result+=%s\n",fullName.right(l-p).data());
6378  return result;
6379 }
6380 
6390 QCString mergeScopes(const QCString &leftScope,const QCString &rightScope)
6391 {
6392  // case leftScope=="A" rightScope=="A::B" => result = "A::B"
6393  if (leftScopeMatch(rightScope,leftScope)) return rightScope;
6394  QCString result;
6395  int i=0,p=leftScope.length();
6396 
6397  // case leftScope=="A::B" rightScope=="B::C" => result = "A::B::C"
6398  // case leftScope=="A::B" rightScope=="B" => result = "A::B"
6399  bool found=FALSE;
6400  while ((i=leftScope.findRev("::",p))!=-1)
6401  {
6402  if (leftScopeMatch(rightScope,leftScope.right(leftScope.length()-i-2)))
6403  {
6404  result = leftScope.left(i+2)+rightScope;
6405  found=TRUE;
6406  }
6407  p=i-1;
6408  }
6409  if (found) return result;
6410 
6411  // case leftScope=="A" rightScope=="B" => result = "A::B"
6412  result=leftScope.copy();
6413  if (!result.isEmpty() && !rightScope.isEmpty()) result+="::";
6414  result+=rightScope;
6415  return result;
6416 }
6417 
6425 int getScopeFragment(const QCString &s,int p,int *l)
6426 {
6427  int sl=s.length();
6428  int sp=p;
6429  int count=0;
6430  bool done;
6431  if (sp>=sl) return -1;
6432  while (sp<sl)
6433  {
6434  char c=s.at(sp);
6435  if (c==':') sp++,p++; else break;
6436  }
6437  while (sp<sl)
6438  {
6439  char c=s.at(sp);
6440  switch (c)
6441  {
6442  case ':': // found next part
6443  goto found;
6444  case '<': // skip template specifier
6445  count=1;sp++;
6446  done=FALSE;
6447  while (sp<sl && !done)
6448  {
6449  // TODO: deal with << and >> operators!
6450  char c=s.at(sp++);
6451  switch(c)
6452  {
6453  case '<': count++; break;
6454  case '>': count--; if (count==0) done=TRUE; break;
6455  default: break;
6456  }
6457  }
6458  break;
6459  default:
6460  sp++;
6461  break;
6462  }
6463  }
6464 found:
6465  *l=sp-p;
6466  //printf("getScopeFragment(%s,%d)=%s\n",s.data(),p,s.mid(p,*l).data());
6467  return p;
6468 }

6472 PageDef *addRelatedPage(const char *name,const QCString &ptitle,
6473  const QCString &doc,
6474  QList<SectionInfo> * /*anchors*/,
6475  const char *fileName,int startLine,
6476  const QList<ListItemInfo> *sli,
6477  GroupDef *gd,
6478  TagInfo *tagInfo,
6479  SrcLangExt lang
6480  )
6481 {
6482  PageDef *pd=0;
6483  //printf("addRelatedPage(name=%s gd=%p)\n",name,gd);
6484  if ((pd=Doxygen::pageSDict->find(name)) && !tagInfo)
6485  {
6486  // append documentation block to the page.
6487  pd->setDocumentation(doc,fileName,startLine);
6488  //printf("Adding page docs `%s' pi=%p name=%s\n",doc.data(),pd,name);
6489  }
6490  else // new page
6491  {
6492  QCString baseName=name;
6493  if (baseName.right(4)==".tex")
6494  baseName=baseName.left(baseName.length()-4);
6495  else if (baseName.right(Doxygen::htmlFileExtension.length())==Doxygen::htmlFileExtension)
6496  baseName=baseName.left(baseName.length()-Doxygen::htmlFileExtension.length());
6497 
6498  QCString title=ptitle.stripWhiteSpace();
6499  pd=new PageDef(fileName,startLine,baseName,doc,title);
6500 
6501  pd->setRefItems(sli);
6502  pd->setLanguage(lang);
6503 
6504  if (tagInfo)
6505  {
6506  pd->setReference(tagInfo->tagName);
6507  pd->setFileName(tagInfo->fileName);
6508  }
6509 
6510  //printf("Appending page `%s'\n",baseName.data());
6511  Doxygen::pageSDict->append(baseName,pd);
6512 
6513  if (gd) gd->addPage(pd);
6514 
6515  if (!pd->title().isEmpty())
6516  {
6517  //outputList->writeTitle(pi->name,pi->title);
6518 
6519  // a page name is a label as well!
6520  QCString file;
6521  if (gd)
6522  {
6523  file=gd->getOutputFileBase();
6524  }
6525  else
6526  {
6527  file=pd->getOutputFileBase();
6528  }
6529  SectionInfo *si = Doxygen::sectionDict->find(pd->name());
6530  if (si)
6531  {
6532  if (si->lineNr != -1)
6533  {
6534  warn(file,-1,"multiple use of section label '%s', (first occurrence: %s, line %d)",pd->name().data(),si->fileName.data(),si->lineNr);
6535  }
6536  else
6537  {
6538  warn(file,-1,"multiple use of section label '%s', (first occurrence: %s)",pd->name().data(),si->fileName.data());
6539  }
6540  }
6541  else
6542  {
6543  si=new SectionInfo(
6544  file,-1,pd->name(),pd->title(),SectionInfo::Page,0,pd->getReference());
6545  //printf("si->label=`%s' si->definition=%s si->fileName=`%s'\n",
6546  // si->label.data(),si->definition?si->definition->name().data():"<none>",
6547  // si->fileName.data());
6548  //printf(" SectionInfo: sec=%p sec->fileName=%s\n",si,si->fileName.data());
6549  //printf("Adding section key=%s si->fileName=%s\n",pageName.data(),si->fileName.data());
6550  Doxygen::sectionDict->append(pd->name(),si);
6551  }
6552  }
6553  }
6554  return pd;
6555 }

6559 void addRefItem(const QList<ListItemInfo> *sli,
6560  const char *key,
6561  const char *prefix, const char *name,const char *title,const char *args,Definition *scope)
6562 {
6563  //printf("addRefItem(sli=%p,key=%s,prefix=%s,name=%s,title=%s,args=%s)\n",sli,key,prefix,name,title,args);
6564  if (sli && key && key[0]!='@') // check for @ to skip anonymous stuff (see bug427012)
6565  {
6566  QListIterator<ListItemInfo> slii(*sli);
6567  ListItemInfo *lii;
6568  for (slii.toFirst();(lii=slii.current());++slii)
6569  {
6570  RefList *refList = Doxygen::xrefLists->find(lii->type);
6571  if (refList
6572  &&
6573  (
6574  // either not a built-in list or the list is enabled
6575  (lii->type!="todo" || Config_getBool(GENERATE_TODOLIST)) &&
6576  (lii->type!="test" || Config_getBool(GENERATE_TESTLIST)) &&
6577  (lii->type!="bug" || Config_getBool(GENERATE_BUGLIST)) &&
6578  (lii->type!="deprecated" || Config_getBool(GENERATE_DEPRECATEDLIST))
6579  )
6580  )
6581  {
6582  RefItem *item = refList->getRefItem(lii->itemId);
6583  ASSERT(item!=0);
6584 
6585  item->prefix = prefix;
6586  item->scope = scope;
6587  item->name = name;
6588  item->title = title;
6589  item->args = args;
6590 
6591  refList->insertIntoList(key,item);
6592 
6593  }
6594  }
6595  }
6596 }

6598 bool recursivelyAddGroupListToTitle(OutputList &ol,Definition *d,bool root)
6599 {
6600  GroupList *groups = d->partOfGroups();
6601  if (groups) // write list of group to which this definition belongs
6602  {
6603  if (root)
6604  {
6605  ol.pushGeneratorState();
6606  ol.disableAllBut(OutputGenerator::Html);
6607  ol.writeString("<div class=\"ingroups\">");
6608  }
6609  GroupListIterator gli(*groups);
6610  GroupDef *gd;
6611  bool first=true;
6612  for (gli.toFirst();(gd=gli.current());++gli)
6613  {
6614  if (recursivelyAddGroupListToTitle(ol, gd, FALSE))
6615  {
6616  ol.writeString(" &raquo; ");
6617  }
6618  if (!first) { ol.writeString(" &#124; "); } else first=FALSE;
6619  ol.writeObjectLink(gd->getReference(),gd->getOutputFileBase(),0,gd->groupTitle());
6620  }
6621  if (root)
6622  {
6623  ol.writeString("</div>");
6624  ol.popGeneratorState();
6625  }
6626  return true;
6627  }
6628  return false;
6629 }

6631 void addGroupListToTitle(OutputList &ol,Definition *d)
6632 {
6633  recursivelyAddGroupListToTitle(ol,d,TRUE);
6634 }
6635 
6636 void filterLatexString(FTextStream &t,const char *str,
6637  bool insideTabbing,bool insidePre,bool insideItem,bool keepSpaces)
6638 {
6639  if (str==0) return;
6640  //if (strlen(str)<2) stackTrace();
6641  const unsigned char *p=(const unsigned char *)str;
6642  const unsigned char *q;
6643  int cnt;
6644  unsigned char c;
6645  unsigned char pc='\0';
6646  while (*p)
6647  {
6648  c=*p++;
6649 
6650  if (insidePre)
6651  {
6652  switch(c)
6653  {
6654  case '\\': t << "\\(\\backslash\\)"; break;
6655  case '{': t << "\\{"; break;
6656  case '}': t << "\\}"; break;
6657  case '_': t << "\\_"; break;
6658  case ' ': if (keepSpaces) t << "~"; else t << ' ';
6659  break;
6660  default:
6661  t << (char)c;
6662  break;
6663  }
6664  }
6665  else
6666  {
6667  switch(c)
6668  {
6669  case '#': t << "\\#"; break;
6670  case '$': t << "\\$"; break;
6671  case '%': t << "\\%"; break;
6672  case '^': t << "$^\\wedge$"; break;
6673  case '&': // possibility to have a special symbol
6674  q = p;
6675  cnt = 2; // we have to count & and ; as well
6676  while ((*q >= 'a' && *q <= 'z') || (*q >= 'A' && *q <= 'Z') || (*q >= '0' && *q <= '9'))
6677  {
6678  cnt++;
6679  q++;
6680  }
6681  if (*q == ';')
6682  {
6683  --p; // we need & as well
6684  DocSymbol::SymType res = HtmlEntityMapper::instance()->name2sym(QCString((char *)p).left(cnt));
6685  if (res == DocSymbol::Sym_Unknown)
6686  {
6687  p++;
6688  t << "\\&";
6689  }
6690  else
6691  {
6692  t << HtmlEntityMapper::instance()->latex(res);
6693  q++;
6694  p = q;
6695  }
6696  }
6697  else
6698  {
6699  t << "\\&";
6700  }
6701  break;
6702  case '*': t << "$\\ast$"; break;
6703  case '_': if (!insideTabbing) t << "\\+";
6704  t << "\\_";
6705  if (!insideTabbing) t << "\\+";
6706  break;
6707  case '{': t << "\\{"; break;
6708  case '}': t << "\\}"; break;
6709  case '<': t << "$<$"; break;
6710  case '>': t << "$>$"; break;
6711  case '|': t << "$\\vert$"; break;
6712  case '~': t << "$\\sim$"; break;
6713  case '[': if (Config_getBool(PDF_HYPERLINKS) || insideItem)
6714  t << "\\mbox{[}";
6715  else
6716  t << "[";
6717  break;
6718  case ']': if (pc=='[') t << "$\\,$";
6719  if (Config_getBool(PDF_HYPERLINKS) || insideItem)
6720  t << "\\mbox{]}";
6721  else
6722  t << "]";
6723  break;
6724  case '-': t << "-\\/";
6725  break;
6726  case '\\': t << "\\textbackslash{}";
6727  break;
6728  case '"': t << "\\char`\\\"{}";
6729  break;
6730  case '\'': t << "\\textquotesingle{}";
6731  break;
6732  case ' ': if (keepSpaces) { if (insideTabbing) t << "\\>"; else t << '~'; } else t << ' ';
6733  break;
6734 
6735  default:
6736  //if (!insideTabbing && forceBreaks && c!=' ' && *p!=' ')
6737  if (!insideTabbing &&
6738  ((c>='A' && c<='Z' && pc!=' ' && pc!='\0' && *p) || (c==':' && pc!=':') || (pc=='.' && isId(c)))
6739  )
6740  {
6741  t << "\\+";
6742  }
6743  t << (char)c;
6744  }
6745  }
6746  pc = c;
6747  }
6748 }

6750 QCString latexEscapeLabelName(const char *s,bool insideTabbing)
6751 {
6752  QGString result;
6753  QCString tmp(qstrlen(s)+1);
6754  FTextStream t(&result);
6755  const char *p=s;
6756  char c;
6757  int i;
6758  while ((c=*p++))
6759  {
6760  switch (c)
6761  {
6762  case '|': t << "\\texttt{\"|}"; break;
6763  case '!': t << "\"!"; break;
6764  case '@': t << "\"@"; break;
6765  case '%': t << "\\%"; break;
6766  case '{': t << "\\lcurly{}"; break;
6767  case '}': t << "\\rcurly{}"; break;
6768  case '~': t << "````~"; break; // to get it a bit better in index together with other special characters
6769  // NOTE: adding a case here, means adding it to while below as well!
6770  default:
6771  i=0;
6772  // collect as long string as possible, before handing it to docify
6773  tmp[i++]=c;
6774  while ((c=*p) && c!='@' && c!='[' && c!=']' && c!='!' && c!='{' && c!='}' && c!='|')
6775  {
6776  tmp[i++]=c;
6777  p++;
6778  }
6779  tmp[i]=0;
6780  filterLatexString(t,tmp.data(),insideTabbing);
6781  break;
6782  }
6783  }
6784  return result.data();
6785 }

6849 
6850 QCString rtfFormatBmkStr(const char *name)
6851 {
6852  static QCString g_nextTag( "AAAAAAAAAA" );
6853  static QDict<QCString> g_tagDict( 5003 );
6854 
6855  g_tagDict.setAutoDelete(TRUE);
6856 
6857  // To overcome the 40-character tag limitation, we
6858  // substitute a short arbitrary string for the name
6859  // supplied, and keep track of the correspondence
6860  // between names and strings.
6861  QCString key( name );
6862  QCString* tag = g_tagDict.find( key );
6863  if ( !tag )
6864  {
6865  // This particular name has not yet been added
6866  // to the list. Add it, associating it with the
6867  // next tag value, and increment the next tag.
6868  tag = new QCString( g_nextTag.copy() ); // Make sure to use a deep copy!
6869  g_tagDict.insert( key, tag );
6870 
6871  // This is the increment part
6872  char* nxtTag = g_nextTag.rawData() + g_nextTag.length() - 1;
6873  for ( unsigned int i = 0; i < g_nextTag.length(); ++i, --nxtTag )
6874  {
6875  if ( ( ++(*nxtTag) ) > 'Z' )
6876  {
6877  *nxtTag = 'A';
6878  }
6879  else
6880  {
6881  // Since there was no carry, we can stop now
6882  break;
6883  }
6884  }
6885  }
6886 
6887  return *tag;
6888 }

6917  {

6942 bool containsWord(const QCString &s,const QCString &word)
6943 {
6944  static QRegExp wordExp("[a-z_A-Z\\x80-\\xFF]+");
6945  int p=0,i,l;
6946  while ((i=wordExp.match(s,p,&l))!=-1)
6947  {
6948  if (s.mid(i,l)==word) return TRUE;
6949  p=i+l;
6950  }
6951  return FALSE;
6952 }
6953 
6954 bool findAndRemoveWord(QCString &s,const QCString &word)
6955 {
6956  static QRegExp wordExp("[a-z_A-Z\\x80-\\xFF]+");
6957  int p=0,i,l;
6958  while ((i=wordExp.match(s,p,&l))!=-1)
6959  {
6960  if (s.mid(i,l)==word)
6961  {
6962  if (i>0 && isspace((uchar)s.at(i-1)))
6963  i--,l++;
6964  else if (i+l<(int)s.length() && isspace(s.at(i+l)))
6965  l++;
6966  s = s.left(i)+s.mid(i+l); // remove word + spacing
6967  return TRUE;
6968  }
6969  p=i+l;
6970  }
6971  return FALSE;
6972 }
6973 
6982 QCString stripLeadingAndTrailingEmptyLines(const QCString &s,int &docLine)
6983 {
6984  const char *p = s.data();
6985  if (p==0) return 0;
6986 
6987  // search for leading empty lines
6988  int i=0,li=-1,l=s.length();
6989  char c;
6990  while ((c=*p++))
6991  {
6992  if (c==' ' || c=='\t' || c=='\r') i++;
6993  else if (c=='\n') i++,li=i,docLine++;
6994  else break;
6995  }
6996 
6997  // search for trailing empty lines
6998  int b=l-1,bi=-1;
6999  p=s.data()+b;
7000  while (b>=0)
7001  {
7002  c=*p; p--;
7003  if (c==' ' || c=='\t' || c=='\r') b--;
7004  else if (c=='\n') bi=b,b--;
7005  else break;
7006  }
7007 
7008  // return whole string if no leading or trailing lines where found
7009  if (li==-1 && bi==-1) return s;
7010 
7011  // return substring
7012  if (bi==-1) bi=l;
7013  if (li==-1) li=0;
7014  if (bi<=li) return 0; // only empty lines
7015  return s.mid(li,bi-li);
7016 }

7071 bool updateLanguageMapping(const QCString &extension,const QCString &language)
7072 {
7073  const Lang2ExtMap *p = g_lang2extMap;
7074  QCString langName = language.lower();
7075  while (p->langName)
7076  {
7077  if (langName==p->langName) break;
7078  p++;
7079  }
7080  if (!p->langName) return FALSE;
7081 
7082  // found the language
7083  SrcLangExt parserId = p->parserId;
7084  QCString extName = extension.lower();
7085  if (extName.isEmpty()) return FALSE;
7086  if (extName.at(0)!='.') extName.prepend(".");
7087  if (g_extLookup.find(extension)!=0) // language was already register for this ext
7088  {
7089  g_extLookup.remove(extension);
7090  }
7091  //printf("registering extension %s\n",extName.data());
7092  g_extLookup.insert(extName,new int(parserId));
7093  if (!Doxygen::parserManager->registerExtension(extName,p->parserName))
7094  {
7095  err("Failed to assign extension %s to parser %s for language %s\n",
7096  extName.data(),p->parserName,language.data());
7097  }
7098  else
7099  {
7100  //msg("Registered extension %s to language parser %s...\n",
7101  // extName.data(),language.data());
7102  }
7103  return TRUE;
7104 }

7172 SrcLangExt getLanguageFromFileName(const QCString fileName)
7173 {

7175  if (i!=-1) // name has an extension
7176  {
7177  QCString extStr=fileName.right(fileName.length()-i).lower();
7178  if (!extStr.isEmpty()) // non-empty extension
7179  {
7180  int *pVal=g_extLookup.find(extStr);
7181  if (pVal) // listed extension
7182  {
7183  //printf("getLanguageFromFileName(%s)=%x\n",extStr.data(),*pVal);
7184  return (SrcLangExt)*pVal;
7185  }
7186  }
7187  }
7188  //printf("getLanguageFromFileName(%s) not found!\n",fileName.data());
7189  return SrcLangExt_Cpp; // not listed => assume C-ish language.
7190 }

7192 //--------------------------------------------------------------------------
7193 
7194 MemberDef *getMemberFromSymbol(Definition *scope,FileDef *fileScope,
7195  const char *n)
7196 {
7197  if (scope==0 ||
7198  (scope->definitionType()!=Definition::TypeClass &&
7199  scope->definitionType()!=Definition::TypeNamespace
7200  )
7201  )
7202  {
7203  scope=Doxygen::globalScope;
7204  }
7205 
7206  QCString name = n;
7207  if (name.isEmpty())
7208  return 0; // no name was given
7209 
7210  DefinitionIntf *di = Doxygen::symbolMap->find(name);
7211  if (di==0)
7212  return 0; // could not find any matching symbols
7213 
7214  // mostly copied from getResolvedClassRec()
7215  QCString explicitScopePart;
7216  int qualifierIndex = computeQualifiedIndex(name);
7217  if (qualifierIndex!=-1)
7218  {
7219  explicitScopePart = name.left(qualifierIndex);
7220  replaceNamespaceAliases(explicitScopePart,explicitScopePart.length());
7221  name = name.mid(qualifierIndex+2);
7222  }
7223  //printf("explicitScopePart=%s\n",explicitScopePart.data());
7224 
7225  int minDistance = 10000;
7226  MemberDef *bestMatch = 0;
7227 
7228  if (di->definitionType()==DefinitionIntf::TypeSymbolList)
7229  {
7230  //printf("multiple matches!\n");
7231  // find the closest closest matching definition
7232  DefinitionListIterator dli(*(DefinitionList*)di);
7233  Definition *d;
7234  for (dli.toFirst();(d=dli.current());++dli)
7235  {
7236  if (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeMember)
7237  {
7238  g_visitedNamespaces.clear();
7239  int distance = isAccessibleFromWithExpScope(scope,fileScope,d,explicitScopePart);
7240  if (distance!=-1 && distance<minDistance)
7241  {
7242  minDistance = distance;
7243  bestMatch = (MemberDef *)d;
7244  //printf("new best match %s distance=%d\n",bestMatch->qualifiedName().data(),distance);
7245  }
7246  }
7247  }
7248  }
7249  else if (di->definitionType()==Definition::TypeMember)
7250  {
7251  //printf("unique match!\n");
7252  Definition *d = (Definition *)di;
7253  g_visitedNamespaces.clear();
7254  int distance = isAccessibleFromWithExpScope(scope,fileScope,d,explicitScopePart);
7255  if (distance!=-1 && distance<minDistance)
7256  {
7257  minDistance = distance;
7258  bestMatch = (MemberDef *)d;
7259  //printf("new best match %s distance=%d\n",bestMatch->qualifiedName().data(),distance);
7260  }
7261  }
7262  return bestMatch;
7263 }
7264 
7266 bool checkIfTypedef(Definition *scope,FileDef *fileScope,const char *n)
7267 {
7268  MemberDef *bestMatch = getMemberFromSymbol(scope,fileScope,n);
7269 
7270  if (bestMatch && bestMatch->isTypedef())
7271  return TRUE; // closest matching symbol is a typedef
7272  else
7273  return FALSE;
7274 }
7275 
7276 const char *writeUtf8Char(FTextStream &t,const char *s)
7277 {
7278  char c=*s++;
7279  t << c;
7280  if (c<0) // multibyte character
7281  {
7282  if (((uchar)c&0xE0)==0xC0)
7283  {
7284  t << *s++; // 11xx.xxxx: >=2 byte character
7285  }
7286  if (((uchar)c&0xF0)==0xE0)
7287  {
7288  t << *s++; // 111x.xxxx: >=3 byte character
7289  }
7290  if (((uchar)c&0xF8)==0xF0)
7291  {
7292  t << *s++; // 1111.xxxx: >=4 byte character
7293  }
7294  if (((uchar)c&0xFC)==0xF8)
7295  {
7296  t << *s++; // 1111.1xxx: >=5 byte character
7297  }
7298  if (((uchar)c&0xFE)==0xFC)
7299  {
7300  t << *s++; // 1111.1xxx: 6 byte character
7301  }
7302  }
7303  return s;
7304 }
7305 
7306 int nextUtf8CharPosition(const QCString &utf8Str,int len,int startPos)
7307 {
7308  int bytes=1;
7309  if (startPos>=len) return len;
7310  char c = utf8Str[startPos];
7311  if (c<0) // multibyte utf-8 character
7312  {
7313  if (((uchar)c&0xE0)==0xC0)
7314  {
7315  bytes++; // 11xx.xxxx: >=2 byte character
7316  }
7317  if (((uchar)c&0xF0)==0xE0)
7318  {
7319  bytes++; // 111x.xxxx: >=3 byte character
7320  }
7321  if (((uchar)c&0xF8)==0xF0)
7322  {
7323  bytes++; // 1111.xxxx: >=4 byte character
7324  }
7325  if (((uchar)c&0xFC)==0xF8)
7326  {
7327  bytes++; // 1111.1xxx: >=5 byte character
7328  }
7329  if (((uchar)c&0xFE)==0xFC)
7330  {
7331  bytes++; // 1111.1xxx: 6 byte character
7332  }
7333  }
7334  else if (c=='&') // skip over character entities
7335  {
7336  static QRegExp re1("&#[0-9]+;"); // numerical entity
7337  static QRegExp re2("&[A-Z_a-z]+;"); // named entity
7338  int l1,l2;
7339  int i1 = re1.match(utf8Str,startPos,&l1);
7340  int i2 = re2.match(utf8Str,startPos,&l2);
7341  if (i1!=-1)
7342  {
7343  bytes=l1;
7344  }
7345  else if (i2!=-1)
7346  {
7347  bytes=l2;
7348  }
7349  }
7350  return startPos+bytes;
7351 }
7352 
7353 QCString parseCommentAsText(const Definition *scope,const MemberDef *md,
7354  const QCString &doc,const QCString &fileName,int lineNr)
7355 {
7356  QGString s;
7357  if (doc.isEmpty()) return s.data();
7358  FTextStream t(&s);
7359  DocNode *root = validatingParseDoc(fileName,lineNr,
7360  (Definition*)scope,(MemberDef*)md,doc,FALSE,FALSE);
7361  TextDocVisitor *visitor = new TextDocVisitor(t);
7362  root->accept(visitor);
7363  delete visitor;
7364  delete root;
7365  QCString result = convertCharEntitiesToUTF8(s.data());
7366  int i=0;
7367  int charCnt=0;
7368  int l=result.length();
7369  bool addEllipsis=FALSE;
7370  while ((i=nextUtf8CharPosition(result,l,i))<l)
7371  {
7372  charCnt++;
7373  if (charCnt>=80) break;
7374  }
7375  if (charCnt>=80) // try to truncate the string
7376  {
7377  while ((i=nextUtf8CharPosition(result,l,i))<l && charCnt<100)
7378  {
7379  charCnt++;
7380  if (result.at(i)>=0 && isspace(result.at(i)))
7381  {
7382  addEllipsis=TRUE;
7383  }
7384  else if (result.at(i)==',' ||
7385  result.at(i)=='.' ||
7386  result.at(i)=='?')
7387  {
7388  break;
7389  }
7390  }
7391  }
7392  if (addEllipsis || charCnt==100) result=result.left(i)+"...";
7393  return result.data();
7394 }
7395 
7396 //--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7397 
7398 static QDict<void> aliasesProcessed;
7399 
7400 static QCString expandAliasRec(const QCString s,bool allowRecursion=FALSE);
7401 
7402 struct Marker
7403 {
7404  Marker(int p, int n,int s) : pos(p),number(n),size(s) {}
7405  int pos; // position in the string
7406  int number; // argument number
7407  int size; // size of the marker
7408 };
7409 
7420 static int findEndOfCommand(const char *s)
7421 {
7422  const char *p = s;
7423  char c;
7424  int i=0;
7425  if (p)
7426  {
7427  while ((c=*p) && isId(c)) p++;
7428  if (c=='{')
7429  {
7430  QCString args = extractAliasArgs(p,0);
7431  i+=args.length();
7432  }
7433  i+=p-s;
7434  }
7435  return i;
7436 }
7437 
7442 static QCString replaceAliasArguments(const QCString &aliasValue,const QCString &argList)
7443 {
7444  //printf("----- replaceAliasArguments(val=[%s],args=[%s])\n",aliasValue.data(),argList.data());
7445 
7446  // first make a list of arguments from the comma separated argument list
7447  QList<QCString> args;
7448  args.setAutoDelete(TRUE);
7449  int i,l=(int)argList.length();
7450  int s=0;
7451  for (i=0;i<l;i++)
7452  {
7453  char c = argList.at(i);
7454  if (c==',' && (i==0 || argList.at(i-1)!='\\'))
7455  {
7456  args.append(new QCString(argList.mid(s,i-s)));
7457  s=i+1; // start of next argument
7458  }
7459  else if (c=='@' || c=='\\')
7460  {
7461  // check if this is the start of another aliased command (see bug704172)
7462  i+=findEndOfCommand(argList.data()+i+1);
7463  }
7464  }
7465  if (l>s) args.append(new QCString(argList.right(l-s)));
7466  //printf("found %d arguments\n",args.count());
7467 
7468  // next we look for the positions of the markers and add them to a list
7469  QList<Marker> markerList;
7470  markerList.setAutoDelete(TRUE);
7471  l = aliasValue.length();
7472  int markerStart=0;
7473  int markerEnd=0;
7474  for (i=0;i<l;i++)
7475  {
7476  if (markerStart==0 && aliasValue.at(i)=='\\') // start of a \xx marker
7477  {
7478  markerStart=i+1;
7479  }
7480  else if (markerStart>0 && aliasValue.at(i)>='0' && aliasValue.at(i)<='9')
7481  {
7482  // read digit that make up the marker number
7483  markerEnd=i+1;
7484  }
7485  else
7486  {
7487  if (markerStart>0 && markerEnd>markerStart) // end of marker
7488  {
7489  int markerLen = markerEnd-markerStart;
7490  markerList.append(new Marker(markerStart-1, // include backslash
7491  atoi(aliasValue.mid(markerStart,markerLen)),markerLen+1));
7492  //printf("found marker at %d with len %d and number %d\n",
7493  // markerStart-1,markerLen+1,atoi(aliasValue.mid(markerStart,markerLen)));
7494  }
7495  markerStart=0; // outside marker
7496  markerEnd=0;
7497  }
7498  }
7499  if (markerStart>0)
7500  {
7501  markerEnd=l;
7502  }
7503  if (markerStart>0 && markerEnd>markerStart)
7504  {
7505  int markerLen = markerEnd-markerStart;
7506  markerList.append(new Marker(markerStart-1, // include backslash
7507  atoi(aliasValue.mid(markerStart,markerLen)),markerLen+1));
7508  //printf("found marker at %d with len %d and number %d\n",
7509  // markerStart-1,markerLen+1,atoi(aliasValue.mid(markerStart,markerLen)));
7510  }
7511 
7512  // then we replace the markers with the corresponding arguments in one pass
7513  QCString result;
7514  int p=0;
7515  for (i=0;i<(int)markerList.count();i++)
7516  {
7517  Marker *m = markerList.at(i);
7518  result+=aliasValue.mid(p,m->pos-p);
7519  //printf("part before marker %d: '%s'\n",i,aliasValue.mid(p,m->pos-p).data());
7520  if (m->number>0 && m->number<=(int)args.count()) // valid number
7521  {
7522  result+=expandAliasRec(*args.at(m->number-1),TRUE);
7523  //printf("marker index=%d pos=%d number=%d size=%d replacement %s\n",i,m->pos,m->number,m->size,
7524  // args.at(m->number-1)->data());
7525  }
7526  p=m->pos+m->size; // continue after the marker
7527  }
7528  result+=aliasValue.right(l-p); // append remainder
7529  //printf("string after replacement of markers: '%s'\n",result.data());
7530 
7531  // expand the result again
7532  result = substitute(result,"\\{","{");
7533  result = substitute(result,"\\}","}");
7534  result = expandAliasRec(substitute(result,"\\,",","));
7535 
7536  return result;
7537 }
7538 
7539 static QCString escapeCommas(const QCString &s)
7540 {
7541  QGString result;
7542  const char *p = s.data();
7543  char c,pc=0;
7544  while ((c=*p++))
7545  {
7546  if (c==',' && pc!='\\')
7547  {
7548  result+="\\,";
7549  }
7550  else
7551  {
7552  result+=c;
7553  }
7554  pc=c;
7555  }
7556  result+='\0';
7557  //printf("escapeCommas: '%s'->'%s'\n",s.data(),result.data());
7558  return result.data();
7559 }
7560 
7561 static QCString expandAliasRec(const QCString s,bool allowRecursion)
7562 {
7563  QCString result;
7564  static QRegExp cmdPat("[\\\\@][a-z_A-Z][a-z_A-Z0-9]*");
7565  QCString value=s;
7566  int i,p=0,l;
7567  while ((i=cmdPat.match(value,p,&l))!=-1)
7568  {
7569  result+=value.mid(p,i-p);
7570  QCString args = extractAliasArgs(value,i+l);
7571  bool hasArgs = !args.isEmpty(); // found directly after command
7572  int argsLen = args.length();
7573  QCString cmd = value.mid(i+1,l-1);
7574  QCString cmdNoArgs = cmd;
7575  int numArgs=0;
7576  if (hasArgs)
7577  {
7578  numArgs = countAliasArguments(args);
7579  cmd += QCString().sprintf("{%d}",numArgs); // alias name + {n}
7580  }
7581  QCString *aliasText=Doxygen::aliasDict.find(cmd);
7582  if (numArgs>1 && aliasText==0)
7583  { // in case there is no command with numArgs parameters, but there is a command with 1 parameter,
7584  // we also accept all text as the argument of that command (so you don't have to escape commas)
7585  aliasText=Doxygen::aliasDict.find(cmdNoArgs+"{1}");
7586  if (aliasText)
7587  {
7588  cmd = cmdNoArgs+"{1}";
7589  args = escapeCommas(args); // escape , so that everything is seen as one argument
7590  }
7591  }
7592  //printf("Found command s='%s' cmd='%s' numArgs=%d args='%s' aliasText=%s\n",
7593  // s.data(),cmd.data(),numArgs,args.data(),aliasText?aliasText->data():"<none>");
7594  if ((allowRecursion || aliasesProcessed.find(cmd)==0) && aliasText) // expand the alias
7595  {
7596  //printf("is an alias!\n");
7597  if (!allowRecursion) aliasesProcessed.insert(cmd,(void *)0x8);
7598  QCString val = *aliasText;
7599  if (hasArgs)
7600  {
7601  val = replaceAliasArguments(val,args);
7602  //printf("replace '%s'->'%s' args='%s'\n",
7603  // aliasText->data(),val.data(),args.data());
7604  }
7605  result+=expandAliasRec(val);
7606  if (!allowRecursion) aliasesProcessed.remove(cmd);
7607  p=i+l;
7608  if (hasArgs) p+=argsLen+2;
7609  }
7610  else // command is not an alias
7611  {
7612  //printf("not an alias!\n");
7613  result+=value.mid(i,l);
7614  p=i+l;
7615  }
7616  }
7617  result+=value.right(value.length()-p);
7618 
7619  //printf("expandAliases '%s'->'%s'\n",s.data(),result.data());
7620  return result;
7621 }
7622 
7623 
7624 int countAliasArguments(const QCString argList)
7625 {
7626  int count=1;
7627  int l = argList.length();
7628  int i;
7629  for (i=0;i<l;i++)
7630  {
7631  char c = argList.at(i);
7632  if (c==',' && (i==0 || argList.at(i-1)!='\\')) count++;
7633  else if (c=='@' || c=='\\')
7634  {
7635  // check if this is the start of another aliased command (see bug704172)
7636  i+=findEndOfCommand(argList.data()+i+1);
7637  }
7638  }
7639  //printf("countAliasArguments=%d\n",count);
7640  return count;
7641 }
7642 
7643 QCString extractAliasArgs(const QCString &args,int pos)
7644 {
7645  int i;
7646  int bc=0;
7647  char prevChar=0;
7648  if (args.at(pos)=='{') // alias has argument
7649  {
7650  for (i=pos;i<(int)args.length();i++)
7651  {
7652  if (prevChar!='\\')
7653  {
7654  if (args.at(i)=='{') bc++;
7655  if (args.at(i)=='}') bc--;
7656  prevChar=args.at(i);
7657  }
7658  else
7659  {
7660  prevChar=0;
7661  }
7662 
7663  if (bc==0)
7664  {
7665  //printf("extractAliasArgs('%s')->'%s'\n",args.data(),args.mid(pos+1,i-pos-1).data());
7666  return args.mid(pos+1,i-pos-1);
7667  }
7668  }
7669  }
7670  return "";
7671 }
7672 
7673 QCString resolveAliasCmd(const QCString aliasCmd)
7674 {
7675  QCString result;
7676  aliasesProcessed.clear();
7677  //printf("Expanding: '%s'\n",aliasCmd.data());
7678  result = expandAliasRec(aliasCmd);
7679  //printf("Expanding result: '%s'->'%s'\n",aliasCmd.data(),result.data());
7680  return result;
7681 }
7682 
7683 QCString expandAlias(const QCString &aliasName,const QCString &aliasValue)
7684 {
7685  QCString result;
7686  aliasesProcessed.clear();
7687  // avoid expanding this command recursively
7688  aliasesProcessed.insert(aliasName,(void *)0x8);
7689  // expand embedded commands
7690  //printf("Expanding: '%s'->'%s'\n",aliasName.data(),aliasValue.data());
7691  result = expandAliasRec(aliasValue);
7692  //printf("Expanding result: '%s'->'%s'\n",aliasName.data(),result.data());
7693  return result;
7694 }

7696 void writeTypeConstraints(OutputList &ol,Definition *d,ArgumentList *al)
7697 {
7698  if (al==0) return;
7699  ol.startConstraintList(theTranslator->trTypeConstraints());
7700  ArgumentListIterator ali(*al);

7703  {

7705  ol.parseText(a->name);
7706  ol.endConstraintParam();
7707  ol.startConstraintType();
7708  linkifyText(TextGeneratorOLImpl(ol),d,0,0,a->type);
7709  ol.endConstraintType();

7711  ol.generateDoc(d->docFile(),d->docLine(),d,0,a->docs,TRUE,FALSE);
7712  ol.endConstraintDocs();
7713  }
7714  ol.endConstraintList();
7715 }

7719 void stackTrace()
7720 {
7721 #ifdef TRACINGSUPPORT
7722  void *backtraceFrames[128];
7723  int frameCount = backtrace(backtraceFrames, 128);
7724  static char cmd[40960];
7725  char *p = cmd;
7726  p += sprintf(p,"/usr/bin/atos -p %d ", (int)getpid());
7727  for (int x = 0; x < frameCount; x++)
7728  {
7729  p += sprintf(p,"%p ", backtraceFrames[x]);
7730  }
7731  fprintf(stderr,"========== STACKTRACE START ==============\n");
7732  if (FILE *fp = popen(cmd, "r"))
7733  {
7734  char resBuf[512];
7735  while (size_t len = fread(resBuf, 1, sizeof(resBuf), fp))
7736  {
7737  fwrite(resBuf, 1, len, stderr);
7738  }
7739  pclose(fp);
7740  }
7741  fprintf(stderr,"============ STACKTRACE END ==============\n");
7742  //fprintf(stderr,"%s\n", frameStrings[x]);
7743 #endif
7744 }
7745 
7746 static int transcodeCharacterBuffer(const char *fileName,BufStr &srcBuf,int size,
7747  const char *inputEncoding,const char *outputEncoding)
7748 {
7749  if (inputEncoding==0 || outputEncoding==0) return size;
7750  if (qstricmp(inputEncoding,outputEncoding)==0) return size;
7751  void *cd = portable_iconv_open(outputEncoding,inputEncoding);
7752  if (cd==(void *)(-1))
7753  {
7754  err("unsupported character conversion: '%s'->'%s': %s\n"
7755  "Check the INPUT_ENCODING setting in the config file!\n",
7756  inputEncoding,outputEncoding,strerror(errno));
7757  exit(1);
7758  }
7759  int tmpBufSize=size*4+1;
7760  BufStr tmpBuf(tmpBufSize);
7761  size_t iLeft=size;
7762  size_t oLeft=tmpBufSize;
7763  char *srcPtr = srcBuf.data();
7764  char *dstPtr = tmpBuf.data();
7765  uint newSize=0;
7766  if (!portable_iconv(cd, &srcPtr, &iLeft, &dstPtr, &oLeft))
7767  {
7768  newSize = tmpBufSize-(int)oLeft;
7769  srcBuf.shrink(newSize);
7770  strncpy(srcBuf.data(),tmpBuf.data(),newSize);
7771  //printf("iconv: input size=%d output size=%d\n[%s]\n",size,newSize,srcBuf.data());
7772  }
7773  else
7774  {
7775  err("%s: failed to translate characters from %s to %s: check INPUT_ENCODING\n",
7776  fileName,inputEncoding,outputEncoding);
7777  exit(1);
7778  }
7779  portable_iconv_close(cd);
7780  return newSize;
7781 }
7782 
7784 bool readInputFile(const char *fileName,BufStr &inBuf,bool filter,bool isSourceCode)
7785 {
7786  // try to open file
7787  int size=0;
7788  //uint oldPos = dest.curPos();
7789  //printf(".......oldPos=%d\n",oldPos);
7790 
7791  QFileInfo fi(fileName);
7792  if (!fi.exists()) return FALSE;
7793  QCString filterName = getFileFilter(fileName,isSourceCode);
7794  if (filterName.isEmpty() || !filter)
7795  {
7796  QFile f(fileName);
7797  if (!f.open(IO_ReadOnly))
7798  {
7799  err("could not open file %s\n",fileName);
7800  return FALSE;
7801  }
7802  size=fi.size();
7803  // read the file
7804  inBuf.skip(size);
7805  if (f.readBlock(inBuf.data()/*+oldPos*/,size)!=size)
7806  {
7807  err("problems while reading file %s\n",fileName);
7808  return FALSE;
7809  }
7810  }
7811  else
7812  {
7813  QCString cmd=filterName+" \""+fileName+"\"";
7814  Debug::print(Debug::ExtCmd,0,"Executing popen(`%s`)\n",qPrint(cmd));
7815  FILE *f=portable_popen(cmd,"r");
7816  if (!f)
7817  {
7818  err("could not execute filter %s\n",filterName.data());
7819  return FALSE;
7820  }
7821  const int bufSize=1024;
7822  char buf[bufSize];
7823  int numRead;
7824  while ((numRead=(int)fread(buf,1,bufSize,f))>0)
7825  {
7826  //printf(">>>>>>>>Reading %d bytes\n",numRead);
7827  inBuf.addArray(buf,numRead),size+=numRead;
7828  }
7829  portable_pclose(f);
7830  inBuf.at(inBuf.curPos()) ='\0';
7831  Debug::print(Debug::FilterOutput, 0, "Filter output\n");
7832  Debug::print(Debug::FilterOutput,0,"-------------\n%s\n-------------\n",qPrint(inBuf));
7833  }
7834 
7835  int start=0;
7836  if (size>=2 &&
7837  ((inBuf.at(0)==-1 && inBuf.at(1)==-2) || // Litte endian BOM
7838  (inBuf.at(0)==-2 && inBuf.at(1)==-1) // big endian BOM
7839  )
7840  ) // UCS-2 encoded file
7841  {
7842  transcodeCharacterBuffer(fileName,inBuf,inBuf.curPos(),
7843  "UCS-2","UTF-8");
7844  }
7845  else if (size>=3 &&
7846  (uchar)inBuf.at(0)==0xEF &&
7847  (uchar)inBuf.at(1)==0xBB &&
7848  (uchar)inBuf.at(2)==0xBF
7849  ) // UTF-8 encoded file
7850  {
7851  inBuf.dropFromStart(3); // remove UTF-8 BOM: no translation needed
7852  }
7853  else // transcode according to the INPUT_ENCODING setting
7854  {
7855  // do character transcoding if needed.
7856  transcodeCharacterBuffer(fileName,inBuf,inBuf.curPos(),
7857  Config_getString(INPUT_ENCODING),"UTF-8");
7858  }
7859 
7860  //inBuf.addChar('\n'); /* to prevent problems under Windows ? */
7861 
7862  // and translate CR's
7863  size=inBuf.curPos()-start;
7864  int newSize=filterCRLF(inBuf.data()+start,size);
7865  //printf("filter char at %p size=%d newSize=%d\n",dest.data()+oldPos,size,newSize);
7866  if (newSize!=size) // we removed chars
7867  {
7868  inBuf.shrink(newSize); // resize the array
7869  //printf(".......resizing from %d to %d result=[%s]\n",oldPos+size,oldPos+newSize,dest.data());
7870  }
7871  inBuf.addChar(0);
7872  return TRUE;
7873 }
7874 
7875 // Replace %word by word in title
7876 QCString filterTitle(const QCString &title)
7877 {
7878  QCString tf;
7879  static QRegExp re("%[A-Z_a-z]");
7880  int p=0,i,l;
7881  while ((i=re.match(title,p,&l))!=-1)
7882  {
7883  tf+=title.mid(p,i-p);
7884  tf+=title.mid(i+1,l-1); // skip %
7885  p=i+l;
7886  }
7887  tf+=title.right(title.length()-p);
7888  return tf;
7889 }

7891 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
7892 // returns TRUE if the name of the file represented by `fi' matches
7893 // one of the file patterns in the `patList' list.
7894 
7895 bool patternMatch(const QFileInfo &fi,const QStrList *patList)
7896 {
7897  bool found=FALSE;
7898  if (patList)
7899  {
7900  QStrListIterator it(*patList);
7901  QCString pattern;
7902 
7903  QCString fn = fi.fileName().data();
7904  QCString fp = fi.filePath().data();
7905  QCString afp= fi.absFilePath().data();
7906 
7907  for (it.toFirst();(pattern=it.current());++it)
7908  {
7909  if (!pattern.isEmpty())
7910  {
7911  int i=pattern.find('=');
7912  if (i!=-1) pattern=pattern.left(i); // strip of the extension specific filter name
7913 
7914 #if defined(_WIN32) || defined(__MACOSX__) // Windows or MacOSX
7915  QRegExp re(pattern,FALSE,TRUE); // case insensitive match
7916 #else // unix
7917  QRegExp re(pattern,TRUE,TRUE); // case sensitive match
7918 #endif
7919  found = re.match(fn)!=-1 ||
7920  re.match(fp)!=-1 ||
7921  re.match(afp)!=-1;
7922  if (found) break;
7923  //printf("Matching `%s' against pattern `%s' found=%d\n",
7924  // fi->fileName().data(),pattern.data(),found);
7925  }
7926  }
7927  }
7928  return found;
7929 }

7967 QCString externalRef(const QCString &relPath,const QCString &ref,bool href)

8000 void writeColoredImgData(const char *dir,ColoredImgDataItem data[])
8001 {

8013  sat,hue,gamma);

8030 QCString replaceColorMarkers(const char *str)
8031 {
8032  QCString result;
8033  QCString s=str;
8034  if (s.isEmpty()) return result;
8035  static QRegExp re("##[0-9A-Fa-f][0-9A-Fa-f]");
8036  static const char hex[] = "0123456789ABCDEF";
8037  static int hue = Config_getInt(HTML_COLORSTYLE_HUE);
8038  static int sat = Config_getInt(HTML_COLORSTYLE_SAT);
8039  static int gamma = Config_getInt(HTML_COLORSTYLE_GAMMA);
8040  int i,l,sl=s.length(),p=0;
8041  while ((i=re.match(s,p,&l))!=-1)
8042  {
8043  result+=s.mid(p,i-p);
8044  QCString lumStr = s.mid(i+2,l-2);
8045 #define HEXTONUM(x) (((x)>='0' && (x)<='9') ? ((x)-'0') : \
8046  ((x)>='a' && (x)<='f') ? ((x)-'a'+10) : \
8047  ((x)>='A' && (x)<='F') ? ((x)-'A'+10) : 0)
8048 
8049  double r,g,b;
8050  int red,green,blue;
8051  int level = HEXTONUM(lumStr[0])*16+HEXTONUM(lumStr[1]);
8052  ColoredImage::hsl2rgb(hue/360.0,sat/255.0,
8053  pow(level/255.0,gamma/100.0),&r,&g,&b);
8054  red = (int)(r*255.0);
8055  green = (int)(g*255.0);
8056  blue = (int)(b*255.0);
8057  char colStr[8];
8058  colStr[0]='#';
8059  colStr[1]=hex[red>>4];
8060  colStr[2]=hex[red&0xf];
8061  colStr[3]=hex[green>>4];
8062  colStr[4]=hex[green&0xf];
8063  colStr[5]=hex[blue>>4];
8064  colStr[6]=hex[blue&0xf];
8065  colStr[7]=0;
8066  //printf("replacing %s->%s (level=%d)\n",lumStr.data(),colStr,level);
8067  result+=colStr;
8068  p=i+l;
8069  }
8070  result+=s.right(sl-p);
8071  return result;
8072 }

8077 bool copyFile(const QCString &src,const QCString &dest)
8078 {
8079  QFile sf(src);
8080  if (sf.open(IO_ReadOnly))
8081  {
8082  QFileInfo fi(src);
8083  QFile df(dest);
8084  if (df.open(IO_WriteOnly))
8085  {
8086  char *buffer = new char[fi.size()];
8087  sf.readBlock(buffer,fi.size());
8088  df.writeBlock(buffer,fi.size());
8089  df.flush();
8090  delete[] buffer;
8091  }
8092  else
8093  {
8094  err("could not write to file %s\n",dest.data());
8095  return FALSE;
8096  }
8097  }
8098  else
8099  {
8100  err("could not open user specified file %s\n",src.data());
8101  return FALSE;
8102  }
8103  return TRUE;
8104 }
8105 
8110 QCString extractBlock(const QCString text,const QCString marker)
8111 {
8112  QCString result;
8113  int p=0,i;
8114  bool found=FALSE;
8115 
8116  // find the character positions of the markers
8117  int m1 = text.find(marker);
8118  if (m1==-1) return result;
8119  int m2 = text.find(marker,m1+marker.length());
8120  if (m2==-1) return result;
8121 
8122  // find start and end line positions for the markers
8123  int l1=-1,l2=-1;
8124  while (!found && (i=text.find('\n',p))!=-1)
8125  {
8126  found = (p<=m1 && m1<i); // found the line with the start marker
8127  p=i+1;
8128  }
8129  l1=p;
8130  int lp=i;
8131  if (found)
8132  {
8133  while ((i=text.find('\n',p))!=-1)
8134  {
8135  if (p<=m2 && m2<i) // found the line with the end marker
8136  {
8137  l2=p;
8138  break;
8139  }
8140  p=i+1;
8141  lp=i;
8142  }
8143  }
8144  if (l2==-1) // marker at last line without newline (see bug706874)
8145  {
8146  l2=lp;
8147  }
8148  //printf("text=[%s]\n",text.mid(l1,l2-l1).data());
8149  return l2>l1 ? text.mid(l1,l2-l1) : QCString();
8150 }
8151 
8155 int lineBlock(const QCString text,const QCString marker)
8156 {
8157  int result = 1;
8158  int p=0,i;
8159  bool found=FALSE;
8160 
8161  // find the character positions of the first marker
8162  int m1 = text.find(marker);
8163  if (m1==-1) return result;
8164 
8165  // find start line positions for the markers
8166  while (!found && (i=text.find('\n',p))!=-1)
8167  {
8168  found = (p<=m1 && m1<i); // found the line with the start marker
8169  p=i+1;
8170  result++;
8171  }
8172  return result;
8173 }

8244 //---------------------------------------------------------------------------
8245 
8246 QCString stripIndentation(const QCString &s)
8247 {
8248  if (s.isEmpty()) return s; // empty string -> we're done
8249 
8250  //printf("stripIndentation:\n%s\n------\n",s.data());
8251  // compute minimum indentation over all lines
8252  const char *p=s.data();
8253  char c;
8254  int indent=0;
8255  int minIndent=1000000; // "infinite"
8256  bool searchIndent=TRUE;
8257  static int tabSize=Config_getInt(TAB_SIZE);
8258  while ((c=*p++))
8259  {
8260  if (c=='\t') indent+=tabSize - (indent%tabSize);
8261  else if (c=='\n') indent=0,searchIndent=TRUE;
8262  else if (c==' ') indent++;
8263  else if (searchIndent)
8264  {
8265  searchIndent=FALSE;
8266  if (indent<minIndent) minIndent=indent;
8267  }
8268  }
8269 
8270  // no indent to remove -> we're done
8271  if (minIndent==0) return s;
8272 
8273  // remove minimum indentation for each line
8274  QGString result;
8275  p=s.data();
8276  indent=0;
8277  while ((c=*p++))
8278  {
8279  if (c=='\n') // start of new line
8280  {
8281  indent=0;
8282  result+=c;
8283  }
8284  else if (indent<minIndent) // skip until we reach minIndent
8285  {
8286  if (c=='\t')
8287  {
8288  int newIndent = indent+tabSize-(indent%tabSize);
8289  int i=newIndent;
8290  while (i>minIndent) // if a tab crosses the minIndent boundary fill the rest with spaces
8291  {
8292  result+=' ';
8293  i--;
8294  }
8295  indent=newIndent;
8296  }
8297  else // space
8298  {
8299  indent++;
8300  }
8301  }
8302  else // copy anything until the end of the line
8303  {
8304  result+=c;
8305  }
8306  }
8307 
8308  result+='\0';
8309  return result.data();
8310 }

8325 void addDocCrossReference(MemberDef *src,MemberDef *dst)
8326 {
8327  static bool referencedByRelation = Config_getBool(REFERENCED_BY_RELATION);
8328  static bool referencesRelation = Config_getBool(REFERENCES_RELATION);
8329 
8330  //printf("--> addDocCrossReference src=%s,dst=%s\n",src->name().data(),dst->name().data());
8331  if (dst->isTypedef() || dst->isEnumerate()) return; // don't add types
8332  if ((referencedByRelation || dst->hasCallerGraph()) &&
8333  src->showInCallGraph()
8334  )

8340  mdDef->addSourceReferencedBy(src);
8341  }
8342  MemberDef *mdDecl = dst->memberDeclaration();
8343  if (mdDecl)
8344  {
8345  mdDecl->addSourceReferencedBy(src);
8346  }
8347  }
8348  if ((referencesRelation || src->hasCallGraph()) &&
8349  src->showInCallGraph()
8350  )
8351  {
8352  src->addSourceReferences(dst);
8353  MemberDef *mdDef = src->memberDefinition();
8354  if (mdDef)
8355  {
8356  mdDef->addSourceReferences(dst);
8357  }
8358  MemberDef *mdDecl = src->memberDeclaration();
8359  if (mdDecl)
8360  {
8361  mdDecl->addSourceReferences(dst);
8362  }
8363  }
8364 }

8376 uint getUtf8Code( const QCString& s, int idx )
8377 {
8378  const int length = s.length();
8379  if (idx >= length) { return 0; }
8380  const uint c0 = (uchar)s.at(idx);
8381  if ( c0 < 0xC2 || c0 >= 0xF8 ) // 1 byte character
8382  {
8383  return c0;
8384  }
8385  if (idx+1 >= length) { return 0; }
8386  const uint c1 = ((uchar)s.at(idx+1)) & 0x3f;
8387  if ( c0 < 0xE0 ) // 2 byte character
8388  {
8389  return ((c0 & 0x1f) << 6) | c1;
8390  }
8391  if (idx+2 >= length) { return 0; }
8392  const uint c2 = ((uchar)s.at(idx+2)) & 0x3f;
8393  if ( c0 < 0xF0 ) // 3 byte character
8394  {
8395  return ((c0 & 0x0f) << 12) | (c1 << 6) | c2;
8396  }
8397  if (idx+3 >= length) { return 0; }
8398  // 4 byte character
8399  const uint c3 = ((uchar)s.at(idx+3)) & 0x3f;
8400  return ((c0 & 0x07) << 18) | (c1 << 12) | (c2 << 6) | c3;
8401 }
8402 
8403 
8412 uint getUtf8CodeToLower( const QCString& s, int idx )
8413 {
8414  const uint v = getUtf8Code( s, idx );
8415  return v < 0x7f ? tolower( v ) : v;
8416 }

8418 
8427 uint getUtf8CodeToUpper( const QCString& s, int idx )
8428 {
8429  const uint v = getUtf8Code( s, idx );
8430  return v < 0x7f ? toupper( v ) : v;
8431 }

8435 bool namespaceHasVisibleChild(NamespaceDef *nd,bool includeClasses)

8444  {
8445  return TRUE;

8448  {
8449  return TRUE;
8450  }
8451  }
8452  }
8453  if (includeClasses && nd->getClassSDict())
8454  {
8455  ClassSDict::Iterator cli(*nd->getClassSDict());
8456  ClassDef *cd;
8457  for (;(cd=cli.current());++cli)

8459  if (cd->isLinkableInProject() && cd->templateMaster()==0)

8478 QCString extractDirection(QCString &docs)
8479 {
8480  QRegExp re("\\[[^\\]]+\\]"); // [...]
8481  int l=0;
8482  if (re.match(docs,0,&l)==0)
8483  {
8484  int inPos = docs.find("in", 1,FALSE);
8485  int outPos = docs.find("out",1,FALSE);
8486  bool input = inPos!=-1 && inPos<l;
8487  bool output = outPos!=-1 && outPos<l;
8488  if (input || output) // in,out attributes
8489  {
8490  docs = docs.mid(l); // strip attributes
8491  if (input && output) return "[in,out]";
8492  else if (input) return "[in]";
8493  else if (output) return "[out]";
8494  }
8495  }
8496  return QCString();
8497 }

8514 void convertProtectionLevel(
8515  MemberListType inListType,
8516  Protection inProt,
8517  int *outListType1,
8518  int *outListType2
8519  )
8520 {
8521  static bool extractPrivate = Config_getBool(EXTRACT_PRIVATE);
8522  // default representing 1-1 mapping
8523  *outListType1=inListType;
8524  *outListType2=-1;
8525  if (inProt==Public)
8526  {
8527  switch (inListType) // in the private section of the derived class,
8528  // the private section of the base class should not
8529  // be visible
8530  {
8531  case MemberListType_priMethods:
8532  case MemberListType_priStaticMethods:
8533  case MemberListType_priSlots:
8534  case MemberListType_priAttribs:
8535  case MemberListType_priStaticAttribs:
8536  case MemberListType_priTypes:
8537  *outListType1=-1;
8538  *outListType2=-1;
8539  break;
8540  default:
8541  break;
8542  }
8543  }
8544  else if (inProt==Protected) // Protected inheritance
8545  {
8546  switch (inListType) // in the protected section of the derived class,
8547  // both the public and protected members are shown
8548  // as protected
8549  {
8550  case MemberListType_pubMethods:
8551  case MemberListType_pubStaticMethods:
8552  case MemberListType_pubSlots:
8553  case MemberListType_pubAttribs:
8554  case MemberListType_pubStaticAttribs:
8555  case MemberListType_pubTypes:
8556  case MemberListType_priMethods:
8557  case MemberListType_priStaticMethods:
8558  case MemberListType_priSlots:
8559  case MemberListType_priAttribs:
8560  case MemberListType_priStaticAttribs:
8561  case MemberListType_priTypes:
8562  *outListType1=-1;
8563  *outListType2=-1;
8564  break;
8565 
8566  case MemberListType_proMethods:
8567  *outListType2=MemberListType_pubMethods;
8568  break;
8569  case MemberListType_proStaticMethods:
8570  *outListType2=MemberListType_pubStaticMethods;
8571  break;
8572  case MemberListType_proSlots:
8573  *outListType2=MemberListType_pubSlots;
8574  break;
8575  case MemberListType_proAttribs:
8576  *outListType2=MemberListType_pubAttribs;
8577  break;
8578  case MemberListType_proStaticAttribs:
8579  *outListType2=MemberListType_pubStaticAttribs;
8580  break;
8581  case MemberListType_proTypes:
8582  *outListType2=MemberListType_pubTypes;
8583  break;
8584  default:
8585  break;
8586  }
8587  }
8588  else if (inProt==Private)
8589  {
8590  switch (inListType) // in the private section of the derived class,
8591  // both the public and protected members are shown
8592  // as private
8593  {
8594  case MemberListType_pubMethods:
8595  case MemberListType_pubStaticMethods:
8596  case MemberListType_pubSlots:
8597  case MemberListType_pubAttribs:
8598  case MemberListType_pubStaticAttribs:
8599  case MemberListType_pubTypes:
8600  case MemberListType_proMethods:
8601  case MemberListType_proStaticMethods:
8602  case MemberListType_proSlots:
8603  case MemberListType_proAttribs:
8604  case MemberListType_proStaticAttribs:
8605  case MemberListType_proTypes:
8606  *outListType1=-1;
8607  *outListType2=-1;
8608  break;
8609 
8610  case MemberListType_priMethods:
8611  if (extractPrivate)
8612  {
8613  *outListType1=MemberListType_pubMethods;
8614  *outListType2=MemberListType_proMethods;
8615  }
8616  else
8617  {
8618  *outListType1=-1;
8619  *outListType2=-1;
8620  }
8621  break;
8622  case MemberListType_priStaticMethods:
8623  if (extractPrivate)
8624  {
8625  *outListType1=MemberListType_pubStaticMethods;
8626  *outListType2=MemberListType_proStaticMethods;
8627  }
8628  else
8629  {
8630  *outListType1=-1;
8631  *outListType2=-1;
8632  }
8633  break;
8634  case MemberListType_priSlots:
8635  if (extractPrivate)
8636  {
8637  *outListType1=MemberListType_pubSlots;
8638  *outListType2=MemberListType_proSlots;
8639  }
8640  else
8641  {
8642  *outListType1=-1;
8643  *outListType2=-1;
8644  }
8645  break;
8646  case MemberListType_priAttribs:
8647  if (extractPrivate)
8648  {
8649  *outListType1=MemberListType_pubAttribs;
8650  *outListType2=MemberListType_proAttribs;
8651  }
8652  else
8653  {
8654  *outListType1=-1;
8655  *outListType2=-1;
8656  }
8657  break;
8658  case MemberListType_priStaticAttribs:
8659  if (extractPrivate)
8660  {
8661  *outListType1=MemberListType_pubStaticAttribs;
8662  *outListType2=MemberListType_proStaticAttribs;
8663  }
8664  else
8665  {
8666  *outListType1=-1;
8667  *outListType2=-1;
8668  }
8669  break;
8670  case MemberListType_priTypes:
8671  if (extractPrivate)
8672  {
8673  *outListType1=MemberListType_pubTypes;
8674  *outListType2=MemberListType_proTypes;
8675  }
8676  else
8677  {
8678  *outListType1=-1;
8679  *outListType2=-1;
8680  }
8681  break;
8682  default:
8683  break;
8684  }
8685  }
8686  //printf("convertProtectionLevel(type=%d prot=%d): %d,%d\n",
8687  // inListType,inProt,*outListType1,*outListType2);
8688 }

8690 bool mainPageHasTitle()
8691 {
8692  if (Doxygen::mainPage==0) return FALSE;
8693  if (Doxygen::mainPage->title().isEmpty()) return FALSE;
8694  if (Doxygen::mainPage->title().lower()=="notitle") return FALSE;
8695  return TRUE;
8696 }

8698 QCString getDotImageExtension(void)
8699 {
8700  QCString imgExt = Config_getEnum(DOT_IMAGE_FORMAT);
8701  imgExt = imgExt.replace( QRegExp(":.*"), "" );
8702  return imgExt;
8703 }
8704 
8705 bool openOutputFile(const char *outFile,QFile &f)
8706 {
8707  bool fileOpened=FALSE;
8708  bool writeToStdout=(outFile[0]=='-' && outFile[1]=='\0');
8709  if (writeToStdout) // write to stdout
8710  {
8711  fileOpened = f.open(IO_WriteOnly,stdout);
8712  }
8713  else // write to file
8714  {
8715  QFileInfo fi(outFile);
8716  if (fi.exists()) // create a backup
8717  {
8718  QDir dir=fi.dir();
8719  QFileInfo backup(fi.fileName()+".bak");
8720  if (backup.exists()) // remove existing backup
8721  dir.remove(backup.fileName());
8722  dir.rename(fi.fileName(),fi.fileName()+".bak");
8723  }
8724  f.setName(outFile);
8725  fileOpened = f.open(IO_WriteOnly|IO_Translate);
8726  }
8727  return fileOpened;
8728 }
8729 
8730 void writeExtraLatexPackages(FTextStream &t)
8731 {
8732  // User-specified packages
8733  QStrList &extraPackages = Config_getList(EXTRA_PACKAGES);
8734  if (!extraPackages.isEmpty())
8735  {
8736  t << "% Packages requested by user\n";
8737  const char *pkgName=extraPackages.first();
8738  while (pkgName)
8739  {
8740  if ((pkgName[0] == '[') || (pkgName[0] == '{'))
8741  t << "\\usepackage" << pkgName << "\n";
8742  else
8743  t << "\\usepackage{" << pkgName << "}\n";
8744  pkgName=extraPackages.next();
8745  }
8746  t << "\n";
8747  }
8748 }
